title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach. Add cream cheese while spinach is hot and cream together well. Add mushroom soup. Pour into baking dish. Sprinkle top with onion rings. Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 15 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into casserole dish. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: succotash
directions: Combine corn and beans.
Add seasonings, butter and milk and heat slowly.
Serves 6.

title: chow mein noodle candy
directions: Melt morsels in double boiler.
Stir in noodles and nuts. Drop by spoonful on wax paper.
Refrigerate until time to eat. Enjoy.

title: raisin crisscross cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, sugar, egg, and extract. Blend flour, cream of tartar, soda, and salt. Stir into shortening mixture. Mix in raisins. Roll into 1-inch balls. Place 3-inch apart on ungreased baking sheet. Flatten with fork, making crisscross pattern. Bake at 400° for 8-10 minutes till edges begin to brown. Makes 3 dozen.

title: quick blueberry dessert
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream together the butter and sugar. Add the eggs and beat until light and fluffy. Add the vanilla extract. Stir in the flour and baking powder.

Mix until smooth. Butter a 13 x 9-inch cake pan and spread the mixture into the pan. Spoon pie filling into the cake in approximately 16 spots. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until the cake tests done. Filling will sink into the cake while baking. Serve with ice cream, whipped cream or dust with powdered sugar.

title: easy shrimp and rice dinner
directions: Melt margarine in separate frypan.
Add vegetables and cook until onion is clear.
Transfer to an automatic rice cooker, adding all ingredients. Stir well. Add salt and pepper.
With lid on, turn cooker on and cook 20 minutes on cook and 25 minutes on warm.

title: lime fruit salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water; chill and let thicken slightly.
Cut up fruit and add to jello.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, combine crackers and melted butter or oleo and set aside.
Place squash in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, cut side down.
Pour 1/4 way up dish with water.
Bake 40 minutes.
Turn squash and sprinkle with crumb mixture and bake 10 minutes more until squash is fork-tender.

title: cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add sugar and baking powder.
Fold in pecans and crushed Ritz crackers.
Add a pinch of salt.
Pour in a pie plate and bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Refrigerate overnight and top with whipped cream.

title: carrot relish
directions: Bring vinegar and sugar to a boil and pour over first 3 ingredients.
Add tomato soup and oil.
Mix together and refrigerate.
Very good with any roast.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; set aside.
Mix oil, eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until done.
Can add raisins, nuts or both.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Grease 9X13 pan.
Cut up mushrooms and place in pan.
Add oil and toss.
Combine dry ingredients and mix with mushrooms.
Cut butter into pats and place over dry ingredients in pan.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 25-30 minutes.

title: caramel icing(this is a great icing for german chocolate cake.)
directions: In a medium sized bowl, mix well all ingredients.
Spread on cake.
Refrigerate cake until served.

title: magic muffins
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Stir together until all ingredients are moistened.
Pour batter into a greased or paper-lined muffin pan, filling cups 3/4 full.
Bake on 400° for 18 to 20 minutes or until center is firm to the touch. Yield: 12 muffins.

title: southern roast beef
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Trim roast of all silver skin and trim the fat to 1/4-inch thick.
Lay the roast, fat-side up, in a 11 x 15-inch roasting pan (without rack).
Combine the blackened Steak Magic and the mustard in a small bowl.
Melt the butter over medium heat in a large, heavy pan.
Add the vegetables; saute 1 1/2 minutes more, stirring occasionally.
Add the garlic and saute 1 1/2 minutes more, stirring and scraping pan bottom well.
Remove from heat and pour mixture into glass bowl.

title: hot apple cider punch
directions: Heat all ingredients in a saucepan and simmer 20 minutes.

title: zippy beef biscuit casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown ground beef and onion; drain. Add diced green chilies, tomato sauce, chili powder and garlic powder. Heat until bubbly.

title: meat and potato casserole
directions: Toss potatoes with butter and salt, arrange on bottom and up sides of greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes at 400° or until tender.
Meanwhile, in a skillet, brown beef.
Sprinkle beef and corn over potatoes.
Combine soup, milk, garlic powder, pepper, onions and 1/2 cup cheese; pour over beef.
Bake at 400°, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven, top with remaining cheese and return to oven for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: daddy's venison pot roast
directions: Wash meat thoroughly and dry.
Add salt and pepper to all surfaces.
Make gashes on all sides and insert a thin slice of garlic in each.
Douse with Worcestershire.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in small amount of oil.
Add meat, brown until done.
Rinse meat under hot water to get rid of fat. Put back in pan, add tomatoes, corn, salt and chili powder to taste.
Stir cornmeal into boiling water.
Cover and cook 4 to 5 minutes, until a good mush.
Pour layer of mush in greased baking dish, layer of meat mixture and repeat, ending with meat mixture. Add grated cheese to top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter.
Add remaining ingredients and season to taste.
Bake in casserole in preheated 350° oven for 1/2 hour.
Serve hot with any kind of meat.

title: monkey bread
directions: Break biscuits into bottom of greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Pour butter on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: baked liver - 1871
directions: Lay pork strips in slits cut in liver.
Place onion in baking dish; place liver on it.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and flour mixture and pour tomatoes over.
Bake in oven at 350° until tender.

title: huntington chicken
directions: Stew and cube chicken.
Cook the macaroni.
Cube Velveeta cheese.
Save broth from chicken and thicken with flour.
Mix this together and place in the bottom of casserole dish.
Brown the crumbs and add cream; place on top of the casserole.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes in 8x11 or square pan.
Serves 6-8.

title: baptist slush
directions: Place in blender lemonade, orange juice, bananas (chopped) and pineapple (undrained juice-pak). Blend slowly. Stir in 7-Up. Pour into small plastic cups and freeze. Serve frozen.

title: party pups
directions: Separate biscuits into 20 pieces.
Spread each with mustard and sprinkle with cheese.
Wrap dough around wiener or sausage, pressing edges to seal.
Brush with egg; sprinkle with seed. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes, until golden brown.
Serve warm with additional mustard or sauce.

title: moist and creamy coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix.
Use 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool 15 minutes, then poke holes in it with a fork.
While cake is cooling, combine milk, sugar and 1/2 cup coconut.
Bring to boil, then simmer 1 minute. Carefully spoon over warm cake.
Fold 1/2 cup coconut into Cool Whip.
Spread on cake.
Sprinkle on rest of coconut.
Keep refrigerated.

title: strawberry butter
directions: Blend at high speed until smooth.
Chill.
Serve on toast, waffles or pancakes.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: hot or cold german potato salad
directions: Best if made a day in advance.
Serve on lettuce leaves and top with toasted sliced almonds.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Line muffin tins with liners.
Place one cookie in each. Combine remaining ingredients, except pie filling.
Mix well. Spoon mixture into each liner on top of cookies.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Remove liners (optional). Refrigerate until ready to serve.
In sunken spot, top with pie filling.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in large Dutch oven.
Bring to boil.
Cover and reduce heat; simmer until tender.
Remove chicken, reserving broth in Dutch oven.
Discard vegetables.
Let chicken cool.
Skin, bone and cut into bite sized pieces.
Skim fat from broth.
Bring broth to boil.
Add frozen vegetables and potatoes.
Simmer until tender.
Remove vegetables from broth. Measure 3 cups broth and set aside.

title: finger jello
directions: Soak Knox gelatine in 2 cups water for 15 minutes.
Mix jello, sugar and 2 1/2 cups water; boil until jello and sugar dissolves. Add to Knox gelatine mixture plus 1 cup cold water.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch oiled or "Pammed" pan.
Cut in squares.
Excellent source of protein.

title: perfect pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. With wire whisk, beat pumpkin, Eagle Brand, eggs, spices and salt. Pour into crust. Bake 15 minutes; reduce oven heat to 350°. Continue baking 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted 1-inch from crust comes out clean. Cool.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use approximately 1/4 cup mix for each cup of hot water.
Makes approximately 30 cups.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until creamy.
Add vanilla and water; beat well.
Gradually add flour and salt until well blended.
Add pecans or walnuts; mix well.
On greased (lightly) cookie sheet, roll dough into walnut size balls; prick 2 to 3 times for 12 to 15 minutes.
Let cookies cool for 1 minute, then remove from cookie sheet and roll in powdered sugar.
Let cool.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: graham cracker candy
directions: In a saucepan, combine the sugar, Pet milk and margarine and boil for 3 minutes.
Stir in the remaining ingredients and drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper to harden.

title: spiced peach salad
directions: Make jello with 2 juices according to instructions on box. Season cream cheese with mayonnaise and grated onion.
Seed peaches and stuff with cream cheese mixture.
Put peaches in individual molds.
Pour jello mixture on top of each peach. Congeal.
Use cream cheese mixture for dressing.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Mix sausage, Cheddar cheese and Bisquick.
Clean (seed) jalapeno peppers and stuff with a strip of Monterey Jack cheese. Wrap with sausage mix.
Dip in beaten eggs and roll in Shake 'N Bake (pork) or bread crumbs.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 35 minutes. Yield: 24 peppers.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Put in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan that has wax paper placed in bottom of pan.
To prepare frosting, bring to a boil the flour and milk; let cool. Cream together the butter, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy and then add to cool milk mixture.

title: old-fashioned sweet and sour beef borscht and cabbage
directions: In a large soup kettle or 5-quart Dutch oven, heat oil over high heat until hot.
Add beef and cook over high heat, turning, until browned on all sides, 5 to 7 minutes.
Add onions and carrots and cook, stirring often, over medium heat 3 to 5 minutes, until onions are golden brown.
Stir in garlic.
Add water; heat to boiling over high heat.
Skim off any residue that rises to the surface of the soup.
Stir in tomatoes.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add cabbage, salt, pepper and bay leaf. Simmer 1 hour longer.
Discard bay leaf.
Add lemon juice, brown sugar and drained beets.
Cook over low heat 15 minutes.
Stir in crushed gingersnaps.
Remove ribs with slotted spoon.
Cut meat into small pieces; discard bones.
Return to soup.
Taste and season with additional salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan. Layer coconut, then chopped pecans. Mix cake mix according to directions. Pour over top of nuts. Melt oleo, cream cheese and powdered sugar; mix and pour over cake mix. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour. Done when tested in center with a straw. Frost the top with 1 can prepared milk chocolate frosting (melt a little while in microwave) and pour over cake. This makes a big cake, so be sure to use a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: tomato soup salad
directions: Will need an 8 x 8-inch Pyrex or a 9 x 13-inch dish if doubled.

title: baked orange lamb steaks
directions: Arrange lamb in a shallow baking dish; sprinkle with salt. Top with oranges.
Blend together sugar, ginger, cloves, mint and butter.
Pour over lamb.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until desired degree of doneness.

title: corn chowder
directions: Peel the potatoes; dice and cook until fork-tender.
Drain; set aside.
Cook the bacon; save about 5 tablespoons bacon grease. Add about 6 or 7 tablespoons flour and brown.
Remove from heat. Add the milk.
Cook and stir on low until it thickens.
Add drained potatoes and the cream-style corn; heat.
Pour in bowl; crumble bacon on top.

title: crunchy snack mix
directions: Slice apple wedges; baste with melted butter.
Top with cinnamon.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: apple raisin snack cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend salad dressing, cake mix and eggs at low speed until moistened. Beat on medium speed 2 minutes. Add apples and raisins. Spread into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes. Cool.

title: chicken divan
directions: Either saute peppered chicken breasts or boil until done.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Cook broccoli for just a few minutes (will still be crisp).
Mix soup, mayonnaise, curry and lemon juice. Put broccoli on bottom of pan (1 1/2 or 2-quart baking dish), then chicken and cover with soup mixture evenly over top.
Top with cheese and sprinkle with bread crumbs, mixed with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, syrup, water and salt to hard crack stage.
Add butter and peanuts and boil until golden brown.
Remove from fire and add soda.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered pan or cookie sheet. When hard, break apart.

title: bridget's favorite salad
directions: Mix together & enjoy!

title: grandma's salad dressing cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Then add water and salad dressing.
Mix together until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured 9
x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center springs back.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Cook all vegetables separately, except peas and tomatoes.
Do not overcook!
In a 4-quart pot, melt 1 stick butter.
Add chicken broth, wine and lemon.
Bring to a boil.
Dissolve cornstarch in a small amount of water and add to chicken broth.
Broth will thicken.
Cook spaghetti as directed on box.

title: pickled tomato and pepper
directions: Wash green tomato and peppers.
Steam peppers and set aside. Mix vinegar, water and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Add tomatoes and peppers.
Cook until changes color.
Pack in pint jars, turn jars upside down until sealed.
Good with green beans.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into 2 greased bread pans.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: peanut butter log
directions: Mix Margarine, cracker crumbs, peanut butter and sugar.
Roll into 2 logs.
Refrigerate.
Cut into slices and serve.

title: cornbread dressing per nancy's mom
directions: Mix lightly the cornbread, eggs, onions, margarine, broth, salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Mix until ingredients are moistened.

title: peach custard pie
directions: Put in large bowl the flour, salt and margarine.
Mix with pastry blender until crumbly.
Press into 8-inch pan buttered on bottom and sides.
Drain large can peaches and save juice (1/2 cup).
Place sliced peaches over crust.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over peaches.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: caesar salad dressing
directions: Mix in blender until light gravy color.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Mix with other ingredients and cook in oven 45 minutes covered.
Uncover and cook 15 minutes longer. Remove from oven and cover.
Let set 5 minutes before serving.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix everything but the corn. Add corn.
Pour into a greased dish and bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: rice pilaf with peas
directions: In 12-inch skillet over medium heat, cook bacon until crisp. With slotted spoon, remove bacon to drain on paper towels.
Pour off all but 1/4 cup of drippings from skillet.
Add chopped onion to skillet and cook until tender.
Stir rice, frozen peas, water, chicken broth, salt and pepper into mixture; heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer about 20 minutes until rice is tender.

title: twice-baked yams
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Bake yams until tender, about 1 1/4 hours. Remove from oven and cut about 1/2-inch off the tops of the yams. Scoop out flesh from yams and tops, leaving a shell in the bottoms.
Discard tops.
Put flesh in large bowl and mash with 2 tablespoons of the butter, the milk and 1 teaspoon salt.
Place shells on baking sheet and fill with mashed yams.
In saucepan, melt remaining 2 tablespoons butter.
Stir in bread crumbs, remaining salt, thyme and pepper.
Top potato with bread crumb mixture.
Return to oven and bake until browned, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: oriental chicken
directions: You may add any vegetables that you like. You may substitute beef or seafood for chicken. Please use the cloves and curry powder sparingly (they are very strong).

title: smoked brisket
directions: Pour the liquid smoke over the brisket. Season with salt, celery salt and garlic salt. Cover with onions. Refrigerate overnight before cooking. Pour off liquid smoke and douse with Worcestershire sauce. Cover with foil and bake 4 to 5 hours at 275°. Uncover and pour on barbecue sauce (I use Masterpiece mesquite barbecue sauce). Bake for 1 hour. This is delicious!

title: swedish tea log
directions: Soften dry or cake yeast in warm water.
Sift together flour, salt and sugar.
Cut in or melt butter.
Add evaporated milk and egg.
Add softened yeast to mixture; mix well.
Cover.
Chill for 2 hours or overnight.
(Dough may be kept in refrigerator as long as 1 week.)
After dough has chilled and you are ready to make logs: cream butter and add brown sugar.
Cream well.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Divide dough into thirds.
Roll out one part on floured surface to a 12 x 6-inch rectangle.
Spread with 1/3 of the filling.
Roll up, starting with 12-inch side.
(Do not roll up like jelly roll.)
Fold both sides to center and press them together, then roll sides down.
Seal ends together so that filling will not run out of dough.
Place on foil lined cookie sheet. Repeat with remaining dough.
Let rise in warm place (85° to 90°) until light, about 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until light brown.
Top with Vanilla Glaze:

title: corn cheese chowder
directions: 1st layer - cup of lettuce.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients.
Form ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Serve with choice of crackers.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream together butter, shortening and sugar until light colored and fluffy. Beat in molasses and eggs. Set aside mixture.
In another bowl, combine flour, salt, baking soda, ginger, cloves and cinnamon.
Blend thoroughly with a wire whisk.
Gradually mix flour mixture into creamed ingredients until dough is blended.
Roll dough into 1 1/2-inch balls and dip tops in sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 11 minutes.
Don't overbake.
Store in tightly covered container to maintain softness.

title: alvin's barbecue pork chops
directions: Lay pork chops in pan after seasoning with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Put ketchup evenly on each pork chop and then pour Coke into pan.
Cover pan with tinfoil.
Put in oven at 350° and bake for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: beef and bean bake
directions: Cook bacon and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Brown beef in skillet with onions.
Mix all ingredients in large ovenproof casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy red raspberry dressing
directions: Line a strainer with cheesecloth.
Add the yogurt and allow to drain over a bowl for 30 minutes.
Transfer to a medium bowl. Puree the raspberries in a food processor.
Fold them into the yogurt.
Add the peels and basil.
Combine well.
Yields 1 cup.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes and onion on fine grater.
(Place grater in colander; this removes
excess
starch.)
Transfer
grated potatoes to clean bowl.
Add
other ingredients.
Place 1 inch of oil in frying pan.
Heat.
Place approximately 1 tablespoon of batter in pan; fry until edges
are golden brown.
Turn and fry on other side.
Place between
sheets of paper toweling to remove excess grease.

title: peanut fudge ice-cream dessert
directions: Mix wafer crumbs, margarine and sugar.
Press firmly in ungreased square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches.
Mix chopped peanuts, fudge topping and the caramel flavored topping.
Spread over crumb mixture.
Cut ice cream crosswise into 2-inch slices; place on peanut mixture.
Let stand until slightly softened; spread evenly. Drizzle with 1/2 cup fudge topping.
Cover and freeze until firm, at least 12 hours.
Serve with additional chocolate fudge topping and peanuts, if desired.

title: spicy turkey roast
directions: Remove mesh from the turkey.
Lay turkey out as flat as possible, skin side down.
In food processor with the steel blade, combine the garlic, rosemary, pepper and salt.
Turn on and add the oil, processing until coarsely chopped.
Spread half the garlic mixture over the inside of the turkey.
Reroll the turkey.
Tie firmly with string every two inches to return the meat to its original log shape.
Spread evenly with remaining garlic mixture. Place on rack in roasting pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until a meat thermometer inserted in the center reaches 170°.
A long log shape take less time than a more compact roast.
Let stand 20 minutes before removing string.
Slice thin.
Spoon meat juices over meat or thicken with flour for a gravy.

title: crock-pot barbecue
directions: Brown meat in small amount of oil.
Add onions and peppers (peppers are optional); brown lightly.
Combine all ingredients in slow cooker (crock-pot).
Cover; cook on high for 8 hours or on low overnight.
Shred meat with fork.
Serve on hamburger buns or kaiser rolls.

title: crust-less quiche
directions: Spray quiche pan with cooking spray (10-inch size).
Once sausage has started cooking, add onions.
Stir-fry for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add mushrooms.
Spread on bottom of quiche pan.
Pour egg substitute over all.
Sprinkle top with 3 tablespoons grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until set.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Serves 4.

title: louisiana jambalaya
directions: Saute chopped onion, celery and bell pepper.
Add sausage slices and brown.
Pour off grease.
Add shrimp and cook until shrimp turns pink.
Add rice and continue frying over medium heat for 2 minutes.
Add seasonings to taste.
Add about 4 cups water. Bring to a boil and cook on low to medium heat for 20 minutes, until rice is soft.
Cover pot while cooking.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together using as much as you want of the cranberries, cherries and raisins.
Use enough Miracle Whip or mayonnaise to taste.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in frying pan.
Drain grease; use small portion to grease 9 x 13-inch pan. Cook spaghetti; drain. Mix hamburger, sauce and spaghetti.
Pour 1/2 of spaghetti mixture in pan; top with cottage cheese.
Add remainder of spaghetti mixture; cover with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour to melt cheese and warm through.

title: stuffed french bread
directions: Slice bread in half lengthwise.
Core out bread.
Tear core in pieces into large bowl.
Add all ingredients.
Mix well.
Stuff back into bread shell.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: zucchini and tomatoes
directions: Saute zucchini in olive oil for about 5 minutes until tender. Add tomato and seasonings and cook for 5 minutes more.
If desired, place mixture in shallow baking dish.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and put under broiler until cheese melts.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Punch holes in cake after baking while hot and pour Icing over cake.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Put everything through food chopper.
Mix well and let set in refrigerator.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients with mixer in a large, extra large, I mean big bowl!
Add oatmeal, candy and chips.
Mix with wooden spoon or, if easier, with hands.
Drop by rounded spoonful.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
(This is half the original recipe.)

title: easy supper
directions: Brown pork chops and place in casserole dish.
Add onion soup mix and
water.
Add
rice
and cover.
Cook at 400° until bubbly, about 25 minutes.

title: overnight sauer-bean salad
directions: In a bowl, combine all vegetables.
Combine sugar and vinegar in a saucepan; bring to boil.
Stir in caraway seed.
Pour hot vinegar mixture over vegetable mixture; mix well.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Salad will keep several days in refrigerator.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: preserving children
directions: Mix the children with the dogs; empty into the field, stirring continuously.
Sprinkle with flowers.
Pour brook over pebbles. Cover with deep blue sky; bake in sun until the children are well browned.
Remove from sun; they will be found right and ready for setting away to cool in the bath tub.

title: petite pocketbooks
directions: Soften butter to room temperature.
Add cream cheese, salt and sugar to butter.
Cream until well blended.
Work in the flour with fingers.
Chill for several hours.
Divide dough into thirds; roll out each portion on a floured board to about 1/8-inch thick. Cut into 3-inch squares.
Place 1/2 teaspoon jam or canned filling in center of each one.
Fold so corners overlap in center to enclose jam. Bake on greased cookie sheets at 350° for 16 to 18 minutes until golden brown.

title: laura's broccoli casserole
directions: Butter casserole.
Cover contents with Ritz cracker crumbs on top.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: marinated cucumbers and onions
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers and onions.
Soak together 6 hours with 1 tablespoon salt.
Drain off liquid.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add dressing to cucumber-onion mix.
Chill before serving.
Chopped fresh parsley is optional.

title: mom's party beans
directions: Fry bacon; brown onions in bacon grease.
Add hamburg; fry and drain juice.
Bake in microwave oven for 20 minutes.
Rotate in 10 minutes.

title: any occasion punch
directions: Prepare the Kool-Aid.
Pour into jello mold and freeze.
Mix boiled water, jello and sugar together.
Add lemon juice and mix well, until a syrup consistency.
Set aside to cool, but do not refrigerate.
When ready to serve, add cold water, ginger ale and pineapple juice.
Mix well.
Add frozen Kool-Aid.
Makes 1 punch bowl full.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar, milk and cocoa in heavy pan.
Boil 1 to 2 minutes; remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: lynn's cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve either hot or cold.
If serving cold, just set out with assorted crackers and/or party rye.
If you wish to serve hot, spread party rye slices with mixture and place on cookie sheet in 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook chicken stock, carrots, potatoes, green beans, cauliflower and celery.
After ingredients are tender add squash, zucchini and beans.
Cook until tender.

title: overnight green salad
directions: Wash vegetables and drain.
Cut up in small pieces and add pimentos.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper. Add enough mustard to color.
Pour mixture over vegies; stir well. Put in covered dish and let set overnight.
Delicious!

title: green bean bake
directions: Combine soup, milk and pepper.
Stir in green beans.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with French fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Remove stems from spinach, wash leaves thoroughly and pat dry. Tear into pieces. Combine spinach, eggs, zucchini, and bacon in a

large bowl. Combine salad oil, sugar, mustard, onion, and salt in electric blender. Blend well, remove lid of container and slowly add vinegar while blender is running. Toss spinach with dressing until well coated. A few fresh strawberries in season add to this salad. Just slice and put on top.

title: tropical fruit fluff
directions: In small bowl, combine sour cream, coconut, walnuts and preserves.
Mix well.
Stir in enough milk to make mixture dipping consistency.
Chill.
Serve with chilled fruit dippers (grapes, melon or pineapple).

title: earthquake cake
directions: In a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, place the pecans and coconut. Mix cake mix according to directions on box and pour over the pecans and coconut.
Do not stir.
In separate bowl, mix together the cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy and drop by spoonfuls over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with whipped topping.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: mama's bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers (as Mama says, "kindly thin"), onions and pepper into a large crock, do not use metal.
Add salt.
Cover with ice and mix; let stand 3 hours or longer.
Drain.
Combine vinegar, sugar and spices.	Mix with cucumbers.
Bring to a boil. Seal in sterilized jars.
Makes 8 quarts.
Use a crock or churn, no metal containers.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Combine cream cheese with celery, onion and mayonnaise.
Boil tomato soup (no water), add 1 envelope gelatin, dissolved in 1/4 cup cold water, to hot soup.
Combine soup and vegetable mixture.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour oblong 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or 2 (9-inch) or 3 (8-inch) round layer pans.
Measure all ingredients, except frosting, into large mixing bowl.
Mix 1/2 minute on low, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes on high, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into pans and bake in oblong pan 40 to 45 minutes and layers for 30 to 35 minutes or until top springs back when lightly touched.
Cool and frost with Sour Cream Chocolate Frosting.

title: almond chicken
directions: Saute celery and onion until tender.
Combine all ingredients. Add one can Chinese noodles and 1/2 bag almonds, sliced.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: easy biscuits
directions: Mix into meal.
Add buttermilk.
Knead in bowl until smooth and elastic.
Divide into 9 portions 1-inch thick.
Put in round buttered pan.
Bake at 450° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: three layer jello mold
directions: Add 3/4 cup boiling water to strawberry jello.
Dissolve well. Add enough ice to mixture to make 1 2/3 to 1 3/4 cups melted jello.
Pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan (very lightly oiled).
Let chill until set, about 15 minutes.

title: almond tea
directions: Mix everything together, except ginger ale.
Add ginger ale right before serving.

title: chili rice casserole
directions: Cook rice with salt (no butter); mix with celery soup and sour cream.
Put half of this into a buttered casserole dish.
Spread half the green chiles and cheese on top.
Repeat the layers.
Bake at 350° until the cheese is bubbly.
This is really better served the second day, reheated!

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until thick in double boiler over simmering water.
Stir constantly.
Cool, then add 1/3 pint whipping cream.
Fold in last 5 ingredients.
Put mixture in a large Bundt pan or mold and freeze until solid.

title: apricot nectar salad
directions: Bring nectar to a boil.
Add gelatin; stir until dissolved. Stir in water and lemon juice.
Chill until consistency of egg white.
Stir in fruits.
Pour into oiled mold.
Chill.
Garnish with apple, oranges and green grapes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: rolls
directions: Mix salt, sugar, butter and boiling water; set aside.
Mix warm water and yeast in small bowl; set aside.
In first mix add 2 1/2 cups plain flour and egg; mix well.
Add yeast mix; stir well. Now add 2 1/2 cups more plain flour; mix well.
Grease large bowl with oil.
Put dough in bowl; cover with wet towel.
Refrigerate overnight.
Take out, punch down and set in warm place.
Rise 3 hours.
Make rolls, size you want.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: low-fat muffins
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Make a well in the center.
Combine egg substitute, milk and applesauce.
Pour into well and mix just until dry ingredients are moistened (do not overmix).
Spoon into greased muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 1 dozen.
Freeze well.

title: turnips
directions: Peel, wash, quarter and cook turnips until tender.
Saute in butter or margarine the celery and green pepper.
Add this mixture to cooked turnips with turnip stock and salt.
Pour mixture in a well-greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and paprika on top.
Place strips of bacon on top of bread crumbs.
Bake in oven at 325° for 40 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: *Frozen broccoli can be thawed in small saucepan, if you don't like it crunchy.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, milk and honey.
Add eggs; mix well.
Stir in raisins.
Place in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 300° for about 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: tuna supreme
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions, omitting salt in cooking water.
Drain.
Arrange in a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Flake tuna and place over broccoli.
Combine soup, milk and cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Stir in French fried onions, reserving some for top.
Pour over tuna.
Sprinkle remaining onions on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix
all
ingredients well.
Bake in well greased pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: hot wing dip
directions: Mix together hot sauce, ranch dressing and cream cheese. Beat with mixer until well blended.
Add chicken and 1 c. Cheddar cheese.
Pour into baking dish and sprinkle with remaining Cheddar.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: dinosaur food
directions: Mix dirt and swamp water.
Add crushed bones and fat.
Boil
1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and drop from spoon on wax paper.
Cool.
Eat up!

title: pantry shelf sweet pickles
directions: Pack whole cucumbers into gallon jar as tight as possible. Mix other ingredients and pour over cucumbers.
Close jar and tape lid securely with masking tape to seal.
Let stand at room temperature for 3 weeks.

title: buttery cinnamon skillet apples
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Stir in sugar and cornstarch; mix well.
Add water, cinnamon and apples.
Cover and cook over medium heat.
Spoon sauce over apples until they are fork-tender and sauce is thick, about 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Super easy to make and a great side dish for pork.

title: bacon and water chestnut pupu
directions: Marinate chestnuts in soy sauce for 30 minutes.
Drain.
Roll chestnuts lightly in sugar.
Wrap with
bacon strips and secure with toothpicks.
Place on rack in baking pan.
Bake at 400°, until bacon is brown and crisp.
Serve hot.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Yield: 4 cups.

title: coconut snowballs
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Spoon into 18 paper-lined muffin cups.
Bake 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Remove paper liners.
Spread Cool Whip on bottom and sides of cupcakes.
Press coconut into whipped topping.
Place cupcakes, top sides down, on serving plate.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 18 snowballs.

title: no cook fudge
directions: Melt peanut
butter
and
oleo
in
pan at medium heat. When cool,
add sugar, cocoa and vanilla.
Put in buttered pan and press
with hands.
Put in refrigerator until hard and cut to serve.

title: cheesecake bars
directions: Roll out 1 package of rolls (don't separate) in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pinch together if they try to separate.
Mix the cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and egg yolk.
Pour over rolls. Roll out the second package or rolls and put on top of this mixture. Beat egg white with fork and pour on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Mix the confectioners sugar and milk. Glaze top while cheesecake is hot.
Keep refrigerated.
Makes about 15.

title: scalloped corn
directions: In baking dish, mix the 3 cans of corn, onion, eggs and 1/2 cup cheese.
Cover with remaining cheese, croutons and small amount of milk to moisten.
Cover and bake at 275° for 1 hour.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Pare apples; cut in eighths and arrange in unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle with 1/2 sugar mixed with cinnamon.
Mix remaining sugar with flour; cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: beth's rhubarb pudding
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and place in a 6 x 9-inch baking dish. Mix the brown sugar, flour, shortening, oatmeal and butter together.
Sprinkle over the rhubarb mixture. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes. Serve with milk or cream.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Sort and wash beans; place in large Dutch oven. Cover with water and cook for about an hour and a half. Add remaining ingredients. Bring to boil. Cover; reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender. Remove and discard bay leaf. Yield: 5 cups (230 calories per 1 cup serving).

title: sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream oil, butter and sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Stir in dry ingredients and blend.
Roll a teaspoon of dough into a ball, then roll the ball into sugar, granulated.
Put on cookie sheet and press down with bottom of glass tumbler dipped in sugar.
Bake about 12 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottoms only of 2 loaf pans.
Mix zucchini, sugar, oil, vanilla and eggs in large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pans.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Loosen sides of loaves; remove from pan.
Cool completely before slicing.
Wrap tightly and store at room temperature up to four days or refrigerate up to 10 days.

title: baked dip
directions: Blend 8 ounce package of Philadelphia cream cheese with 2 tablespoons milk.
Add 1 (8 ounce) can medium or tiny deveined shrimp and 1 (8 ounce) can of crabmeat, both drained, 2 tablespoons finely minced onion, salt and pepper.
Beat all ingredients until very well mixed.
(I just put everything in a bowl and use the electric mixer.) Cover and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook rice in boiling water.
Cook sausage and onion together; drain.
Heat 1 can mushroom soup and 1 can sweet milk.
Now you later all of this:
rice, sausage, cheese and gravy.
Layer everything.
Put in oven and bake until warm all the way through.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until ropey and a light caramel color.
Pour over popcorn and spread to cool.

title: easy english toffee bars
directions: Cream butter, sugars and egg yolk.
Add flour and blend. Press dough into 9 x 13-inch lightly greased pan.
Bake at 250° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Drop chocolate chips on top; let melt and spread chips evenly.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.
Cool, then cut into diagonal squares.

title: black russian brownies
directions: Line 13 x 9-inch pan with wax paper.
In saucepan, melt chocolate with pepper and butter (low heat).
Beat eggs with sugar and vanilla until blended.
Stir in cooled chocolate mixture, the kahlua and vodka.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Drain salmon, removing boning.
Combine salmon, crackers (crushed), eggs and diced onion.
Shape into patties; cover with flour.
Fry salmon in oil over medium heat and very little oil until lightly browned on both sides.

title: ritz cookies
directions: Put crackers on cookie sheet.
Cook and stir last 3 ingredients until thick.

title: layered mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet; drain. Add corn and salsa; cook until thoroughly heated. Reserve 2 tablespoons olives. Stir remaining olives into beef mixture. Combine cottage cheese and sour cream in medium bowl. In 2-quart casserole, layer 2 cups chips, half of meat mixture, 3/4 cup Cheddar cheese and half of cottage cheese mixture. Repeat layers; cover. Bake in preheated 350° oven 35 minutes. Line edge of casserole with remaining chips. Top with tomato, reserved olives and remaining Cheddar cheese. Bake 10 minutes or until cheese is melted. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Peel peaches and cut in half.
Place in pie shell.
Mix sugar and flour and sprinkle over peaches.
Dribble cream over sugar and flour to moisten.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° until crust is brown and peaches are tender.

title: macaroni and tomatoes
directions: In a large saucepan, cook macaroni in boiling water for 6 to 8 minutes or until nearly tender.
Drain well; return macaroni to the saucepan.
Add undrained tomatoes, the mushrooms, oregano and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes or until macaroni is tender and most of the liquid is absorbed.
Pour into a serving bowl; sprinkle with cheese.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: texas cake
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to boil.
Remove from heat and add sugar and flour, stir well.
Add eggs, buttermilk, vanilla and baking soda.
Pour into greased 12 x 16 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 20 minutes.
Frost immediately.

title: oriental coleslaw
directions: Toss and refrigerate all but noodles.

title: seven-layer casserole
directions: Arrange the ingredients except bacon in layers in order given. Lay bacon strips on top; cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, then uncover and continue baking 30 minutes.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce; break up.
Let chill 1 hour.
Stir in orange and pineapple.
Can be poured in mold.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: coconut cake
directions: Blend together the cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil. Beat well.
Stir in the coconut and walnuts.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350°f. 180°c. gas mark 4 for 35 minutes.

title: danielle's favorite chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; set aside.
Blend together the butter until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Then add 1 tablespoon vanilla.
Pulse (on/off in food processor) the oatmeal.
Set aside.
Add the flour gradually to the butter mixture, then add the oats (do not overmix).
Add the nuts.
Mix until just mixed in.
Drop onto cookie sheets (use parchment paper if you have any) in golf ball size for bigger cookies or 1/2 of that for smaller cookies.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: picante chicken
directions: Cut up chicken.
Coat with egg, then corn meal.
Place in baking pan.
Cover with picante sauce.
Bake 1 hour, covered. Sprinkle with cheese and taco chips.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: ro-tel dip
directions: Melt cheese and add tomatoes.
Add beef and keep hot in crock-pot.
Serve with light tortilla chips.

title: meat and rice mold
directions: In a large heavy saucepan, brown meat in butter.
Add onions and saute until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice; cover and simmer for 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Add more water if necessary.
About 30 minutes before meat is ready, prepare rice according to package directions; set aside.
Place all the meat and half the sauce in bottom of a 9 x 11-inch ring mold.
Add cooked rice and pack tightly.
Turn out onto a heated round serving platter.
Serve remaining sauce separately. Garnish with parsley.
Serves 6.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil; add vegetables.
Saute.
Add all the rest of the ingredients except rice; bring to a boil.
Add rice; stir.
Cover, turn off heat and let stand 5 minutes.

title: icicle pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers lengthwise to fill a two-gallon crock. Dissolve salt in one gallon of boiling water.
Pour salt water over cucumbers.
Cover and let stand one week; drain.

title: pickled mandarin oranges
directions: Drain juice from oranges.
Bring to boil with spices in saucepan.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Continue to simmer for 5 minutes.
Add oranges and heat.
Can be stored in refrigerator or sealed in small canning jars.

title: quick apple cake
directions: Put in 9-inch square pie dish (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: cream frosting with blueberries
directions: Cream the cream cheese.
Gradually add sugars until light and fluffy.
Mix nondairy and whipped topping into frosting.
Spread frosting on bottom layer of cake and pour desired amount of berries.
Add the top layer, frost top and sides.
Pour desired amount of blueberries on top of top frosted layer.

title: chicken in wine sauce
directions: Brown
cut
chicken
in
margarine.
Salt and pepper to taste. Place
in
casserole dish.
Add chicken soup and wine. Stir well. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serve with rice.

title: mom's apple bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs together.
Add soda, salt, flour, sour milk, vanilla, apples and chopped walnuts, if desired. Mix all together and spoon into greased loaf pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer bottom of dish with 1 pack Ritz Crackers.
Cut up half of butter and chip pieces over crackers.
Mix cans of chicken breast (drained) with cream of chicken soup, water chestnuts (drained), pimentos and sour cream.
Mix together and spread over crackers evenly.
Put more Ritz Crackers on top of spread with the other half of butter.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook until casserole starts to bubble.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Bake 6 minutes at 375° and cool.

title: scripture cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with unsalted shortening.
Sift flour with salt, baking powder, cinnamon, allspice and nutmeg.

title: french silk pie
directions: Cream butter in mixing bowl at low speed.
Gradually add sugar, creaming well at medium speed.
Add 1 egg at a time; beat 3 to 5 minutes.
Spoon into baked pastry shell.
Chill 2 hours. Serve with whipped cream and chocolate (sweet) shavings on top of cream.

title: salmon quiche
directions: Beat eggs and milk together until blended.
Add salmon, breaking up lightly with a fork.
Gently stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture into baked pie shell, being sure the solids are distributed evenly in the bottom of the shell. Microwave, uncovered, at power level High for 10 1/2 to 13 1/2 minutes.
Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes, or until center becomes firm.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, saving a small amount of crumbs for topping. Put ingredients in dish and cover with remaining crumbs. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: greek chicken
directions: Melt butter in large
pan.
Add chicken.
Add 2 cans of water or chicken broth.
Mix
well.
Cook
minutes in 400° oven or on top of stove at very low heat.

title: yams
directions: Peel, boil and cut potatoes in pieces.
Place in a baking dish.
Place sugar over potatoes.
Add cherries with juice, pie filling, butter and sprinkle nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: strawberry slush
directions: Fill blender one-half full of ice, add rum, Kool-Aid (sweeten if not already sweetened), and strawberries.
Top off with 7-Up or Sprite.
Blend until slushy.
Top with whipped cream or blend in ice cream (vanilla).
Pour into cocktail glasses and garnish with whole strawberry.
Can be frozen and used later.

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in individual containers with lids.
Freeze.
Take out of freezer 20 minutes before serving.

title: country fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Blend well.
Add preserves, orange rind, juice and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into a large greased stem pan and bake for 3 to 3 1/2 hours at 325°.
Raise oven temperature to 375° during the last 15 minutes to brown cake.
Cake should feel firm in center when done.
Cool on cake rack before turning out of pan.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and milk.
Add margarine.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Take off heat; add vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Put cookie patties on wax paper.
Let cool, then serve.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers together.
Crush crackers and put crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Double this to make good-sized dish.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Mix well and press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: speedy beans
directions: Drain beans, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Combine beans and liquid with other ingredients.
Pour into buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole and bake at 350°
or cook in large skillet until bubbly and heated through.
Yields 6 servings.

title: apple boats
directions: Cut apple into fourths.
Cut out center part with seed.
Let child spread peanut butter into area where middle of apples was. Insert 1 toothpick through peanut butter into apple.
Cut cheese slice into fourths from corner to corner.
Place 1 sail shaped slice onto toothpick.
Now, you have an apple boat.
Delicious and nutritious.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Mix the above and pour over chicken parts in a greased casserole.
Bake uncovered 1 1/2 hours at 350.

title: crunchy cauliflower salad
directions: Combine cauliflower, celery, apples and peanuts in large serving bowl.
Blend yogurt, orange juice, salt and pepper in small bowl.
Pour over cauliflower mixture; toss to coat. Refrigerate, covered, until ready to serve.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 6.

title: holiday sugar roll-out dough
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Mix in egg and vanilla.
Stir dry ingredients together; blend into sugar-margarine mixture. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Heat oven to 375°.
Using half of dough at a time, make cut-outs.
Roll dough to 3/16-inch thickness. Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes until delicately golden.
Decorate with Easy Creamy Decorating Icing.

title: peter paul mounds cake
directions: Melt oleo, Coke and cocoa in saucepan.
Pour over flour and 2 cups sugar.
Mix together and add eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
In another pan, put marshmallows, milk, sugar and coconut.
Cook until thick and pour over cake while hot.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix together. Chill and serve.

title: healthy salad
directions: Wash all vegetables thoroughly.
Chop, dice or slice all vegetables into bite sized pieces.
(You will need a large container.)

title: fiesta salad
directions: Place refried
beans
in
a
10 x 15-inch dish.
Smooth beans out to cover bottom
of dish.
Layer the next 7 ingredients in order.
Refrigerate until ready to serve with tortilla chips.

title: pineapple walnut cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix and pour into a 13 x 9-inch greased and floured baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: toffee
directions: In heavy pan over medium heat, combine the first 4 ingredients.
Heat to 290°.
Add nuts; cook until 300°, stirring constantly.
Pour onto 2 greased cookie sheets.
Melt the Hershey bar; spread over the top.
Pour rolled walnuts on top.
When hardened, break into pieces.

title: chocolate icebox cake
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler; add water and sugar.
After melted and cooled, add unbeaten egg yolks one at a time.
Add beaten egg whites.
Alternate chocolate mixture with ladyfingers. Refrigerate 12 hours and serve with or without whipped cream.

title: rice dressing
directions: Boil chicken and set aside.
Cook rice in chicken broth.
Chop green onions, slice sausage and cut up bacon and brown.
Mix all well, except chicken.
Put in casserole dish and lay chicken on top; brown in oven.

title: creamy chicken spread
directions: Place all ingredients in a food processor and process until coarsely chopped. Use as a sandwich spread or serve on crackers. Yield: 2 1/2 cups.

title: creamy blueberry dessert
directions: Combine boiling water
and
gelatin
packages
in
large bowl. Stir until gelatin
is
dissolved.
Stir
in lemon juice and 1/2 cup cold water.
Slowly
stir in blueberry pie filling. Pour into an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Chill until firm.

title: western chef salad
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed (except last 3).
Brown 1 pound beef and drain.
Add kidney beans and salt.
Heat.
Add this mixture to cold salad.
Mix well.

title: banana dessert
directions: Melt margarine in bottom of 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish.
Add flour and pecans, mix well and spread over bottom of pan.
Bake at 270° for 1 hour.

title: brown sugar mounds
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar together.
Add egg; mix well. Add other ingredients and mix well.
Chill dough and drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until lightly browned.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet on medium-high heat.
Stir in water, catsup, mustard, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice and cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand for 5 minutes; fluff with fork.
Sprinkle with cheese and cover.
Let stand until cheese is melted.
Garnish with lettuce, pickles and tomato slices.

title: sauce
directions: Brown the hamburger; drain off excess fat.
Add rest of ingredients and cook slowly for 4 or 5 hours or until sauce is thick.

title: peanut butter pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla extract and slowly beat in peanut butter.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture, a little at a time, until well blended.
Line a 9 or 10-inch tube pan on the bottom with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes; reduce heat to 325° and bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes; then turn out.

title: goulash steak
directions: Pan fry steak until brown.
Mix ingredients, onion, sweet pepper, banana pepper, tomatoes, garlic salt and sugar.
Add to pan fried steak.
Heat on medium-high heat until boiling.
Lower heat; simmer for 20 minutes.
Serves approximately 8.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Chop cabbage and pack into 6 quart jars.
Bring to boil other ingredients and pour over cabbage.
Seal.

title: macaroons
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into small balls, flatten slightly and place on greased cookie sheet.
Let stand half hour. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes until slightly browned.
Makes 18.

title: chicken noodle bake
directions: In 1 1/2 quart casserole dish, blend soup and milk; stir in chicken, noodles, pimento and parsley.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Stir together, then top with bread crumbs.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: crispix chocolate drops
directions: Melt butterscotch and semi-sweet morsels.
Add cereal and peanuts.
Stir together.
Spoon onto waxed paper.

title: hopscotch candy
directions: Melt the butterscotch morsels over hot water with the peanut butter.
Mix in a large bowl the marshmallows and noodles.
Add butterscotch mixture and mix all together, then drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix and
bring first 4 ingredients to a boil.
After it comes to	a
good
boil, continue boiling 1 1/2 minutes by the clock. Remove
from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper to cool.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Fill a 9-inch pie pan full of sliced apples.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon sugar mixed with cinnamon.
In a small bowl combine 3/4 cup melted butter.
Spread mixture over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: biscuit bread
directions: Spray Bundt pan with nonstick spray. Melt margarine.
Open biscuits.
Dip each biscuit in melted margarine.
Stand biscuits side by side in Bundt pan.
Cook in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: creole black-eyed peas
directions: Place the peas in a medium-sized saucepan.
Cover with 2 cups broth; bring to a boil for 2 minutes.
Cover; remove from heat and allow to soak for 1 hour.
Drain and discard the soaking liquid. Add the remaining ingredients to the pan, including the remaining 1 cup chicken broth.
Bring to a boil, cover again, reduce heat and simmer slowly for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add water as necessary to keep the peas covered with liquid.
Remove the bay leaf.
Place in a serving bowl and serve hot, garnished with parsley.

title: fan potatoes
directions: Peel the potatoes if skins are tough, otherwise scrub.
Cut potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through.
Use handle of wooden spoon to prevent cutting all the way through.
Put in baking dish and fan slightly.
Sprinkle with salt.
Drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with herbs.
Bake potatoes at 425° for about 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake for another 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned and cheese is melted.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Mix rice, broccoli, butter, onion, milk, soup and Cheez Whiz, adding one ingredient at a time.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into balls.
Put into a covered container.
Freeze.
When ready to use, bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Cook all ingredients together in a pot until ground beef is done.
Use Ragu with nothing in it, approximately 1/2 of jar. Consistency should be thick.
Meat mixture can be frozen in small containers and thawed and heated for use.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Bake immediately or divide into rolls and roll in waxed paper and refrigerate until cold.
Slice and bake.

title: fast hollandaise sauce
directions: In blender, mix egg yolks, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Melt butter.
Turn blender on high and gradually pour in hot butter and blend on high speed for three minutes.
Sauce will thicken as it cools.
Served over Chicken Le'Br'y.
Recipe under "Meat."

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk and beat with a mixer until thickened. Add sour cream and fold in cool whip.
Make sure it is mixed well. Line bottom of a dish with wafers then add pudding and sliced bananas.
Top with vanilla wafers.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Reserve 1 egg for garnish; chop remaining eggs.
Combine chopped eggs, beans, celery, relish, onions and salt; toss together lightly.
Blend in sour cream gently.
Chill for at least 1 hour to blend flavors.
Garnish with slices of reserved egg. Yield:
5 to 6 servings.

title: quick sourdough french bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour and next 5 ingredients; blend well.
Add water, sour cream and vinegar to flour mixture.
Blend at low speed until moistened; beat 3 minutes at medium speed.

title: bread dressing
directions: Brown celery and onion in skillet.
Mix muffins, biscuits, eggs, sage and stock.
Bake at 350° until light golden brown.

title: purple cow
directions: Put 2 scoops of vanilla ice cream in a tall glass.
Fill the glass to the top with grape soda.
Stir.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until fluffy.
Add salt, syrup, eggs and vanilla.
Sprinkle pecans on bottom of unbaked pie shell, then pour the filling over pecans.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce temperature to 350° and bake 35 minutes longer.
Outer edge of filling should be set, center slightly soft.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven, in very hot salad oil, gradually cook flour until dark brown.
Stir in diced onion, diced green pepper, garlic, salt and diced celery.
Cook until tender.
Add tomatoes with their liquid, okra and water.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until mixture thickens.
Add shrimp, crab and hot sauce.
Cook 10 minutes. Serve in soup bowls over scoop of rice.
Serves 8.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over 100% bran and cool.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Mix bran into eggs.
Add flour, 40% bran flakes, soda, salt, buttermilk, nutmeg, ginger and cinnamon.
Refrigerate up to 30 days.
Bake in greased muffin tins 25 to 30 minutes at 375° to 400°.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and salt together; drain. Combine with the spaghetti sauce. Add mushrooms, if desired. Add the oregano. Let simmer.
Cook the lasagna noodles and drain.
In a large baking dish, layer noodles and add sauce until all is used.
Cover with shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers and melted margarine.
Mix 1 package lemon jello with hot water in separate bowl.
Set until congealed to coat a spoon.
Mix 1 cup sugar with 8 ounce package cream cheese and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Add cream cheese to jello mixture.
Fold 9 ounces Cool Whip into sugar, cream cheese and jello mixture. Pour into pan and let set awhile. Top with cherry pie mix.

title: tropical fruit cake
directions: Combine (sift first 5 ingredients).
Add eggs and oil, stirring until moistened (do not beat).
Stir in vanilla, pecans, pineapple and bananas.
Pour into pan (greased and floured). Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: strawberry-pretzel salad
directions: Combine and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Cool completely.

title: honey garlic chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees.
Separate chicken wings at the joints, discarding the tips.
Arrange the chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Combine the honey, bouillon, soy sauce, lemon juice, garlic powder and ginger in a small mixing bowl and mix well.
Pour over the chicken, turning to coat.
Increase the oven temperature to 475 degrees.
Bake for 25 minutes longer or until the chicken is cooked through.

title: raised doughnuts
directions: Dissolve dry yeast in warm water.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes. Place scalded milk, sugar and salt in large bowl.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir yeast solution thoroughly and add to mixture.
Add half the flour which has been sifted with the mace; beat well.
Add eggs and cool melted shortening, stirring vigorously.
Add remaining flour, stirring well.
Place on lightly floured board and knead 3 minutes.
Shape into small ball and place in greased bowl. Brush top lightly with shortening.
Cover and let rise in warm place 45 minutes.
Without punching down turn dough onto lightly floured board and roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut dough with 3-inch floured doughnut cutter.
Place doughnuts on floured baking sheet.
Let rise in warm place until very light, about 3/4 hour. Do not cover.
Fry in hot fat 350° on both sides.
Drain, cool, and roll in sugar.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: dijon-glazed chicken
directions: Place chicken in a greased 2-inch baking dish.
Combine mustard, brown sugar and ginger; stir well.
Brush half of glaze mixture evenly over chicken.
Cover and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until chicken is done.
Uncover and baste with remaining glaze mixture.
Broil chicken 4 inches from heat 1 to 2 minutes or until brown.
Transfer chicken to a serving platter and sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sundae delight cake
directions: Bake a chocolate cake mix according to box directions.
As soon as cake is done, punch holes in cake with end of handle of wooden spoon.

title: raspberry, blueberry or blackberry pie
directions: Save our 1/2 cup choice berries.
Simmer 1 cup berries and 2/3 cup water about 3 minutes.
Blend 1 cup sugar, 3 tbsp. cornstarch and 1/3 cup water and add to simmering mixture.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Spread cream cheese over bottom of crust.
Put 2 1/2 cups berries over cream cheese and cover with cooked mixture.
Garnish with the 1/2 cup berries. Refrigerate about 2 hours until firm.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: "cup of" cobbler
directions: Put 1 stick of butter in a glass baking dish. Melt in oven. Mix flour, sugar and milk in bowl. Pour fruit in pan with butter, then pour batter on top. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: italian antipasto(antipasto all'italiana)
directions: Wash and dry lettuce
leaves.
Prepare
a large platter lined with a bed of
lettuce
leaves.
Arrange
cold
cuts and cheese attractively on lettuce.
Garnish with pickled peppers, tomato wedges, artichoke
hearts,
mushrooms, olives and chick peas. Sprinkle with olive
oil,
oregano
and vinegar.
Serve with bread sticks or
sliced Italian bread, if desired.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and debone. Cook spaghetti in chicken broth. Saute onion and bell pepper in butter. Add milk, both cans of soup, pimento and salt and pepper to taste. Heat until mixture bubbles and add boned chicken. Drain spaghetti and add chicken mixture. Put in casserole and heat in a 350° oven about 30 minutes. Add grated cheese on top and put back in oven long enough for cheese to melt. Serve with a sprinkle of Parmesan cheese.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix melted butter and graham cracker crumbs together and press in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° and cool. Mix sugar, eggs and 2 sticks softened margarine; beat until thick, about 10 minutes.
Spread over crust.
Drain the can of pineapple and spread over the sugar mixture.
Slice bananas on top of pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with nuts and maraschino cherries.

title: chicken strata
directions: Cut bread into 1-inch cubes.
Place half in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix chicken,
onion,
celery,
pepper,
mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Spoon
over bread
crumbs.
Sprinkle remaining half of bread cubes on top.
Combine
eggs and milk. Pour over the top.
Cover and chill overnight.
Before baking, spoon soup over top and
sprinkle
with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle
cheese
over
top last few minutes of baking.

title: quick spanish rice
directions: Cook green pepper, onion and rice in hot fat, stirring constantly, until lightly browned.
Dissolve bouillon cube in hot water; add to rice along with the tomato sauce and meat; mix. Bring quickly to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered 5 minutes or until rice is tender.
Makes 5 servings.

title: sunrise smoothie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in blender.
With blender on high, add ice cubes, one at a time, processing until smooth after each addition.
Serve immediately.
Makes 2 cups.

title: squash casserole
directions: Beat eggs lightly with oil and seasonings. Stir in onions and squash.
Mix together the Bisquick mix, cheese and cream-style corn. Stir into egg mixture and pour into greased and
floured 2-quart casserole.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain.
Arrange in greased baking dish.
Layer chicken on top.
Combine next 3 ingredients; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine crumbs and butter; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: diet graham cracker crust
directions: In food processor, process crackers to coarse crumbs.
Using pulse control, blend in remaining ingredients to a coarse, crumbly texture.
Press mixture into 9-inch pie pan.
Chill crust until ready to fill.
(See reduced calorie pie recipes for filling.) Nutrient Exchange: 1/2 bread and 1/3 fat.

title: jim's sweet potatoes
directions: Peel, slice and boil the sweet potatoes until done.
Whip with the butter, then add the maple syrup and stir until blended.
Add brown sugar.
Stir in the spices, vanilla and rum.
Chop one apple and cook in butter until soft.
Add raisins and cook for another minute.
Stir into the sweet potato mixture and add chopped pecans.

title: easy pot roast
directions: Put meat in crock-pot.
Spread on soup.
Sprinkle on dry soup and pour in water.
Cook on low for 8 hours.

title: apricot congealed salad with secret ingredient
directions: Mix Jell-O and crushed pineapple in saucepan.
Cook until it comes to a boil.
Set aside and cool slightly.
Add buttermilk (secret ingredient).
Stir well and refrigerate until texture is like mayonnaise.
Take out and add Cool Whip and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into long Pyrex dish (13 x 9-inch), sprayed with Pam. Chill several hours or overnight.
This is very good and buttermilk is undetected.

title: pineapple cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
In small bowl, stir pineapple, pudding and milk until well blended.
Add to cream cheese and beat until smooth.
Pour into pie crust and chill until set.

title: larkin world famous dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in flat casserole dish, 10 x 13-inch.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in 350° oven, preheated.
Serve with hot chips.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: Put cupcake liners in a muffin tin and put 1 vanilla wafer in the bottom of each liner.
Beat cream cheese and sugar together. Beat in the eggs, lemon juice and vanilla.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and top with pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Partially cook sausage and drain into 2-quart casserole.
Put layers of potatoes, carrots, onions, sausage, rice and the tomatoes with the juice.
Combine seasonings and sprinkle over top.
Cover casserole.
Bake in a moderate 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: aunt marion's sweet waffles
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook in a hot waffle iron.
Leftovers may be reheated in the toaster.

title: emily's spinach salad
directions: Mix vegetable oil, red wine vinegar, lemon juice, soy sauce, sugar, dry mustard, curry powder, salt, seasoned pepper and garlic powder in a jar.
Cover tightly and shake until well mixed.
Place spinach, torn into bite-size pieces, in a large salad bowl.
Just before serving, pour dressing over spinach and toss gently. Garnish with crumbled bacon and egg slices.

title: avocado dip
directions: Mash avocados and tomatoes until smooth.
Dice onion and chiles; mix with avocado and tomatoes.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: vegetable pasta salad
directions: Combine salad dressing, cheese, parsley and salt.
Mix well. Add ham, noodles and vegetables.
Mix lightly. Chill at least 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: meat-bean dish
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Can be eaten alone or served on bun.

title: mr. loyal's whole hominy
directions: Remove the hominy from the cans and cook for 15 to 20 minutes, then butter and salt to taste.
Serve hot.

title: oyster puffs
directions: Drain oysters in colander.
Make a thick batter of eggs, flour, salt, baking powder, pepper, Old Bay seasoning and water.
Turn oysters into batter.
Drop one oyster at a time using spoon, into deep fat, heated to 400°.
Fry until brown.

title: red kidney beans with turnips
directions: Pick beans over and wash well.
Soak overnight; drain.
Put red kidney beans in large pan.
Add 5 cups water and bring to boil.
Boil vigorously for 10 minutes. Turn heat down and simmer, partially covered, for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until cooked through.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Combine soup and mayonnaise. Add to drained Veg-All. Toss until blended. Add water chestnuts. Pour in buttered casserole. Sprinkle with Ritz cracker crumbs and dot with butter. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: toffee bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter, sugar and egg yolk together.
Add flour gradually, stirring with spoon until well blended.
Spread dough in a lightly greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
(Make sure sides are at least an inch deep or dough will overflow.)
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until medium brown.
Immediately after removing from oven, split Hershey bars 3 or 4 ways and distribute over top of dough evenly.
When melted, spread evenly.
Sprinkle with nuts.
When cool, cut into diamonds by slicing diagonally.

title: coconut cake with white frosting
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Make 3 layers.
Let cool.
Beat together in top of double boiler egg whites, Karo syrup,
sugar and cream of tartar and water.
Beat until it stands in peaks.
Remove double boiler from heat.
Add vanilla; beat until vanilla is mixed.
Spread frosting and coconut between cake layers and on top.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Wash, stem, seed and grind or finely chop peppers.
Measure 2 cups; stir in 2 cups water and 1 cup vinegar.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Strain and measure 3 cups of juice.

title: chicken and rice soup
directions: Rinse chicken.
Combine with water, onion, celery, bay leaf, salt and pepper in heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Simmer, covered, for 45 minutes.
Remove and cool chicken; discard bay leaf.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Add rice and carrot to broth in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Add chicken. Heat to serving temperature.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: tea cakes
directions: Add flour to ingredients to make a dough.
Roll out and cut with cutter.
Bake until brown.

title: blueberry cornmeal scones
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large bowl combine flour and next 4 ingredients; mix well.
Add butter, using two knives or pastry cutter to cut butter into dry mixture.
Cut mixture until it resembles coarse meal; set aside.
In small bowl, beat eggs and milk.
Pour all at once into dry ingredients.
Stir quickly with fork until just moistened.
Fold in frozen berries.
Gather dough into ball.
Place on lightly floured board.
Sprinkle with 2 teaspoons flour.
Knead 6 times.
Press into a rectangle, about 3/4 inch thick.
Cut into 6 squares, then in half to form 12 triangles. Place 1 inch apart on buttered baking sheet.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve immediately with Honey Butter. Makes 12 scones.

title: pineapple torte
directions: Bake cake mix 15 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese with 1/2 cup milk, add pudding and 1 1/2 cups milk to that. Mix and beat until slightly thick and spread on cake.
Sprinkle drained pineapple on top.
Top with whipped cream and sprinkle nuts on top.

title: potato balls
directions: Mix potatoes, cheeses, butter, onions, soup mix and peppers; shape into 16 balls.
Roll in beaten eggs and corn flakes.
Bake on greased baking sheet for 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.
Yields 8 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cut grapes in half and remove seeds.
Chop walnuts.
Drain pineapple tidbits or diced pineapple.
Add dry mustard and salt to slightly beaten eggs and the juice of 1 lemon.
Cool until thick, stirring constantly.
Let cool.
Whip 1 pint of whipping cream.
Mix in egg mixture and fruit, nuts and marshmallows. Chill overnight in covered dish.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except coconut in a saucepan well. Cook over medium heat until thick. Add coconut and mix well. Pour into baked pie shell.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all 7 ingredients until smooth.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: antipasta salad
directions: Cook pasta accordingly to package directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water to cool quickly; drain well.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate overnight or for 4 to 5 hours.
Set out beforehand at least a couple of hour.

title: original banana pudding
directions: Reserve 1 banana and 10 to 12 vanilla wafers for garnish.

title: pizza sausage supper pie
directions: In skillet, cook sausage and onion until meat is brown; drain well.
In large bowl, combine eggs, milk, shredded cheese, spice and pepper.
Stir in sausage and onion.
Turn into pie shell and bake in a preheated 375° oven for 25 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Spread top with pizza sauce and arrange triangles of cheese in spoke fashion over top.
Return to oven 5 to 8 minutes.
Cut in wedges.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Heat soup, cream cheese, lemon jello and water until cheese is melted. Cool. Add mayonnaise, bell pepper, onion and
nuts.
Mix well and let stand overnight.

title: peanut crispy drops
directions: Combine melted almond bark and peanut butter, blending well. Add marshmallows, cereal and peanuts; stirring to coat.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let cool.
Makes approximately 130 pieces.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Grease the casserole dish.
Scrub the potatoes under running water.
Put them into 3 cups water in the saucepan.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Boil them over a medium heat until they are tender to a fork touch. This will be about 25 minutes.

title: old settler's beans
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Combine sugars, ketchup, liquid smoke, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Add to meat mixture.
Combine with beans.
Bake for 1 hour in a casserole in a 350° oven.
Or put in crock-pot for several hours.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Combine
water, noodle soup and brown rice and cook until done, about 45 minutes.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla. Sift flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda; add to first mixture. Make a topping of the last 3 ingredients. Pour 1/2 the batter into a well-greased 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle with 1/2 the topping mix. Add the rest of the batter and sprinkle the rest of the topping on top of the batter. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: peppermint cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Butter and flour two 8-inch round pans. Cream sugar and shortening together. Add eggs. Add flour, salt and baking powder. Mix together.

Add milk. Mix until batter is smooth. Add peppermint that has been crushed. Pour into pans. Bake until inserted toothpick comes out clean. Remove from pans immediately onto cake plate. This will be a very moist cake.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Whisk all ingredients together to make a mayo-like cream. Marinate meat for at least 1 hour or, if possible, overnight. Grill on hot coals until meat is done.

title: tropical cream punch
directions: In a punch bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and juice concentrates; mix well.
Gradually add club soda; stir.
Garnish with orange slices.
Serve over ice.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: lemon pie filling
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick; add sugar.
Mix some milk with the flour, cornstarch and salt to make a thin paste.
Scald remaining milk; add a little to each of the 2 mixtures.
Then slowly stir the 2 mixtures into the scalded milk.
Should be cooked in a double boiler over boiling water.
Remove from heat; add butter, juice and lemon rind.
Cool before putting in crust.
For meringue, bake in 300° oven until just light brown.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place cut apples on the bottom of an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup white sugar.
Mix softened margarine, oatmeal, flour, brown sugar, salt and cinnamon; pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: oriental vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
