Combine all ingredients, except chow mein noodles.
Spoon into a 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Top with chow mein noodles.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 12 servings.
Calories: 100 per cup. Cholesterol: 0 mg.
Fat: 4 gms.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together; shape into small balls.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
May be refrigerated for several days.
If stored this way, be sure to heat in oven at 300° for several minutes or until warm before serving.

title: venison chili
directions: Work meat, flour, salt and pepper together until all of flour is worked into meat.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in heavy pan; add meat mixture and saute slowly so meat will cook thoroughly but not too brown.
Add onions and garlic and cook until clear and soft. Add 2 quarts of hot water and let simmer for 1 hour.
Add paprika, cumin, chili powder, beans and tomato sauce.
Simmer for about 1 hour, stirring often.
This is kind of zingy.
If you want it milder, reduce black pepper and cumin.

title: no-bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter and milk in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Add all dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Take off heat.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a real good boil.
Simmer. Good on all meats.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and 1 egg together until a dough-like consistency is reached.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar, 2 eggs, cream cheese and vanilla with electric mixer and pour over dough base.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: pineapple meringue pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in water and pineapple juice; cook until mixture thickens and boils.
Add small amount to egg yolks, then return to hot mixture.
Boil a minute longer.
Remove from heat.
Add butter or oleo, lemon juice and rind, then pineapple.
Pour into a cooled pie shell.
Top with meringue; brown in oven.
Cool.

title: crustless cushaw pie
directions: Blend all together well.
Spray glass pie plate with Pam. Pour filling into plates and bake at 375° until a table knife inserted in center of pie comes out clean.

title: easy bake cookies
directions: Place in a 9 x 12-inch pan in order listed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool, cut in squares.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first four ingredients in a large pan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, for two minutes.
Turn off heat.
Add marshmallows and other ingredients.
Stir until chips are melted. Pour into 12 x 15-inch buttered pan.
Chill.
Cut into 1 x 1-inch squares.
Makes about five pounds.

title: hot chicken or ham sandwiches
directions: Butter 8 slices of bread.
Put buttered side down in baking dish.
Cover with enough chicken or ham to make an even layer. Cover with remaining bread.
Put one slice of cheese on each piece of bread.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over sandwiches.
Refrigerate overnight.
Lightly brown crusts; roll into crumbs.

title: maw's dried apple fritters
directions: Combine apples with enough flour to make a stiff batter.
Form mixture into flat cakes.
Fry in deep fat until golden brown on both sides.
Pour off excess fat.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Serve warm.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Melt oleo.
In large bowl, combine oleo, sugar, milk, eggs (slightly beaten) and pineapple.
Add bread crumbs.
Stir until well mixed and place in 2-quart or larger ungreased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
Best served hot.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with coating spray.
Line pan with 1 can of the crescent rolls.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and egg yolk.
Spread on top of crescent rolls.
Spread 2nd can of rolls on top of cream cheese mixture.
Beat egg white and spread on top of rolls.
Sprinkle with sugar/cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: string beans vinaigrette
directions: Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil.
Add beans.
Stir and return to water to a boil.
Cook for 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain immediately and rinse well with cold water.
Drain again.
Place in a large serving bowl and toss with red pepper and onion.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Cream well eggs and sugar.
Add Eagle Brand milk, salt and vanilla.
Add milk and freeze according to directions on freezer.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Place oysters in colander to drain.
Cut stems from mushrooms and chop.
Slice mushroom caps.
Saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter (if you are using fresh ones, if you used canned ones drain) until soft.
Add soup and heat, stirring until smooth.
Blend crushed crackers and Parmesan cheese.
Place a layer of crushed crackers in bottom of buttered casserole.
Add layer of oysters, then soup.
Continue with remainder of crushed crackers and oysters and soup.
Melt the butter and add whole oyster crackers and stir until well blended.
Top the casserole with this and sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 350° oven about 20 minutes and serve hot.

title: yellow layer cake
directions: Cream shortening, margarine and sugar, beating well.
Combine sifted flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Add vanilla; beat well.
Add eggs last.
Beat well and pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Frost with Burnt Caramel Icing.

title: mrs. bank's white frosting
directions: Combine sugar, water, syrup and salt in a kettle.
Boil until thickened (unstirred).
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add vanilla. Pour syrup mixture slowly into egg whites, beating constantly, until just right (if mixture is too thin, stir in a little 10x sugar).

title: red velvet cake
directions: Make a paste of
coloring
and	cocoa.	Mix butter with sugar. Cream until light.
Add
eggs
and beat 1 minute.	Add coloring and cocoa to
mixture
with
salt.	Put
vanilla
in buttermilk. Put vinegar and soda
in
a cup; mix with buttermilk.
Add to mixture with flour,
sifted
3 times.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) layer pans 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pastry for apple pie
directions: Sift flour with salt into medium bowl.

With pastry blender, cut in lard and butter until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal. Sprinkle ice water, 1 tablespoon at a time, over flour mixture, stirring lightly with fork after each addition and pushing dampened portion to side of bowl.

title: 1993 united way campaign report meeting brownies
directions: To the	water to be added to brownie mix add 1 teaspoon instant
coffee, then bake according to directions.
Turn oven off.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients with bacon fat; bake for 25 minutes at 400°.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni not completely done.
Toss cooked macaroni in the oil and add all remaining ingredients.
Pour into lightly greased crock-pot (3 to 4 quart).
Stir well.
Cover and cook on low for 3 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: meat loaf
directions: Thoroughly mix ground beef, crumbs, 1/2 cup soup or 3/4 cup tomato juice, onions, egg and seasoning.
Shape firmly into 2 loaves.
Pour remaining soup over the loaves.
Put cheese on the loaves about 5 minutes before the loaves are done.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Pour all ingredients into a crock pot sprayed with Pam.
Stir until mixed.
Cook on low 8 hours.
Serve with crackers or cornbread.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Combine jello and hot water. Dissolve jello.
Cool until almost firm. Add all other ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: escalloped french fries
directions: Melt butter in an 8 x 10-inch baking dish. Add the French fries (crinkle-cut) and pour milk over all. Top with cheese. Cover with foil. Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cinnamon and sugar popcorn crunch
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Spray 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
In small bowl, beat egg white until soft peaks form.
Add brown sugar and cinnamon, beating until stiff peaks form, about 1 minute. Place popcorn in large bowl.
Fold egg white mixture into popcorn. Spread in sprayed baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes, stirring twice while baking.
Cool completely.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 5 (1-cup) servings.

title: dilled carrots
directions: Combine last six ingredients and pour over carrots.
Chill overnight or at least 6 hours.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Butter a 9 x 12 baking dish. Cook the chicken in water until tender; remove and cut into bite-size pieces. In a large pot, mix together the soup, sour cream, onion, garlic and chiles and simmer for 5 minutes. In another skillet, heat the oil. Cook each tortilla in the oil until soft, about 1 to 2 minutes. Drain on paper towels. Top each tortilla with chicken pieces and about 2 tablespoons of soup mixture. Roll up tortillas. Arrange in the prepared dish and pour the remaining soup mixture over the enchiladas. Top with shredded cheese and bake, covered, for 20 minutes. Uncover and bake an additional 10 minutes. Serve hot.

title: portzelky(new year's cookies)
directions: Soften yeast in 2 cups of water and 5 teaspoons sugar.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Then mix in 2 cups of flour to make sponge. Now let this rise in a warm place.
When light, add all other ingredients and approximately 4 cups flour to make a stiff batter. Let rise until double.
Fry in deep fat in blobs of about 1 tablespoon.
Drain and sprinkle with powdered sugar when slightly cooled.

title: chicken magnific
directions: Cut chicken breasts into pieces or strips.
Melt margarine in frypan; add chicken and cook until white (covered on low heat). Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Melt margarine on the griddle and pour excess in batter.
Batter should be thin.
Fry on medium-high or high.
Roll up pancake and add whipped cream and fruit.

title: sloppy joes for 50 people
directions: Brown ground beef, green peppers and onions.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and bring to boil over full flame.
Turn flame to simmer and cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally. Enjoy!

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Place cake mix and flour into large mixing bowl and combine. In smaller bowl, cream together egg, oil and water.
Stir in dry mixture.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven until done, about 8 minutes.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown sausage and drain.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.
Spread cheese and bread cubes over sausage.
Combine eggs, powdered milk, mustard and salt. Pour over mixture.
Sprinkle parsley on top.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes or until set and firm.
Makes 10 servings.

title: crab and rice casserole
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a bowl. Blend together all remaining ingredients except cheese.
Turn into the crab-rice mixture.
Mix well until blended.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: black walnut bread
directions: Mix sugar, egg and milk until well blended.
Add flour, baking powder and salt into batter.
Add walnuts, mixing well.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Brush top and sides with butter.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together until creamy; pour into a casserole dish.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Mix together and pat into 9 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Add onion, green pepper and celery. Saute until tender.
Add salt, dry soup, water, rice and margarine. Stir well.
Put in greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with almonds.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Stir after 15 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos, cream butter or margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix pudding and milk.
Fold cream cheese and pudding together and then add in Cool Whip.
Layer pudding mixture and Oreos alternating each, with cookies on top.
Serve in a pail with a shovel and gummy worms.

title: squash preserves
directions: Here is something new to do with squash and surprisingly good.

title: delicious torte
directions: Combine flour, margarine, sugar and nuts.
Bake this in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar.
Spread this mixture on cooled base.
Mix pudding with milk; cook until thick.
Cool.
Spoon over cheese mixture. Finally top with Cool Whip.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Chill and serve as desired.

title: open-face strawberry cheese sandwiches
directions: In bowl, combine cream cheese and strawberry spread.
Mix well. Divide and spread on bread.
Cut into 4 triangles.
Serve immediately or cover and refrigerate.
Serves 2. Contains 116 calories, 6 gm fat and 165 mg sodium.

title: cheese chicken pie
directions: Debone cooked chicken and cut in large pieces and set aside. In frying pan, mix onions, bell pepper, celery and butter. Stir frequently, cook on medium heat. After vegetables are cooked, add flour. Cook until golden brown. Stir in chicken broth and chicken and place in casserole dish. Blend flour and shortening in medium bowl. Add shredded cheese; mix well. Add some milk to make consistency to roll out for biscuits. Knead well; roll out into thin layer crust. Cut fifty cent size biscuits; place over chicken mixture. Bake in oven at 350° until topping is golden brown.

title: italian cookies
directions: Mix margarine and sugar together well.
Add anise, eggs, flour and baking powder.
Mix well (will be sticky).
Put dough on floured board and divide into 3 parts.
Roll each into a thin log. Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 8 minutes.
Makes 36 cookies.
Sift confectioners sugar on baked cookies.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle diced apples with lemon juice.
Add celery and enough mayonnaise to moisten.
Serve on lettuce and garnish with Blue Plate mayonnaise.

title: fresh fruit pizza
directions: Crust:
Mix cake mix with the water, brown sugar, margarine and eggs.
Put foil on pizza pan and grease it.
Spread cake mixture over the foil.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
For ease in serving, peel off foil and replace cake on pizza pan.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Melt butter or margarine and add salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Brush chicken thoroughly after cutting it into serving pieces.
Place in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.
Remove from oven and add the combination mushroom soup and water and continue baking for approximately 15 minutes more.
Serves 4.

title: frosted creams
directions: Stir together first 5 ingredients.
Add spices and then add about 6 cups of flour.
Make dough about as thick as you would for cookies that you are going to cut out.
Add raisins, nuts or whatever you like.
Spread in pans and bake at 350°.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Fry sausage and pour out grease.
Add cheese and egg.
Open crescent rolls.
Make one rectangle; pinch seams good.
Spread with 1/3 of mixture and roll like for nut rolls.
Makes 3 rolls.
(Can spread with egg whites on top.)
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fish sticks with cucumber sauce
directions: Cook fish sticks as directed on package.
Cut unpared cucumber into 1-inch pieces.
Chop in blender; drain thoroughly.
Stir cucumber and seasonings into yogurt.
Serve sauce with fish. Makes 6 servings.

title: orange walnut bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking
powder, soda and salt.
Combine eggs, melted oleo, orange juice, orange peel and water; add all at once to flour mixture.
Stir quickly until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in walnuts.
Turn into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.
Slice and serve with oleo.

title: date-nut candy
directions: Cook sugar and milk until thick.
Add butter and dates.
Stir until cool.
Add pecans.
Drop on greased cookie sheet. Cool.

title: mammaroni
directions: Saute meat.
Saute onion, garlic and herbs.
Combine meat, onion mixture, zucchini and crushed tomatoes in a large saucepan. Simmer 2 to 4 hours.
This freezes well.
To serve, add tomato sauce and simmer while cooking macaroni.
Toss pasta with sauce and serve.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: In a large bowl, layer cake, pudding, fruit and Cool Whip. Repeat again, ending with Cool Whip.
Top with a few strawberries.

title: peppy tomato sipper
directions: In a small pitcher, stir together tomato juice or vegetable juice, lime juice or lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, horseradish and hot pepper sauce.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cut up chicken into serving pieces.
Put rice, soup and water in 14-inch Dutch oven.
Stir.
Place chicken over top of mixture. Cover.
Cook
1 1/2 hours with12 coals on top and 10 coals	on the
bottom.
Replenish coals as needed to maintain even baking temperature.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Remove hash browns from freezer for 30 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into rectangular Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sandwich for a crowd
directions: Cut the bread in half lengthwise. Hollow out top and bottom of loaves, leaving a 1/2-inch shell. Combine cheeses, onions, mayonnaise and Worcestershire sauce and spread over crust sides of bread. Layer meat on both halves. Place pickles on bottom half. Gently press halves together. Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 2 hours. Cut into 1 1/2-inch slices. This travels very well.

title: cheese meat loaf
directions: Beat egg in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix lightly, but thoroughly.
Put mixture in a 9 x 4-inch pan.
Spread tomato catsup on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until no red juice runs out when pricked with fork in center.
Garnish with parsley or serve with mushrooms or parsley sauce.
Freezes well and good sliced cold.

title: banana nut ice cream
directions: Fill rest of freezer with milk and freeze.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken pieces in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: low calorie harvest vegetable soup
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, over medium heat, in hot oil, cook onion and garlic until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low and simmer for 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Remove bay leaf before serving. Makes 6 cups or 6 servings.

title: inside out cheeseburger
directions: Mix ground beef, onion and green chilies.
Shape mixture into 8 thin patties; top each of 4 patties with 2 slices of cheese.
Place remaining 4 patties on top.
Pinch edges to seal securely.	Cover and grill patties 4 to 5-inches from medium heat 14 to 16 minutes, turning only once, until burgers are slightly firm when pressed in center.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Prepare pie shell; cool.
Combine cocoa, sugar and cornstarch in medium saucepan; blend in milk until smooth.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture boils; boil and stir 3 minutes. Remove from heat; blend in butter and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell; press plastic wrap onto surface.
Chill 3 hours.

title: salmon and cream cheese ball
directions: Remove the bones from salmon, add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Shape into a ball or log.
Refrigerate.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix pudding according to directions.
Mix in cream cheese until well blended.
Pour into ready made graham cracker crust and chill for 1 hour.
Top with favorite pie filling or fresh fruit.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms.
Mix mayonnaise, crumbled bacon and Lawry's seasoned salt.
Put mix in mushroom caps.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake in 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together thoroughly. Form into small balls. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until brown at 350°.

title: potato salad supreme
directions: Mix well and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: pralines
directions: Mix and cook over medium heat.
When it boils down, drop a few drops in cool water.
When a soft ball is formed, remove from heat.
Add vanilla and pecan halves.
Drop by tablespoon onto waxed paper; cool.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Pour into baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy beef casserole
directions: Cook beef and salt in skillet over medium heat, stirring until meat crumbles and is no longer pink, then drain. Spoon meat into a lightly greased 2 1/2-quart baking dish. Layer vegetables, soup and cheese over beef. Top with Tater Tots. Bake casserole at 400° for 30 minutes or until potatoes are golden brown.

title: foil oven roast
directions: Rub roast with seasoned flour into which garlic has been mashed.
Place large piece of heavy-duty foil on baking pan and center roast on it.
Put under broiler.
Brown meat well on all sides, turning with long-handled meat fork once or twice.
Drain or spoon off fat left in foil after browning.
Combine liquid and seasonings.
Pour over roast.
Place vegetables around roast. Seal foil at top and sides.
Roast at 375° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: mrs. see's never fail fudge
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in large heavy pan. Bring to rolling boil, stirring constantly. Boil for 8 minutes.

title: family-size tuna melt
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix baking mix, 1/3 cup mayonnaise and the milk until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Turn onto surface floured with baking mix.
Knead 10 times.
Pat into rectangle, 12 x 8-inches, on greased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown, about 8 minutes.

title: holiday fruit cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt into bowl and reserve.
Put butter in a large bowl of mixer; add sugar and eggs.
Beat until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add buttermilk, vanilla and flour mixture. Mix well.
Stir in nuts, cherries and dates.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to
350°.	In medium bowl, beat egg yolks; stir in milk,
lime
juice,
rind and food coloring.
In small bowl, stiffly beat
one
egg
white;
fold
into milk mixture. Turn into shell.
Beat
reserved
egg
whites
with
cream
of tartar until foamy;
gradually
add sugar, beating until stiff but not dry. Spread meringue on top of pie, sealing carefully to edge of shell. Bake 15 minutes or until meringue is golden brown.
Cool.	Chill before
serving.
Refrigerate
any leftovers.

title: tea cakes cookies
directions: Add enough flour for a stiff dough; roll thin and cook in hot oven (400°).

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in airtight container.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Soak 3 or 4 slices of bread in milk; add to meat.
Make small meat balls.
Brown in skillet or bake.

title: heavenly bean salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, salt, pepper and vegetable oil.
Heat, but do not boil.
Combine beans and other ingredients; toss together. Pour oil mixture over bean mixture.
Cover tightly; let set for 24 hours.
This salad will keep for weeks, refrigerated.
The longer it marinates, the better the flavor.
Serves approximately 12 to 16.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Mix cocoa, soda and water.
Let stand.
Mix other ingredients in the order given.
Mix well.
Add cocoa mixture.
Pour into lightly greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
(Test doneness after 30 minutes by inserting knife into the center. If the knife comes out clean, the cake is ready!) Frost the cake if you like or cover with confectioners sugar, lightly sprinkled.

title: garbanzo pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain; rinse with cold water and drain.
Crush minced garlic and salt together in a large bowl.
Add chickpeas, kidney beans, sliced olives, onion, broccoli florets, oil and vinegar.
Stir until coated.
Add cooled and drained macaroni and toss.
Serve chilled.
Makes 4 to 8 servings.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into eighths.
Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in a bag.
Moisten potatoes with water and shake (a few at a time), coating well with cheese mixture.
Melt oleo in preheated 375° oven on flat, uncovered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange potatoes in baking pan on the melted oleo.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
(After 30 minutes of baking, turn potatoes over and continue baking for 30 minutes more.)

title: spinach-orzo pie
directions: In medium bowl combine eggs, cooked orzo, 1/2 cup sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Spread over bottom and sides of greased 9-inch pie pan to form a shell.
Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain well.
In another bowl, stir together spinach, Ricotta and nutmeg.
Spoon into bottom of pasta shell.
Spread remaining sauce atop filling.
Cover edge of pasta shell with foil. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with Mozzarella and return to oven 3 to 5 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: heather's favorite wings
directions: Spread wings in shallow pan and cover with the dressing. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until brown.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Defrost hash browns and mix with all ingredients.
Put into a greased 9 x 11-inch glass dish.
Mix 1/2 cup margarine (melted) and 2 cups crushed corn flakes.
Put on top of potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream sugar and margarine at medium speed until combined.
Gradually add egg substitute, beating well. Combine sour cream and baking soda; set aside.
Combine flour and salt at low speed.
Add creamed mixture alternating with sour cream mixture, beginning with and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Spoon batter into prepared 10-inch tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: breakfast burrito
directions: Heat frying pan and oil lightly.
When oil gets hot (i.e. forms "spokes"), lay jalapenos in center.
Pour on the beaten egg. Cook until firm, then turn over.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Pour in a well-greased pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vidalia onion scallop
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel and slice onions.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in skillet.
Add onions and green pepper.
Cook until tender.
Stir in chopped pimiento.
Place half of onion mixture in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup grated cheese and 1/2 cup cracker crumbs.
Repeat layers of onions and cheese.
Beat eggs with light cream, salt and pepper.
Pour over onions. Combine remaining cracker crumbs with melted butter.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until set.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: stacked fruit-wiches(makes 2 sandwiches; 224 calories each)
directions: On each bread slice, layer lettuce, 2 Lite-line slices, apple and pineapple.
In small bowl, combine yogurt and honey; spoon over each sandwich.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Serve immediately.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Place artichoke hearts, Parmesan cheese and mayonnaise in blender for 5 minutes.
Place in pie dish.
Bake in oven for 20 minutes at 300°.
When you remove the mixture, place Tostitos chips around edge of serving mixture in the center.
Start dipping!

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all together well.
Put 2 tablespoons oil in skillet and get real hot.
Pour cornbread mixture in and bake at 425° until brown.

title: crusty corn dogs
directions: Mix 1/2 cup flour, cornmeal, salt and soda.
Beat together buttermilk and egg, then stir into flour mixture until smooth. Cut wieners in half crosswise and roll in flour to coat.
Dip in cornmeal batter to coat.
Fry in about 2 inches hot oil (370° on deep-fat thermometer), 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown. Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot with mustard.
Makes 5 servings.

title: huge rich chocolate cake
directions: Cream together the butter, Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Sift together the flour, cocoa and baking powder; add alternately with milk and vanilla.
Grease and dust with cocoa a 12-cup tube pan or 2 large loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour and 25 minutes at 325°
for the tube or 55 minutes for the loaves.
Should be sliced thin to serve since this is a rich cake.

title: school girl pickles
directions: Wash, but don't split cucumbers.
Put in salt water (enough to float an egg).
Sink and keep under water 2 weeks; drain.
Pour clear water on cucumbers and let stand for 24 hours; drain.
Cut cucumbers to desire.

title: peach poodle
directions: Fill bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan with sliced, pared fruit. Sprinkle fruit with cinnamon and sugar.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add melted butter and eggs to flour mixture.
Stir batter until thoroughly mixed.
(Batter will be stiff.)
Spread batter over fruit.
Bake at 350° approximately 40 to 45 minutes, until golden brown and crusty.

title: kay mc's ranch dip
directions: Mix all together.
Gets better after being made after several days, so make early.
Makes a lot.

title: chocolate pudding dessert
directions: Mix softened butter, flour and pecans.
Press in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°; cool completely.

title: apricot coconut balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Make into tiny balls the size of a walnut.
Roll in coconut.
These freeze very well.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip together cream cheese and peanut butter.
Add sugar, milk and Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Chill 24 hours or freeze.
Top with chocolate syrup, if desired.

title: blueberry yogurt muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in center of mixture. Combine egg and next 4 ingredients; add to dry ingredients. Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened. Gently fold in blueberries. Spoon batter evenly into 12 muffin cups coated with cooking spray; sprinkle 1 tablespoon of sugar evenly over batter. Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden on top. Remove from pans immediately; cool on a wire rack. Yield: 1 dozen.

title: chicken pie
directions: Put bite size pieces of chicken in bottom of casserole, then some broth.
Put small can peas on top of chicken, then spoon chicken soup over this.
Melt oleo and stir in self-rising flour (Red Band) and sweet milk.
Pour over chicken and bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Cream margarine, peanut butter, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients until blended.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls. Roll balls in plain granulated sugar.
Press into small 1 3/4-inch muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes (or 8 minutes) until light brown.
Do not overcook.
Remove from oven.
Immediately press one peanut butter cup into each hot cookie crust.
Allow to cool.
Gently remove from pan.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: mini meat loaf with snappy sauce
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and shape into balls.
Place in muffin pan cups.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cut top off tomatoes; scoop out inside.
Mix vegetables, salad dressing and lemon juice.
Spoon into tomato shells.
Chill and serve.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a well greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: custard rhubarb pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and add to the mixed sugar and flour.
Stir until blended.
Mix in rhubarb.
Add red hots, if desired.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake 15 minutes in 450° oven.
Reduce oven heat to 325° and bake 30 minutes.
Beat egg whites for meringue. Add 1 tablespoon sugar for each egg white (gradually) until whites hold a firm peak.
Spread whipped egg whites over hot pie and brown in 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: spicy holiday punch
directions: Core apples and slice into rings.
In a large pan, combine cider, cinnamon, cloves, apple rings and raisins.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes, until apples are fork tender.
Thinly slice the orange and lemon.
Add orange and lemon slices and the lemon juice to the apple mixture.
Allow to stand for 5 minutes.
Pour into punch bowl and serve warm or chilled. Makes 1/2 gallon.

title: chewy caramel brownies
directions: In large bowl, measure all ingredients.
With mixer at medium speed, beat all ingredients until smooth, occasionally scraping bowl with rubber spatula.
Evenly spread in a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool brownies in pan 5 minutes.
Cut in squares and remove to a wire rack to cool.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: shanghai casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in oil; add chopped onion and cook until tender.
Pour off drippings.
Cook vegetables in water for 5 minutes and drain.
Combine vegetables, soup, salt, pepper, soy sauce and celery.
Stir into meat.
Place in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove cover and sprinkle with Chinese noodles.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: banana pudding
directions: With mixer, beat instant pudding and milk until creamy.
Let stand for a few minutes and it will firm up.
Stir in Cool Whip. In dish, make layers of wafers, bananas, pudding, wafers, bananas and pudding; until all of ingredients are used.
Refrigerate until cool and serve.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion
and
celery
in
oleo.
Salt and pepper to taste. Combine
all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: microwave parsley carrots
directions: Mix all ingredients except carrots in a 1-quart microwave-proof casserole.
Stir in carrots.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap and microwave on High 4 minutes.
Stir.
Cover and microwave until carrots are tender, 4 to 6 minutes longer.
Toss with 2 tablespoons parsley.

title: hamburger and noodle skillet supper
directions: In large pot of boiling water, cook pasta until tender, but firm; drain.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Debone and set aside.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, add all ingredients, except chicken.
Stir together.
Cover with foil.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until rice is done.
Add chicken and place back in oven until chicken gets warm.

title: corn bread
directions: Grease heavily with Crisco an 8-inch iron skillet.
Combine corn meal, buttermilk, oil and water.
Pour into iron skillet and bake at 450° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: granola
directions: You can use honey instead of brown sugar.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Add raisins later.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Cream together the sugar and shortening.
Add the applesauce in which the soda has been dissolved.
Sift in the flour, spices and salt.
Add the raisins and nuts.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet, several inches apart.
Bake at 300° for about 15 minutes. Frost, if desired.
These cookies grow moist and rich with age.

title: chewy bar cookies
directions: Stir cake mix, melted butter and 1 egg.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend cream cheese and 2 eggs.
Sift in powdered sugar and beat until smooth.
Pour over first layer.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Coarsely crush pretzels and melt margarine.
Combine pretzels, margarine and sugar in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Line pan with mixture and bake for 8 minutes at 400°; cool.
Combine Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Beat together and spread over pretzels.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and add strawberries. When it thickens to egg white consistency, spread over Cool Whip mixture.
Let sit, then cut into squares.
Very good!
Pretzels taste like nuts.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream together margaine, vanilla, and sugars.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, and cinnamon.
Add to first mixture and mix thoroughly.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Drop on greased cookie sheets by teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 350 F till light brown.

title: puff balls
directions: Beat well all ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon in hot fat and brown.
Remove from fat and dust with sugar.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Cook hamburger, onion and bay leaf.
Drain.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Put a layer of noodles, meat and sauce, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat steps.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°. Remove and let set for 30 minutes; serve.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat egg yolks; add sugar gradually, mixing well.
Add rum and brandy slowly, beating constantly.
Add ice cream and stir gently. Whip the cream and fold into egg yolk mixture.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Beat egg yolks in bowl you want to serve in or you'll end up in the wrong bowl!
This has a mild taste, but a strong effect!

title: peach spread
directions: Beat the cream cheese until smooth and fluffy.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add almond flavoring.
Mix, then add fresh peaches and mix gently.
Spread on crackers or a cake roll.

title: cinnamon brownies
directions: Combine cocoa and soda.
Melt margarine and blend in 1/3 cup with boiling water.
Add to cocoa mixture, stirring until thickened.
Combine sugar, eggs and vanilla; stir in with 1/3 cup margarine and add to chocolate mixture.
Add flour, cinnamon and salt to chocolate mixture.
Fold in 1 cup semi-sweet chips.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch greased pan for 40 minutes at 350°.
After cooling, frost.

title: banana smash
directions: Mix sugar and water; bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes and cool.
Blend bananas and lemon juice in blender.
Mix all ingredients and freeze.
To serve, thaw until icy and add 2 bottles ginger ale or Mello Yello.

title: hot dog chili sauce
directions: Brown onion and beef in cooking oil.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
Spoon over hamburger buns. Have plenty of finger foods such as dill pickle, carrots, radishes, olives, tomato wedges.
Serve with milk or cocoa or bottled soft drinks.
Cookies or eclairs make the dessert.

title: chocolate raisin cake
directions: Note:
Need 2 (9-inch) or 3 (8-inch) Baker's Secret round cake pans.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook desired amount of noodles according to the box.
Drain and let cool.
Add as many of the next seven ingredients as you like.
Top with Italian dressing.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: taco soup
directions: In large pot, add first 5 ingredients; do not drain canned items.
Simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with taco chips, grated Cheddar cheese, sour cream, green onions or whatever you prefer. This freezes well.

title: sundial dip
directions: 1. Layer above ingredients on large platter.
2. Serve with Tortilla chips

title: curried corn crab cakes
directions: Heat a large non-stick skillet over medium heat. Add first 5 ingredients; saute 4 minutes or until vegetables are soft. Place mixture in a large bowl; cool completely. Stir in crabmeat; set aside.

title: low calorie chili
directions: Combine raw veal
with other ingredients and simmer for 45 minutes.
You may add
diced celery, green pepper and 1 can French-style beans.

title: rosemary roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Warm the stock and melt the butter in a saucepan.
Once the butter is melted, remove from heat.
Pour mixture into a blender.
Add the roasted garlic, rosemary, salt, and black pepper.
Puree.
Place potatoes in a 2 inch deep baking dish.
Pour liquid over the potatoes.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake for approximately 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: cauliflower fritters
directions: Cook the cauliflower in salted water.
Separate into flowerette.
Do not allow to get very soft.
Mix together all the ingredients except oil, until you have a smooth batter.
Heat the oil until very hot.
Dip the flowerette into the batter and fry until golden brown.
Dry on paper towel.
Server over mashed potatoes.

title: unbaked chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a medium saucepan, bring to a boil. Boil for 3 min. over medium heat. Remove from heat, add remaining ingredients; stir well. Drop from tablespoon on waxed paper. Refrigerate.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: chewy charlies
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil (2 minutes), then reduce to low heat.
Add oatmeal and peanut butter.
Mix, then spoon on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Cook butter, sugar and milk 9 minutes; add chips.
Remove from heat and add Marshmallow Creme.
Be sure and beat until chocolate bits and Marshmallow Creme is completely dissolved.
Add nuts before finished beating.
(If you can find the mint chocolate bits it is really delicious.)

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay out coconut and pecan pieces in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix according to the directions on the box.
Pour cake batter over the coconut and pecans.
In a small bowl, mix softened butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth.
Drop this mixture by spoonfuls over the top of the cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.
When done, cake will crack on top.
That's where the name comes from.

title: apple cider syrup
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan; cook and stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves and mixture is bubbly.
Good over pancakes or waffles.

title: lemon pie(heritage recipe)
directions: Mix sugar, flour, and milk and mix well.
Then add lemon rind, lemon juice.
Then pour boiling water over (sugar, flour, and milk mixture) and cook till thick.
pour over the 3 beaten egg yolks (slowly) so as not to curd eggs.
Return to stove and cook till filling is clear.
pour into bake pie crust.

title: hominy grits cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven
to
Bring	grits,	3 cups milk and salt to a
boil; then add eggs and 3/4 cup milk and cook until thickened.	Stir
in cheese and butter and blend well and bake in a buttered baking dish for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: nutty yam bake
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water until tender.
Mash potatoes while still hot.
Add
sugar,
margarine, cinnamon, allspice and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Beat in milk and eggs.
Whip well with potato mixture.
Pour into greased 3 qt. casserole dish.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix milk, butter and sugar in heavy saucepan.
Boil to soft ball stage.
Remove from burner and add peanut butter.
Stir thoroughly.
Pour on buttered platter and cool.
Cut into pieces.

title: ann's lemon lush
directions: Mix together and pat in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.
Cool.

title: methodist punch
directions: Mix water and sugar and boil 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.

title: french cherry dessert
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy; add sugar to egg whites and beat until stiff peaks form.
Combine crackers with baking powder and fold into egg mixture.
Fold in vinegar, vanilla and chopped nuts. Bake in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 325° for 20 minutes; cool.

title: french stew
directions: Cover and bake 3 1/2 or 4 hours in a 350° oven and stir 3 times while cooking.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together and store in large container in freezer. Remove several hours before serving.
Pour into punch bowl and immediately before serving, add 1 quart ginger ale.

title: jackie's baked french toast
directions: Tear bread into 1-inch cubes.
Cut cream cheese into small cubes.
Mix eggs, milk, syrup and cinnamon together.
Layer bread and cream cheese.
Pour egg mixture over bread and cheese evenly. Cover and let set overnight in refrigerator.
Bake in an 11 x 15-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350° or until light golden brown. Top with fresh or frozen strawberries and whipped cream.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine in saucepan for 5 minutes.
Stir in flour.
Add water, bouillon, garlic powder and pepper.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Add broccoli and milk.
Simmer for 10 minutes or until broccoli is tender.
Stir in half and half and cheese. Simmer until cheese is melted, stirring constantly.
Serve hot. Yield:
8 servings.
Can also use no-fat milk and cheese.

title: dora's broccoli salad
directions: Broccoli may be cooked, if desired, but will be crisper if just thawed and drained well.
Mix lightly with other ingredients.
If broccoli is raw, the flavors mix best if refrigerated several hours.

title: sweet 'n tart cabbage rolls
directions: Blanch cabbage leaves by covering them with boiling water for 3 to 4 minutes.
Combine meat, rice, onion, 1 can of the tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Place equal portions of meat mixture in center of each cabbage leaf; fold ends over.
Roll up and fasten with toothpicks.
Mix remaining can of tomato sauce with brown sugar and lemon juice and pour over rolls.
Simmer covered 30 minutes, basting occasionally.
Uncover and continue cooking for another 30 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a covered container.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In pan put milk, Nestle Quik, sugar and margarine and bring to rolling boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and quick oats.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Roll and cut in desired shapes.
Bake at 350°.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Blend pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Layer in cake pan, graham crackers, pudding, graham crackers, pudding and top with frosting.

title: fudge krispies
directions: Slowly heat butterscotch and peanut butter until well blended. Stir in cereal until coated.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill. Heat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour on top of chilled mixture.
Chill, then cut.

title: french bread(freezer)
directions: In large bowl mix well 2 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast.
Add margarine.
Gradually add water to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add 1 cup flour. Beat at high speed for 3 minutes.
Stir in additional flour to make soft dough.
Turn out on floured board and knead a few times to form a ball.
Divide into 4 pieces.
Roll each into a 15 x 8-inch oblong roll.
Roll up tightly like a jelly roll.
Place on greased baking sheet sprinkled with a little corn meal.
Brush with oil.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap, then freeze up to 6 weeks.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: personal pizzas
directions: Flour hands.
Flatten a canned biscuit very thin with the palm of your hand.
Place on baking sheet which has been sprayed with Pam.
Place 2 teaspoons ground beef and spread on biscuit.
Pour 1 teaspoon tomato sauce and tiny pinch of oregano.
Sprinkle 2 teaspoons grated cheese over top.
Repeat with each biscuit.
Bake in oven at 400° until biscuits are done.

title: shipwreck
directions: Layer onions, potatoes, beef, beans, celery, salt and pepper in greased casserole dish.
Poke holes in top of casserole.
Pour soup and water over top.
Bake, covered, for 2 hours.
Amount of vegetables determines size of casserole.

title: date nut bread
directions: Take 5 cans from peas/corn, wash, dry and spray well with Pam. These can be used over again.
Cut dates; sprinkle with baking soda and pour 2 cups boiling water over them.
Let cool.
Beat 2 eggs; add sugar and butter.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with dates and water.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Fill cans 1/2 full.
Set on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni. Cool. Combine with all other ingredients. Refrigerate at least 5 hours (overnight is best).
Makes 1/2 gallon.

title: nutty fruit cookies
directions: Grate the orange.
Cream shortening and sugars.
Mix rest of ingredients except blenderize the eggs and orange segments together and then add to mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on greased sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: dieter's southern corn bread
directions: Stir in oil, creamed corn and eggs into a 21 x 21 x 5-inch pan.
Mix together and then add corn bread mix.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Combine bread, milk, salt and pepper.
Add to ground beef. Form into medium balls.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat balls.
Cook 45 minutes at 375°.

title: addie's broiled chicken
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in a bowl for marinade.
Add chicken breasts to marinate.
Cover and refrigerate 4 to 6 hours or overnight.
Place chicken on broiling rack and sprinkle with paprika.
Broil 4 inches from heat, about 20 minutes on each side, basting with remaining marinade from time to time.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients except Jiffy mix; blend well. Stir in Jiffy mix. Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples, with sugar, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 350°.
Delicious - enjoy!

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter in shallow baking dish.
Add olive oil, lemon juice, scallion, garlic, salt and pepper to butter in dish. Mix well.
Add shrimp to mixture in dish and turn over until well coated.
Place under broiler; cook 5 minutes.
Turn shrimp and cook 5 more minutes.
Serve over rice, garnished with lemon wedges and parsley.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Completely thaw potatoes.
Cream together the sour cream and soup.
Add cheese and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Add potatoes and pepper.
Put in casserole; sprinkle with corn flakes.
Pour 1/4 cup melted butter over corn flakes.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake another 15 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in salt water.
Drain.
Melt margarine, blend in flour, add broth, cook and stir until thick.
Stir in half and half, salt and dash of pepper.
Place broccoli in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 of the sauce over broccoli, top with chicken.
Add Parmesan cheese to remaining sauce and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Then broil for 8 minutes.

title: gram roode's cranberry-apple pie
directions: Chop raisins.
Cut cranberries in half.
Chop apples to size of small fingernail.
Combine all ingredients and let sit overnight, if possible.
Fill pie crust
(Makes one large or 2 small pies.)
Cook at 400° for 10 minutes, then turn to 325°. Cook another 35 to 40 minutes.

title: microwave-blender carrot cake
directions: Sift first 6 dry ingredients together into large mixing bowl. Place oil and carrots in blender container.
Process on grate for 30 seconds.
Add sugar, eggs, orange juice and vanilla.
Blend for 10 to 15 seconds.
Add raisins.
Process on grate for 10 seconds. Stir blended mixture into dry ingredients.
Pour into ungreased microwave tube pan.
Microwave on Bake for 10 minutes, turning 1/4 turn every 3 minutes.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes or until cake tests done.
Frost with cream cheese icing, if desired.

title: holiday fruit cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix well shortening, brown sugar and eggs. Add milk, flour, soda and salt. Mix in dates, fruit and nuts; chill. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheets. Bake 10 minutes.

title: aunt bea's apple dumplings
directions: Pare and core apples.
Place apple slices on 5-inch squares. Sprinkle generously with sugar and spices; dot with butter.
Fold the four corners toward middle and pinch edges.
Place 1-inch apart on greased baking dish.

title: fruit salad
directions: Fold together all ingredients in serving bowl.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
If desired, sprinkle with nutmeg and more coconut before serving.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: noodle hamburger tomato casserole
directions: Fry onion and celery separately.
Brown hamburger.
Add tomato soup and noodles. Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: taco salad ii
directions: Break up lettuce, chop onions, cut up tomatoes and chop green pepper.
Brown ground beef; drain off grease.
Add taco seasoning. Mix all of the ingredients, except cheese, together.
Put in a large bowl; top with the cheese.
Best if made ahead and chilled overnight in refrigerator.

title: hamburger roast
directions: Make hamburger into patties and place in a baking dish.
Place potato and onion slices on top of the patties.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour soup over this and cover with foil.
Bake at 450° for 45 minutes.
Soup makes an excellent gravy.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt margarine with chocolate over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar, corn syrup, flour, vanilla and salt.
Mix until smooth.
Beat in eggs.
Pour into crust and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until puffy.
Will drop when cool.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Saute
carrots, celery and onions in butter over medium heat, about 10 minutes.
Stir
in
flour
and
cook
1 minute. Combine milk and broth.
Pour
slowly
into
flour mixture and blend well. Continue to
cook
mixture
until it thickens and becomes bubbly. Remove from heat.
Pour into baking dish; add peas, cooked chicken, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Place crust over
mixture, cutting slits in the top to vent.
Bake at 400° for
to
35 minutes until crust is brown.
(Recipe may be doubled.)

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli, drain.
Mix remaining ingredients except bread crumbs and cheese.
Simmer on top of stove 10 minutes.
Place in greased dish (or Pam it).
Sprinkle bread crumbs and cheese on top.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: creamy fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter and milk in heavy 4-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add rest of ingredients.
Mix well and pour into buttered pan.
Delicious! Treat!!

title: janice's cheese meatballs
directions: Shape the first 10 ingredients into balls and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cook the sauce (remaining ingredients) until it is well blended.
Pour over meatballs.
Return to oven and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: 4 layered chocolate speckled cake
directions: Grease 2 round pans with flour and 2 tablespoons butter.
Melt very slowly in a double boiler 1 1/2 pounds butter until just creamy.
Add to mixer 8 egg yolks with 3/4 cup sugar on high 1 minute.
Will be slightly thick and yellowish.
Put on slow speed and add cake flour, scrape bowl, add creamy butter.
Beat 8 egg whites with 1/2 cup sugar until stiff peaks then add to mixture. Fold in 8 ounces grated chocolate.

title: confetti salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
In another bowl mix last 5 ingredients.
Add 2 mixtures together; mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat until fluffy eggs, sugar, vanilla and oil.
Add zucchini, flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir in pineapple, raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured pan (9 x 12-inch) at 350° for about 45 minutes or until done.

title: lemon fluff salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Mix with cream cheese.
Put in refrigerator until partially jelled, then add pineapple and fold in cream that has been whipped.
Chill until set.
May be served in molded form or casserole dish.

title: cheesecake
directions: Let cream cheese set at room temperature until softened. Combine cream cheese and sour cream, beating well.
Add eggs and sugar; beat well.
Add vanilla and cornstarch; beat well.
Stir in whipping cream with spatula.
Use a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Place drained pineapple in bottom of pan; pour in cheesecake mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pistachio salad (watergate)
directions: *Use all of fruit juices.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add chicken broth.
Bring to a boil and add noodles, garlic and broccoli.
Boil for 4 minutes.
Add cheese and milk.
Stir and heat until cheese is fully melted.

title: hot chocolate mix(makes 8 quarts)
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together thoroughly.
Use 1/3 cup of the mixture for each cup of hot chocolate.
Simply add hot water and stir.
It is delicious and because of nonfat nature of the ingredients, it is low in calories.

title: salmon loaf(from 1975 edition)
directions: Mix salmon, crumbs, salt, pepper and butter; combine and add egg and milk or salmon liquid.
Put in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: chili pie
directions: Line a dish with 1/2 package of Fritos.
In skillet, heat a cup of water with salt, pepper, garlic and Worcestershire. Crumble the ground beef and cook until brown.
Put 1/2 of beef over Fritos.
Add 1/2 of cheese and pepper.
Add rest of Fritos. Then add rest of beef over Fritos and onions.
Add cup of broth over top.
Heat chili and put over all of top.
If you like, you may add cheese on top.
Bake in oven at 300° for 25 minutes or until cheese is melted or browned lightly.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add beaten egg.
Add cinnamon, nutmeg and flour.
Add apples and pecans.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Can double or triple recipe.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Let stand while cake is baking.
Pour over cake while it is warm.

title: fast lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna as directed on box. Brown beef with onion and salt and pepper. Add Ragu. Drain lasagna and layer in a 9 x 13-inch casserole or small one serving bowls that can be frozen for later. First a layer of lasagna, sauce and cheeses. Repeat layers. Bake in 350° oven for 20 or 30 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix altogether in large bowl.
Cover and let set in fridge for 3 days.
Stir once a day.
Add fruit juice if it is too dry.

title: mocha freeze
directions: In blender container or food processor bowl with metal blade, combine ice cream, coffee, chocolate syrup and crushed ice. Cover.
Blend until of desired consistency.
Pour into glasses. Garnish with chocolate shavings.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: one cup cookie
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill 1 hour.
Roll in ball and flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine ingredients.
Make into 2 layers and cook in 350° oven. Use only Duncan Hines mix.
Use strawberry filling.

title: peach upside-down cake
directions: In small saucepan, combine brown sugar and 1/2 stick margarine; melt, stirring to combine.
Spread on bottom of 9-inch round cake pan.
Arrange peaches over brown sugar.

title: country style steak
directions: Heat oil to medium heat.
Wash steak; while wet, roll in flour.
Add margarine to oil.
Fry quickly until brown on both sides.
Place in deep baking dish.
Pour off oil leaving about 4 tablespoons.
Brown a scant 1/2 cup flour to a light brown, stirring constantly.
Add 3 large cups water.
Let come to a boil. Continue to stir.
Pour over steak.
Cover dish.
Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Add more water if needed for gravy.

title: chocolate peanut squares
directions: Microwave 3/4 cup margarine with 2 chocolate squares on High 1 to 2 minutes or until melted when stirred, stirring every 30 seconds.

title: mixed berry cobbler
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Add butter.
Pour into 8 1/4 x 1 3/4 inch round ovenware cake dish.

title: chicken, potato and onion bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large casserole dish, place a a layer of sliced potatoes and a layer of onions.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Alternate layers until vegetables are gone.
Place chicken breasts on top and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Tuck bay leaves under the chicken.
Cover and cook for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: aunt edna's american lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and garlic in hot fat.
Add tomato puree, salt, pepper and oregano.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Cook noodles.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Best after setting overnight.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook chicken, chopped celery and salt.
Remove meat from bones and dice.
Place in
a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Save juice from chicken.
Cook rice in juice.
Put rice over chicken.
Pour can of soup over rice.
Mix Bisquick and milk.
Drop with tablespoon on top of casserole, until covered.
Bake in oven at 325° until brown.

title: gau(chinese new year's pudding)
directions: Stir water and sugar together over low heat until sugar is dissolved.	Bring to a boil, remove from heat and let cool. Add gradually to
the
flour;
mix
well.
Add	oil; mix well. Pour mixture into
a
pan
or
Pyrex
dish
(about 8 inches in diameter and 3 inches deep) which has been lined with oiled ti leaves. Steam 3
hours.
(One
cup fresh shredded coconut may be added
to the
pudding
before
steaming;
mix well.) When pudding is done, place 1 red date in the center; sprinkle with sesame seed.

title: chocolaty chili
directions: Heat oil in large skillet; saute onion and garlic until tender. Add beef; cook over medium heat until brown.
Drain.
Stir in beans, puree, paste, peppers and water.
Stir in one envelope ChocoBake, chili powder and bouillon; mix well.
Simmer uncovered 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Stir in remaining ChocoBake and heat through.
Serve over corn chips or over hot rice.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown beef in large skillet.
Drain fat.
Add Ragu; heat just to boiling.
Mix shredded Mozzarella cheese, cottage cheese, egg, parsley, salt and pepper.
Ladle 1/3 of meat sauce into bottom of an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Layer 3 noodles, then 1/2 cheese mixture and 2nd 1/3 of meat sauce.
Repeat.
Top with 3 noodles and Mozzarella slices, in that order.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
This also freezes well for a make-ahead meal.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix with pretzels, sugar and pecans.
Pat in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°. Cool.
Beat cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Spread on first layer.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Mix Jell-O in boiling water.
Add strawberries and stir until thick.
Pour over top and refrigerate.

title: icebox sweet pickles
directions: Mix vinegar and sugar until sugar dissolves.
Add spices and cucumbers and onions.
Let sit in icebox 4 days before serving. This was given to me by Sharon Guthrie.
It's a very good pickle.

title: jambalaya (large)
directions: Brown chickens and sausage in grease (small amount).
Take up meat and remove some of the grease.
Put rice in and brown some more.
Add onions and celery; brown a little.
Add 6 cups hot water.
Season to taste (sauce) with salt and pepper.
Add chicken and sausage; bring to simmer.
Cover and let simmer for 20 minutes. Turn mixture after 20 minutes and be sure to get all the rice from the bottom of pan.
Let cook until tender.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a mixer until smooth.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Add topping.

title: granny's chewy bread
directions: Combine sugar and eggs in heavy saucepan, stirring well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients, mixing well. Spoon mixture into a greased and floured baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: heritage caramel frosting
directions: Combine 3 cups of sugar and milk in a large saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, until sugar is dissolved. Remove from heat and set aside.

title: cranberry orange salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add cold water.
Chill until very thick.
Cut orange in wedges; remove seeds.
Put orange and cranberries through food chopper.
Mix fruit and sugar.
Fold into gelatin.
Pour into large (2-quart) mold, or individual molds.
Chill until firm.
Makes about 12 servings.
Great for the holidays!

title: shrimp spread
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Add remaining ingredients except shrimp and cocktail sauce.
Blend well and shape into a 9-inch pie pan, cover and refrigerate overnight. Before serving, cover with cocktail sauce.
Place thawed shrimp on top of sauce and serve.

title: pumpkin spice bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Beat eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin.
Stir in flour, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda, salt, ginger and cloves. Mix in raisins.
Pour into pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost when cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Cut up chicken into small chunks in oblong casserole dish.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Crunch up Ritz crackers and put on top of chicken. Melt 1 stick of butter and pour on top of crackers.
Sprinkle poppy seed on top.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350° or until bubbly.

title: meat ball oven stew
directions: Combine meat, onion, green pepper, corn meal, seasonings, milk and egg.
Mix thoroughly and form into 12 balls.
Sprinkle with flour and brown in hot shortening.
Place in 4-quart casserole.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Cut in shortening, then add water, vinegar, eggs and sugar.
Store in a covered container in the refrigerator.
This is enough mix to make 3 (8-inch) double crust pies.

title: 24 hour fruit salad
directions: Combine egg yolks, sugar, vinegar, pineapple syrup and salt in top of double boiler.
Cook over hot, not boiling, water until thick, stirring constantly.
Add butter and cool.
Fold in whipped cream, a little at a time.
Add to fruit.
Spoon into serving bowl.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Layer 1: Mix pretzels and melted butter. Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes. Let cool.

title: pearl onions in cream sauce
directions: Melt butter over medium-high heat.
When melted, add flour, stirring constantly with wire whisk.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Add nutmeg and hot pepper sauce.
Fold in onions and mix well.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.

title: perfect pasta salad
directions: Cook linguine; drain.
Add spinach, ham, carrots and peppers (matchstick thin strips).
Add cheese, oil, vinegar, salt, pepper and oregano.
Serves 6 main dish servings, 330 calories, 15 g fat.

title: nana's pineapple and carrot salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water; add grated carrot and pineapple. Place in refrigerator until jelled.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into two 9-inch graham cracker pie shells.
Place in refrigerator to set.

title: hot chocolate(homemade)
directions: Mix together.
Add 1/3 to 1/2 cup mix to boiling water.

title: pecan cheese ball
directions: Let cheese soften to room temperature.
Blend with electric mixer.
Add onion,
A-1 sauce and 1 cup pecan pieces.
Chill mixture until firm enough to mold.
Make into ball the size of a grapefruit.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Boil pineapple and enough water to make 2 cups of liquid.
Mix jello with this boiling liquid.
Add cranberries, pineapple, pecans, lemon juice and sugar.
Stir well and pour into bowl or mold.
Refrigerate until set.

title: peach cobbler with praline biscuits
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Gradually stir in water; add peaches.
Bring to a boil and cook 1 minute, stirring often.
Remove from heat.
Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside.

title: kathy's valentine mimosa
directions: Prepare the orange juice according to the package instructions.
Combine with the pineapple juice in a large bowl or pot; chill.
When ready to serve, pour in the champagne.
Serve in wine glasses with a cherry in the bottom of each.
Yields about 1 gallon.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Line an 8-inch pie pan with pastry. Combine pineapple with cornstarch, sugar and salt. Cook until thick and clear, stirring constantly. Add butter and lemon juice. Pour into pie pan. Weave strips of pie dough across top. Bake in 425° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: frozen bread caramel rolls
directions: Thaw, but do not allow to rise (they shall rise some though) the 2 loaves of bread.
Break 1 loaf up in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients in 4-quart glass dish.
Microwave 5 minutes.
Stir.
Microwave 4 minutes and stir.
Then microwave 2 minutes and stir.
Remove from microwave and add the vanilla. Beat 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour by tablespoons onto buttered cookie sheet.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Add sour cream, seasoning, soups, green chilies, onion and grated cheese.
Place 1/4 cup mixture on tortilla shell; roll up.
Place in pan.
Continue until all shells are filled.
Put remaining mixture on top of rolled shells.
Top with remaining grated cheese.
Microwave for 20 minutes at half power.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in blender.
Blend 30 to 45 seconds, low speed.
Stir in poppy seed.
Cover and chill.
Stir before using.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.
Good with fruit or spinach salads.

title: fabulous fake "tenderloin"
directions: Place in baking pan. Put in 250° oven for several hours. Should look charred and cracked like a too done hot dog from your char grill. Put on serving platter. Use greens and cherry tomatoes around. Use party rye and mini French bread, several mustards, mayos, horseradish, whipped cream, etc. around fabulous fake. Delish and no one sure what it is, but most think it is beef tender!

title: shrimp thermidor
directions: Cook onion, green pepper and butter together.
Add cream and potato soup; stir over heat until boiling point.
Add cheese, lemon juice and shrimp.
Serve in patty shells or with toast points.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Grease 4 (8-inch) round cake pans.
In large mixing bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in flour (1 cup at a time), until well mixed.
Divide dough into 4 equal pieces.
Pat each piece evenly into bottom of pan with hands.
With tines of fork, prick dough all over to prevent bubbles.
Serves 32.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Marinate for several hours or overnight.

title: busy day pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place meat in a heavy Dutch oven.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Spread over top and sides of roast.
Cover and bake about 3 hours or until tender. Remove meat from pan to a cutting board or platter.
Let stand about 5 minutes.
Cut into thin slices.
Pour gravy from Dutch oven into a bowl or sauce boat.
Spoon over each slice of roast.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: monkey juice
directions: Mash the banana.
Combine all ingredients together in a blender, bowl or in a jar with a tight fitting lid.
Shake well.

title: white sauce
directions: Blend first three ingredients with wire whip or blender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with chicken or other meats.
May use to baste meats before cooking.
Store in refrigerator.

title: nut candy("nuent")
directions: Bring the sugar and honey to a boil; boil them for 10 minutes. Slowly add
the nuts.
Cook the mixture until it is thick, until the candy thermometer registers the soft-crack stage.
Spoon the mixture out onto a wet marble slab or wooden board.
Dip your hands in ice water and pat the mixture into a square, about 1-inch thick.
Let the square cool slightly.
Using a sharp knife, cut into squares or diamonds.
Yields about 2 1/2 pounds.

title: louisiana pralines
directions: Let this come to a boil, then add a big pinch of soda.
After this boils, add 1 1/2 cups nuts and cook until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Beat until creamy and drop from spoon on waxed paper.
For best results, cook in a heavy skillet.

title: escalloped potatoes(serves approximately 50 people.)
directions: Melt margarine; add flour gradually to make a thick base.
Add 1/2 milk gradually and alternate with soup until all has been added to base.
Using large roaster sprayed with Pam, pour white sauce in bottom to cover.
Add layer of potatoes, then more of sauce until all is used, ending with sauce.
You may have to add more milk.
Bake in 350° oven until done.
Remove lid to brown top if desired.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Bake cornbread, fry bacon and let both cool.
Chop tomatoes, pepper, onion and pickles together.
Crumble bacon into chopped veggies and toss.
Mix pickle juice, salad dressing and sugar until creamy and smooth.

title: never fail heart shaped cookies
directions: Mix well. Wrap dough in plastic wrap and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Roll out. Cut with heart shaped cookie cutter and sprinkle with regular or red hearts. Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: mrs. n. c. payne's special pound cake
directions: Mix flour and butter until real creamy and fluffy.
Now beat eggs well and add the sugar with the baking powder sifted in to the eggs.
Add this to the creamy flour and butter and beat thoroughly.
Bake in a tube cake pan, greased and dusted with flour for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken crescents
directions: Combine cream cheese, margarine and lemon pepper.
Stir in chicken and mushrooms.
Unroll crescents into triangles with a rolling pin.
Put 1/4 cup of chicken mixture onto each triangle.

title: low-fat pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large bowl, combine egg whites and pumpkin.
Stir in sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Stir in milk.
Pour into crust.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 40 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Cool on rack.

title: orange candied pecans
directions: Mix all of the ingredients, except pecans; cook to soft ball stage.
Beat, then add pecans.
Stir until pecans are well coated. Spread out on paper and separate.

title: texas pie
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar, flour and corn meal; mix well. Add pineapple and all other ingredients; mix. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 450° for 5 minutes, then at 325° and bake an additional 1 hour. Cool.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Discard chicken wingtips.
Rinse remaining wing pieces and pat dry, then arrange in a single layer in 2 lightly greased shallow 10 x 15-inch baking pans.
Bake, uncovered, in 400° oven until golden brown, about 30 minutes.

title: chicken egg drop soup
directions: In large saucepan, heat chicken broth to boiling.
Blend cornstarch with water to make smooth paste.
Stir in soy sauce. Slowly stir into broth; bring to boil and simmer until clear, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Gradually add eggs, stirring until eggs separate into shreds.
Add green onions and season to taste.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: eagle brand milk
directions: Mix with mixer until thick.
Makes 1 can.

title: basic roll dough
directions: Measure 9 cups sifted flour (reserve 1/2 cup for kneading). Soften 2 packages yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Combine 1 cup scalded milk, 1/2 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon salt, 1/2 cup shortening.
Add 1 cup of water.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add softened yeast.
Blend in 1/2 of flour and beat well for 1 minute (may add crushed seeds of cardamom here).
Add 2 unbeaten eggs and blend thoroughly.
Blend remaining flour in gradually and stir until all of flour is worked in.
Amount will vary from 4 to 4 1/2 cups. Let rise until doubled.
Punch down and form into desired roll shapes.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in 400° oven.

title: nelda's baked brisket
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour over brisket.
Marinate overnight.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour per pound.
Can use a cooking bag and cut down on cooking time and clean up.

title: southwestern shoepeg corn
directions: Melt the butter and cream cheese in a glass casserole dish in the microwave.
Mix well.
Add to the cheese mixture the corn, garlic powder, milk, and peppers.
Mix well.
Place in a preheated 350° oven and bake for 30 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: aunt bev's brownies
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and vanilla; beat in the eggs and blend in the chocolate.
Stir in the flour and nuts.
Bake in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 325°.

title: salmon appetizers
directions: In a small bowl, combine salmon, cream cheese, salsa, parsley and cilantro.
Spread about 2 tablespoons of the salmon mixture over each tortilla.
Roll each tortilla up tightly and wrap individually with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Slice each tortilla into bite-size pieces.
Yield: about 48 appetizers.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Mix well and roll into small balls.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Roll in some additional powdered sugar.
Makes approximately 3 1/2 dozen.

title: chicken zucchini casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Arrange zucchini slices in 8 x 8 x 2-inch casserole.
Top with chicken.
Mix soup, milk and nutmeg.
Spread over chicken.
Mix baking mix, cheese and egg until crumbly. Sprinkle over soup mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Drizzle with margarine.
Bake until golden brown, about 25 to 30 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chinese chews
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar, flour, salt and baking powder. Mix until crumbly.
Add eggs, vanilla and nuts.
Mix thoroughly. Spread in greased and floured 14 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm.
Makes 16 squares.

title: brunch egg casserole
directions: Combine the croutons with the cheese.
Place in baking dish. Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over the crouton mix. Sprinkle cooked bacon or sausage over top.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.
I use a 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch dish.

title: banana cupcakes
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat sugar, butter, egg yolks, banana and vanilla on medium speed until fluffy.
Sift and beat remaining ingredients on low speed.
As soon as the last of the flour disappears, fold in the beaten egg whites.
Spoon into muffin cups.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: christmas cranberry salad
directions: Grind apple, cranberries and orange together.
Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix
graham crackers, margarine and sugar; pack into an 8 x 11-inch pan.
Build up well on sides.
Prepare Dream Whip as directed on package; add softened cream cheese, lemon juice and powdered
sugar.
Beat
until
smooth.
Pour
into graham cracker crust;
chill
until
firm.
Add
1 can of cherry pie filling to top.
Chill and serve.

title: pork loin
directions: Bake covered at 350° for 2 hours.

title: double cheese meat
directions: Combine meat, egg, cracker crumbs, onion, 1/3 cup tomato sauce with cheese, salt, oregano and pepper. Mix well and shape into flat rectangle about 10 x 12-inches on wax paper.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over meat mixture.
Roll up like jelly roll.
Press ends of roll to seal.
Bake in shallow baking dish at 350° for 1 hour. Drain excess fat.
Pour remaining sauce over roll and bake 15 minutes more.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine; press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs, bottle lemon juice and flour; mix well.
Stir in 1 cup blueberries.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until center is set.
Cool.
Chill; top with Blueberry Sauce.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: nonalcoholic orange cocktail
directions: Pour the juice into a 2-quart pitcher.
Add the sugar and stir to mix well.
