Add the mineral water and crushed ice and stir to combine.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 drinks.

title: walnut balls
directions: To prepare shells, soften butter and cream cheese; blend together with flour until dough like.
Take dough and make 24 balls the size of a walnut and press into lining of tart cups.

title: chocolate haystacks
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and oleo in a saucepan; bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Allow oatmeal time to absorb moisture, then spoon out onto waxed paper and allow to harden.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until light brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Put a toothpick into each ball and serve.

title: lemon squares
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour this over baked crust and return to oven for 25 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while still warm.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in greased loaf pan in 375° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until inserted tester comes out clean. Remove from pan and cool at least 10 minutes before slicing. Makes 1 loaf.

title: impossible bacon quiche
directions: Grease 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion into this.
Combine other ingredients and pour over bacon mixture. Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: jello vegetable salad
directions: Combine vegetables, vinegar, salt and pepper; set aside. Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Combine cold water and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups.
Add to Jell-O; stir until slightly thickened.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Add vegetable mixture. Chill until thickened, about 5 minutes.
Pour into individual dishes.
Chill; soft set in 30 minutes.
Garnish with vegetables. Makes 6 servings.

title: italian spaghetti with meat sauce
directions: Cook and stir meat, onion and pepper until meat is brown and onion tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients except spaghetti and cheese.
Cover; simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Cook spaghetti as directed on package and drain.
Serve meat sauce over hot spaghetti.
Pass Parmesan cheese if desired.
Serves 8.

title: spice christmas punch(yield: 5 quarts)
directions: Heat juice with cinnamon candies and sugar until dissolved and chill.
Chill ginger ale and add to juice mixture when ready to serve.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: chicken rolls
directions: *Cook white and/or dark meat of chicken or use leftovers.

title: butterfingers
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Roll into finger shaped rolls.
Bake 25 minutes at 300°.
Cool and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: frozen delight
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar together.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and put into a casserole dish.
Put in freezer and let get hard.
Take out about 10 minutes before ready to serve.

title: fried chicken casserole
directions: Quickly
fry
chicken
just
until golden brown on both sides. Place
in
casserole;
pour all other ingredients over and bake 1 hour or until tender, at 350°.

title: grandma huber's spanish rice
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Brown ground beef.
Cook rice.
Mix meat, rice and vegetables together.
Add tomato sauce, sugar, salt and pepper.
Put 1/2 of mixture in 9-inch pan.
Cover with Velveeta slices.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: praline cookies
directions: Spread large cookie sheet with graham cracker sections.
Bring margarine or butter, brown sugar and vanilla to a boil.
Do not overcook.
Add pecans; pour over graham crackers.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let set 3 minutes and take off pan.
Put on wax paper immediately.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Toast and crumble white bread.
Crumble cornbread.
Mix all ingredients.
Add liquid from turkey.
Make very moist.

title: baked squash
directions: Cook squash and drain; add all ingredients.
Pour into greased, shallow Pyrex dish; top with additional cheese and crackers.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: cornbake
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in margarine.
In separate bowl, mix together corn, eggs and muffin mix.
Add sauteed vegetables. Put in 2-quart casserole and top with sour cream which has been mixed with cheese.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: fresh vegetable dip
directions: Put the mayonnaise and cottage cheese in a blender and blend until smooth.
Sprinkle in the Green Goddess Dressing mix and stir well.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Fry in patties on hot griddle or pan.
Um, um, good!

title: onion-garlic potato bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Over medium heat, melt butter.
Stir in onion soup mix, garlic salt and parsley flakes until blended.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water to a froth.
Combine sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Dip pecans in egg white.
Shake in a plastic bag with sugar mixture.
Place in a shallow pan.
Bake at 300° for 30-45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: brownies (gaye's)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs (beaten) and vanilla.
Mix in chocolate, then the dry ingredients.
Last, stir in nuts.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch pan; do not overcook.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts until done.
Boil egg noodles until done. Melt butter and blend with sour cream and chicken soup.
Cut chicken in bite-size pieces.
Mix chicken, noodles and mixture above.
Spread in baking dish.
Crush crackers and sprinkle on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beef stew(diabetic recipe)
directions: Brown meat and onions, salt, and pepper. add V8 juice. Add cooked potatoes, cover and simmer until everything is cooked (about 30 minutes).

title: ice cream dessert
directions: *Measured after they are crushed.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Combine.
Cook in 3 cake pans at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: a good easy dish
directions: Cook ground beef until done and drain.
Add Ragu sauce and rice.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cracker simpletons
directions: Use saltine crackers, Ritz or any favorite cracker.
On one side only, brush with melted margarine.
Sprinkle buttered top with paprika and a touch of Parmesan cheese.
Place in broiler until brown (watch carefully); don't burn.

title: date bars
directions: Combine dates, butter and brown sugar.
Stir in egg, vanilla, oats, flour, nuts, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Mix together just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spread into prepared pan.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cut into 2 x 1 1/2-inch bars.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: turkey hustle up
directions: Combine turkey with next 8 ingredients and add 1/2 teaspoon salt in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into 8 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix remaining 1/2 teaspoon salt, flour, sesame seed, cheese and butter in bowl.
Spread over turkey mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: baked clams
directions: Mince garlic cloves and chop small onions.
Saute in oil.
Add clams, white wine, celery salt, salt and pepper to taste, oregano and butter; simmer for 15 minutes.
Add chopped parsley for color. Add enough bread crumbs to absorb liquid.
Fill clam shells, then sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Filled clam shells can be frozen until ready to be baked.

title: oatmeal cookies(5 dozen)
directions: Place shortening, sugar, egg, water and vanilla in bowl.
Beat and sift flour, salt and soda.
Add to the other mixture.
Blend well.
Add oats and drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
For variety, add nuts, raisins, chocolate chips or coconut.

title: lime cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
In saucepan, heat pineapple and sugar until dissolved.
Add to jello mix.
Chill in refrigerator until partially set.
Gently fold in cheese and whipped cream. Chill in refrigerator until set.

title: abby seeger's shrimp
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add shrimp and toss to coat.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 450°. Cook shrimp 10 minutes; stir occasionally.
Garnish with lemon wedges.
Serve with French bread slices.

title: california salad with beverly's honey dijon dressing
directions: Wash and pat dry the lettuce leaves. Tear into bite size pieces in a large salad bowl. Add sliced avocado, oranges, onion rings and halved, large black olives. Set aside.

title: chili cheese strata
directions: In buttered 2-quart shallow dish, arrange bread cubes evenly. Sprinkle 1 cup cheese evenly over cubes.
Pour chili salsa to cover evenly; set aside.
In blender, combine eggs, soup, milk, onion and Worcestershire sauce; pour over bread mixture.
Top with remaining cheese.
Cover; refrigerate 6 hours or overnight. Uncover; dust top with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until lightly browned and bubbly.
Makes 8 servings.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients well; save part of cheese.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: old bottled fruit cake
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Put 1 quart of fruit in blender and blend real good.
Add soda to the fruit.
Mix dry ingredients with fruit.
Add oil.
Can add nuts or raisins if wanted.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Combine
margarine,
cocoa,
milk,
powdered
sugar and vanilla; blend well.
Stir	in pecans and coconut.	Will frost one 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake

title: cindy's chicken casserole
directions: Tear chicken into pieces.
Melt oleo in stewer or skillet. Add flour and brown.
Add soup, broth and Cheddar cheese; cook. Melt 1/2 stick oleo in casserole dish.
Add cracker crumbs.
Place chicken on top of crumbs and pour sauce mixture on chicken and top with crushed potato chips.
Bake 20 minutes in a 400° oven.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: peaches 'n cream pancakes
directions: Beat all ingredients, except peaches and whipping cream, with a wire whisk or hand beater until well blended. Pour by scant 1/4 cupfuls onto hot griddle (grease griddle if necessary). Cook until pancakes are dry around the edges. Turn; cook until golden brown. Top with peaches and whipped cream.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Add cream cheese, pineapple and baby food; mix together.
When cool, fold in Cool Whip.
Mold.

title: pink salmon dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Refrigerate 3 hours.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: baked chicken that makes its own gravy
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
Arrange in single layer with skin sides down in melted butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in moderately hot oven at 425° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken, bake until brown, 15 to 20 minutes longer or until tender.
Remove from oven; reduce temperature to 325°.
Pour off excess fat.
Add onions and mushrooms to chicken.
Combine undiluted milk, soup, cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with foil.
Return to oven; continue baking 15 to 20 minutes.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti. Melt margarine and spread on bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Toss spaghetti around in margarine, then sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Layer the following over the spaghetti: 8 ounces shredded Mozzarella cheese, mushrooms (drained), pepperoni slices, spaghetti sauce and 8 ounces shredded Mozzarella cheese. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until bubbly. Set 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fantastic fruit salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese with 1 package orange jello.
Add drained pineapple, oranges and container of Cool Whip.
Mix all together well and place in the refrigerator to set up.

title: peach pie
directions: Combine white sugar, flour, nutmeg and egg.
Blend well.
Add the peaches and toss to coat.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Mix in grenadine syrup and pour mixture into uncooked pie crust (deep dish).
Dot with butter, cover with top crust or lattice strips and bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.
If served cold, top with whipped cream.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Mix vinegar, oil, sugar and black pepper.
Pour mixture over cucumbers and onions and marinate, the longer the better.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together. Melt marshmallows and condensed milk and mix with first 4 ingredients. Pack in foil lined container and set in the refrigerator for 3 days. On the fourth day, peel off foil and roll in sugar. Repack in foil and refrigerate a couple more days before slicing. Keep refrigerated.

title: mock enchilada
directions: Brown ground meat and onion.
Add chili; simmer a few minutes until blended.
Crush corn chips and put half in bottom of casserole.
Add meat mixture.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Add rest of the corn chips.
Garnish with sliced olives.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° or until cheese melts.

title: salmon and rice
directions: Cook rice as usual, using a little less water.
While rice is cooking over a medium fire, fry bacon.
Remove bacon from pan and add minced onions to bacon drippings.
Cook minced onions until golden.
Add salmon to onions, chopping it up in frypan until pieces are small.
Rice should be cooked just until water is boiled off.
Add salmon, mix in with rice.
Cook under low fire until done.
Fried or boiled okra goes excellent with this dish.
Crumble bacon over the salmon and rice.

title: chocolate lush
directions: Mix well the first 3 ingredients.
Press in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes; cool.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Mix milk and pudding until stiff and thick.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with additional Cool Whip and garnish with more chopped nuts.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix together and spread into a greased pan; bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken and asparagus soup
directions: In a soup pot, bring the broth and water to a boil.
Add the noodles.
Bring mixture back to boil, then reduce the heat to medium and cook for about 6 minutes.
Add the asparagus and chicken.
In a small bowl, combine the Hollandaise sauce mix with the half and half and beat until smooth.
Add to the soup mixture along with the butter.
Continue cooking over medium heat for about 3 to 5 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: banana-applesauce bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix the bananas and sugar together.

Set aside for 15 minutes. Add the applesauce and eggs; beat well. Add the remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan that has been coated with nonstick vegetable spray. Bake 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Allow to cool 10 minutes before removing from the pan onto a wire rack.

title: bread pudding(heritage recipe)
directions: Beat eggs, add milk, sugar and vanilla and stir well together.
Add softened butter and mix with dry bread which has been broken into small pieces or cubed.

title: cocktail meatballs ii
directions: *Can substitute ready made and cooked small meatballs.

title: crisco icing
directions: Beat by hand until creamy.
Great on Zucchini Cake.

title: shrimp curry
directions: Make white sauce from ingredients (will actually be yellow from curry) and simmer until thick. Best to make with a whisk. Add 3 pounds small raw shrimp and heat until pink. Remove from heat and stir in 1 teaspoon lemon juice. Serve over hot rice.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Cream together the sugar and butter.
Add egg, persimmon pulp mixture and vanilla.
Sift the flour, spices and salt over the egg mixture.
Mix in the nutmeats and dates.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 325°.

title: angie's bread and butter pickles
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 4 ingredients; stir in a large amount of cracked ice.
Let stand for 3 hours; drain well.
Remove garlic.
In a large kettle, combine remaining ingredients.
Add drained mixture and bring to a boil.
Use water bath canning:
pack pickles and liquid into hot, clean jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Wipe rims and adjust lids.
Process for 5 minutes for pints or half pints.
Makes 6 pints.

title: meal-in-a-skillet
directions: Brown hamburger, do not drain. Add Lipton soup mix, stir and add water, tomatoes and rice. Simmer until rice is nearly done, then
add garden peas and cook until liquid is nearly gone. Grate cheese over top and melt. Can be served with crackers or bread.

title: moody's sweet potato pie
directions: Heat the oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients and bake in pie shells for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: baked chicken
directions: Place desired amount of chicken in pan so there is no space between pieces.
Spread about a tablespoon of orange marmalade on each piece.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over all.
Bake 1 hour or until tender at 350°, covered.

title: pineapple tea
directions: Dissolve tea in 4 cups of water.
Add remaining ingredients. Serve hot or cold.
Yields 50 servings.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Melt butter.
Add eggs.
Add both mixtures and beat.
Add buttermilk and vanilla and beat. Pour into two deep dish pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until thick and brown.

title: pickled beets
directions: Boil beets.
Remove skins.
Bring the vinegar, sugar, water, salt, cloves and cinnamon to a boil.
Place hot beets in hot jars. Pour syrup over beets to cover.
Seal at once.

title: surrey hill beans
directions: Drain butter beans and kidney beans well.
Saute bacon and onions; pour off 3/4 of the fat.
Mix together the catsup, brown sugar, mustard and vinegar.
Combine all ingredients in casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or heat in crock-pot for 1 hour or more; will be juicier this way.

title: spaghetti meat  sauce
directions: Combine hamburger and onion; brown.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and 1 can water and mushrooms.
Stir in garlic powder, oregano, parsley, bay leaf and thyme.
Cook on low heat for 2 to 3 hours.
Serves 6 or more.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephants in small pieces.
Add water to brown gravy. Cook over kerosene fire approximately four weeks at 465°.
This serves 3,800 people.
If more are expected, add 2 rabbits.
But be careful, most people don't like hares in their stew.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crackers.
Add crackers; stir. Let set at least 1 hour before serving.

title: mulled citrus punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in large saucepan.
Boil 1 minute. Reduce heat and simmer 5 to 10 minutes to blend.
Serve hot. Punch may be chilled.
For party, keep warm in crock-pot.

title: beef loaf with wine
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together with 1/4 cup wine.
Pack into a loaf pan lined with waxed paper and chill.
Turn out on a cookie sheet and score top with the back of a knife.
Mix together melted butter and 1/2 cup wine.
Bake loaf in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour, basting occasionally with butter-wine mixture.
Good with mushroom sauce or sour cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: no-sugar apple pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and 1/4 cup apple juice and set aside.
Simmer the sliced apples and remainder of apple juice together in a saucepan (low heat) until apples begin to look transparent.
Add cornstarch mixture and cook briefly until thickened and clear, stirring continuously.
I add some "I Can't Believe It's Not Butter" when I remove the pan from the heat.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
You can use a crumb topping or a second pie crust on top or nothing.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken with garlic cloves until done. Drain. Shred chicken. Shred cheese. Cook each tortilla in hot pan of oil about 1 minute. Dip tortilla in enchilada sauce, coating each side. Fill tortilla with chicken and cheese. Roll and place in baking dish. Pour remaining sauce over enchiladas, then cover top with remaining cheese. Bake in preheated oven at 350° about 15 minutes until hot and cheese has melted. Enjoy! Serves 12.

title: dream pie
directions: 1st Step:
Blend flour and margarine.
Press down in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook 15 minutes or until slightly brown for crust.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine peanut butter, shortening and vanilla in bowl; mix well.
Add sugar gradually, beating well after each addition.
Add whole eggs one at a time, beating well each time.
Blend in flour; stir in nuts.
Pour batter into a greased pan, spreading it evenly.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until center is firm when pressed with finger tips.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: spinach salad
directions: Dressing:
1/2 c. catsup, 1/2 to 3/4 sugar,
1/2 c. onion, 1/4 c. vinegar,
1/2 c. oil.
Put all into a blender and pour over salad mixture.

title: cherry cheesecake tarts
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until smooth.
Place 1 vanilla wafer in a medium size cupcake container (Reynolds aluminum).
Fill 3/4 full of mixture.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Cool and top each with cherry pie filling.

title: turkey chowder
directions: Cook carcass, remove meat; add the rest.
Cook 20 minutes or until done.

title: grilled scallop teriyaki
directions: You will need 6 long skewers (approximately 12-inches).

title: italian seasoned popcorn
directions: In a very large bowl, combine popcorn and pretzels.
Stir gently while spraying mixture with cooking spray.
Immediately sprinkle with Italian seasoning and garlic powder.
Toss to coat well.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 10 (1 cup) servings.
Each serving: 90 calories, 2 gm protein, 15 gm. carbohydrate, 0 mg cholesterol, 240 mg. sodium and 1 gm fat.

title: quick blackberry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in deep dish. Mix dry ingredients, add milk. Pour batter over melted butter. Pour berries and juice over batter. Bake in moderate oven (350 degrees).

title: mogen david salad
directions: Measure juice from cherries.
Add wine and enough water to make a scant 2 cups.
Heat and add to Jell-O.
Add pinch of salt (optional).
Cool.	Add cherries and put into mold.

title: pie cake
directions: Put all ingredients in a large bowl and stir with a wooden spoon.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: seven cup salad
directions: Mix and let stand for at least 1 hour or longer in refrigerator.

title: yummy gooey popcorn balls
directions: Put all ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Keep at boiling for approximately 10 minutes, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Pour over popped popcorn.
Stir with a spoon or hands.
Butter hands so it doesn't stick to your hands.
Form into balls.
Let cool.
Enjoy!

title: tuna soup
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Add flour and stir to make a roux.
Add milk slowly while stirring.
Add bouillon broth. Break up tuna and add to soup.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Serve with ground pepper on top.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pineapple-cool whip pie
directions: Mix lemon juice, sweetened milk, pineapple and Cool Whip together.
Put into graham cracker crusts and chill for approximately 1 hour before serving.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole dish. Combine the milk,
Italian seasoning, salt and garlic powder in a small bowl.
Arrange potato slices in casserole dish.
Pour milk mixture over when potatoes are tender.
Remove cover and sprinkle cheeses and paprika over potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, for 8 to 10 minutes longer, until cheeses are
melted.
Serve hot.

title: scones
directions: Mix potatoes, shortening and sugar and then add milk that has been cooled to lukewarm.
Add yeast that has been dissolved in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add dry ingredients and knead well.
Dough will be sticky.
Grease top of dough.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Roll out on floured surface, cut into squares and fry as usual.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook until the apples are tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Combine 1/4 cup water with 2 tablespoons cornstarch.
Stir into apple mixture.
Cool to room temperature before filling unbaked pie shell and topping with a crust.
Bake at 420° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: braised leg of lamb
directions: Day before roasting, marinate meat in vinegar, oil, bay leaf, salt and pepper; refrigerate.
Just before roasting, sprinkle with garlic powder and brown in roasting pan.
Add a little water and roast, covered, at 325° for 2 to 3 hours, according to weight. Baste 3 or 4 times during the cooking.
A carrot, parsley root and onion may be added during the roasting for added flavor.

title: irish cream
directions: Add ingredients one at a time, blending 30 to 60 seconds between each.
Use condensed milk can to measure whiskey.
Makes 1 quart.
Will last 3 to 4 weeks in refrigerator.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Add bouillon cubes to broth.
Mix together chicken, broth, cream of chicken soup and Veg-All.
Pour into an oblong pan. Mix flour, milk and margarine.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until golden brown.

title: bavarian (st. nick) salad mound
directions: Combine the following cut fresh fruits:
navel oranges, tangelo, apple, bananas, white grapes and tangerines.
Add mandarin orange sections, almonds, pecans, miniature marshmallows and cherries.
Shortly before serving combine with sweetened whipped cream.
Serves about 20.

title: baked beans with pineapple chunks
directions: Saute onion and pepper in margarine.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes, or heat on top of stove.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Chopped ham or crispy bacon (crushed) may be added.

title: cherry fudge cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs and can of cherry pie filling in large bowl.
Mix by hand.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes. Makes 12 large muffins.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate for 2 hours for flavors to blend.

title: company carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until tender.
Cut carrots in strips and arrange in baking dish.
Combine liquids, salt, pepper and onion.
Pour over carrots.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.
Serves 8.

title: hobo meal
directions: Place hamburger patty on aluminum foil.
Slice potatoes, onion, green bell pepper, carrots, cabbage or any vegetables you like in foil with patty.
Fold foil over all.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix the sour cream, Philadelphia cream cheese and mayonnaise, then add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Be sure to make the night before using.
Serve with various fresh vegetables, such as squash, celery, carrots, bell pepper, cucumber, radishes, etc.

title: custard pie
directions: Combine and pour into 1 unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 25 minutes.

title: val-o-gram cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugars.
Add well beaten eggs. Sift flour, baking powder and soda together.
Add with other ingredients to the creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: caramel nut crunch(about 8 cups snack)
directions: Put salt and sugar on a chicken and put it in a cooking pan. Cook for 3 hours on a real hot stove.
Get raw dumplings at Brookshire and heat them up at home.
Put the chicken in the dumplings and heat up for 6 minutes.
Put a whole lot more salt on them.
Put a little pepper on them.
Serve with potatoes, carrots, corn and salad.
This is called "Sunday Food".

title: garden pasta salad
directions: Combine Miracle Whip, parsley, basil and garlic.
Mix well. Add cheese, broccoli and noodles. Mix lightly.
Chill.
Arrange tomatoes on platter.
Top with salad.

title: crab dip #2
directions: Put crabmeat in food processor or chop real fine and add all ingredients and mix well.
Serve on nacho chips or crackers.

title: crunchy ham and cheese ball
directions: Mix and heat cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Stir in the rest of the ingredients.
Chill a few hours.
Make into a ball.
Roll in 1/2 cup chopped peanuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: cherry blossom delight
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Mix in brown sugar and oatmeal.

Blend in shortening until pieces are the size of peas. Put a layer of oatmeal mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan, then a layer of cherry pie filling and then another layer of oatmeal mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Steam raisins and let set 1 hour; drain.
Beat sugar, eggs and oil until fluffy.
Add flour, vanilla, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in zucchini and raisins.
Fill half 2 or 3 loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 3/4 to 1 hour.

title: crabby baked potato
directions: After scrubbing potatoes, slice 3/4 through lengthwise.
Make crosscuts and scoop out part of potato.
Stuff opening with margarine.
Stuff potato cutouts and some diced onions back into potato opening.
Sprinkle generously with seafood seasoning, garlic powder, Nature's Seasoning, salt and pepper.
Wrap in aluminum foil and bake in oven at 350° or in charcoal or gas grill until soft. Serve with sour cream and chives.
Additional seasonings may be added, if desired.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: In large salad bowl (looks beautiful in crystal clear bowl), layer half of lettuce, then layers of carrots, celery and green onions.

title: tex-mex deviled eggs
directions: Slice each egg in half crosswise.
Remove yolks.
Place in small bowl and mash.
Add green onions, cilantro, jalapeno pepper, mayonnaise and mustard; blend well.
Spoon about 1 tablespoon of yolk mixture in each egg half.
Top each with cheese; sprinkle with chili powder.

title: jackie's chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sour cream, oil, eggs, vanilla and pudding and take 1/3 mixture out and sit aside.
Add the following to the remaining mixture:
chocolate chips, chocolate syrup and pecans. Layer the chocolate, then add the fruit mixture.
Next, add the rest of the chocolate in the bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Grease and flour Bundt pan before pouring in cake mixture.

title: santa's thumbprints
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat Crisco and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add combine oats, flour and salt; mix well. Form 1-inch balls and roll in nuts.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press centers with thumb; fill with preserves.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until light golden brown. Remove to wire rack; cool completely.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix eggs with oil, then add remaining ingredients and mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cut in brownie squares.
Easy to handle.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Spread pie filling in 8 1/2 x 11-inch pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine cake mix, nuts and margarine.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: golden rule oreo cookie cake(serve unto others)
directions: You will need a large 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan or dish.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and season.
While rice is cooking chop onion and celery.
Saute in margarine.
Cook broccoli and season until very tender and drain.
Mix together broccoli, rice, onion, celery and soup.
Melt Cheez Whiz in microwave as directed on jar.
Pour into broccoli and rice and mix well.
Heat in 350° oven about 30 minutes until hot.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with 1 stick melted margarine and 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: lima bean bake
directions: Cook lima beans 10 minutes in salted water.
Mix cheese soup and milk.
Combine with celery, parsley, beans and half the onion rings.
Put into 1-quart casserole and bake at 350° until "bubbly" (about 20 to 30 minutes).
Add remaining onion rings and continue baking until brown and crunchy.

title: layered tuna salad
directions: Layer ingredients and refrigerate.

title: no fail fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter and canned milk together in a pot; bring to a boil.
Once it starts boiling, keep boiling for 5 minutes.
Take mixture off stove.
Add to mixture the peanut butter, flour and Marshmallow Fluff; mix well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate.

title: lime delight
directions: Mix dry Jell-O with cottage cheese.
When well mixed, add Cool Whip.
Stir well.
Fold in drained fruits and nuts.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: fruit pizza
directions: *Pineapple, mandarin oranges, kiwi fruit, cherries, bananas, strawberries, coconut and chopped nuts may be used.

title: potato rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add sugar, shortening, potatoes, salt and eggs.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time, until mixture is not sticky and pulls from side of bowl.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and put in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
For the top, melt the marshmallows and cool.
After cooling, stir in the Cool Whip.
Spread marshmallow-Cool Whip mixture on top of jello. Sprinkle crackers on top. Top all with the candy bars.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Fry sausage and drain off fat.
Butter one side of the bread and place evenly in the bottom of a well-greased 13x9 inch pan. Sprinkle cheese over the bread.
Combine beaten eggs, milk, salt, and mustard and pour over the top.
Sprinkle sausage over this. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
The next morning, bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350.
Uncover and bake for 15 minutes longer. Server 6 to 8.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: You will also need aluminum foil.

title: stuffed pistolettes
directions: Season the meat to suit your taste.
Combine with velveeta cubes.
Set aside.
Slice top off of each roll and hollow out. Fill with meat and cheese mixture and replace end of pistolette. Spray rolls with garlic butter and bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar. Add egg and vanilla. Stir in flour, soda and salt, then add pecans. Mold dough into several small rolls. Wrap in wax paper. Chill overnight. Slice thin and bake at 375° until brown.

title: conch dip
directions: Blend the cream cheese and milk together until very smooth. Add the conch and remaining ingredients.
Serve with fresh raw vegetables.

title: picante chicken and rice
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts with salt; set aside.
In deep pot, saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add chicken broth and picante sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Arrange chicken breasts over the rice.
Cover tightly and simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Garnish with avocado, tomato and cheese.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: taco dip
directions: 1st Layer:
Spread bean dip on a large platter.

title: occidentally oriental vegetable soup
directions: Put soup bone, water, onion and carrot in a large pot.
Bring to a boil, lower heat, cover pot and simmer for 2 hours. Remove bone and cut off all meat.
Return meat to pot. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Heat to boiling and serve hot.
Yields 5 servings.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms and remove stems.
Finely chop stems.
Soak bread in a little water and squeeze dry.
Mix chopped stems, bread, garlic, parsley, eggs, Ricotta, salt and pepper.
Fill each mushroom cap with stuffing mixture.
Arrange mushroom cap with stuffing mixture.
Arrange mushroom caps in shallow greased pan. Drizzle with olive oil; sprinkle with grated Romano cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs well; add cream.
Mix all ingredients well.
Put into a buttered casserole and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook beef, pepper and onion until brown.
Drain off fat.
Add taco seasoning and water. Stir in soup.
Pour into 2 to 3-quart dish. Bake 10 minutes. Cut biscuits in half.
Place, cut side down, over hot mixture in spoke fashion around edge.
Bake with cheese on top for 15 minutes. Serve hot.

title: weight watchers pineapple cake
directions: Follow directions on cake mix and add the pineapple in mix. Bake in a Bundt pan.
A delicious and healthy dessert!

title: wiener schnitzel
directions: Marinate veal cutlets in lemon juice in a glass dish for one hour.
Pat dry with paper towels; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Beat eggs in a bowl with water.
Dip each cutlet, coating well, first in flour, next into egg mixture and then in bread crumbs. Place each breaded cutlet on sheet of waxed paper.
Refrigerate at least 20 minutes before cooking.
Heat oil or shortening in heavy 12-inch skillet.
Add cutlets and cook over medium heat 3 to 4 minutes on each side or until brown, using tongs to turn.
Serve immediately with lemon wedges.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Mix cream cheese, bacon bits and pimientos.
Fill celery stalks with mixture.

title: granny's sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar. Blend in egg and add vanilla to mixture. In separate bowl, mix together flour, salt and baking powder, then add to butter mixture. Take 1/3 of dough and roll out to about 1/2-inch in thickness and cut with cookie cutters. Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes. Glaze cookies using 1/4 cup powdered sugar and 3 to 4 teaspoons water. You can also add cream cheese and a dash of almond extract to glaze for better flavor.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower in small pieces.
Mix with onion, bacon and cheese.

title: 4-bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and chopped onions; add beans.
Put in casserole and bake 40 minutes until hot.
Serves 12.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Mix brown sugar, soy sauce and mustard; pour 1/2 of this mixture over the chops.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; turn meat over and pour remaining sauce over chops.
Continue baking for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: millie's meatballs
directions: Form into cocktail size meatballs.

title: sunday chicken
directions: Brown chicken in margarine and place in a covered casserole, skin side up.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all together.
Add about 1 tablespoon to 1 cup boiling water.

title: chili con queso
directions: Melt cheese and milk in double boiler; add the onion, chilies and garlic salt; simmer.
Serve in chafing dish with chips.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until creamy and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk and sour cream to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and lemon extract.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Roll in ball (size of walnuts), roll in sugar and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until almost done, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: blueberry oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix buttermilk, oil and egg; soak oatmeal in liquids.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to liquids; stir just to mix. Fold in blueberries.
Spoon into 18 average size muffin cups, greased or sprayed with nonstick spray.
Bake at 400° about 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken continental(no peek chicken)
directions: Put rice in 9
x 13-inch casserole.
Place the chicken on top of rice. It should cover rice.
Mix soup, water, salt, thyme, celery flakes and paprika together and pour over rice and chicken. Sprinkle onion soup mix over top of dish.
Cover casserole with foil before baking and keep covered while baking.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: corn flake candy
directions: In pan cook sugar, syrup and cream until a soft ball forms.
In separate bowl mix corn flakes, nuts and coconut.
Pour contents of pan over contents in bowl.
Mix in vanilla.
Drop by spoon on wax paper.
Let sit on wax paper until drops become hard.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Drain all the fruit well.
Combine oranges, pineapple, coconut, sour cream and marshmallows.
Blend gently.
Add the cherries for color.
Chill a few hours and serve.

title: pasta carbonara
directions: Prepare fettuccini according to package directions.
Drain. Gradually add milk to combine salad dressing and garlic in small saucepan.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat. Blend egg.
Toss with hot fettuccini until well coated.
Add remaining ingredients and toss lightly.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Put cranberries through the food chopper.
Grate one of the oranges and add the rind to the cranberries. Put the pulp of the two oranges through the food chopper and add to the cranberry mixture.
Add sugar to this.
Add the boiling water to the jello and when cool, mix with the cranberry mixture.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: crawfish etouffee(pronounced a-too-fay)
directions: Melt margarine in aluminum Dutch oven.
Season crawfish tails with creole seasoning.
Add paprika to margarine.
Saute crawfish tails about 5 minutes.
Remove crawfish and set aside.
To pot, add onions, bell pepper and garlic.
Saute well, at least 10 minutes.
Return crawfish tails to pot and add 2 cups water and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir and simmer slowly about 40 minutes. Add mixture of cornstarch and water slowly until slightly thickened.
Serve with rice.
Serves 4.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown oil, sausage and onion in electric skillet approximately 5 minutes.
Add water, au gratin potatoes and carrots.
Mix and simmer until carrots are done, 20 to 25 minutes.
Cook and drain broccoli.
Add broccoli and cheese to casserole.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.

title: candied popcorn
directions: Put popcorn and nuts in extra large baking pan.
Grease the bottom of a large roaster, melt margarine.
Add Karo and brown sugar.
Bring to a good boil.
Remove from stove and add soda. Mix well, being careful since this hot mixture will foam up.
Pour over corn mixture and stir.
Bake in 250° oven for 45 minutes. Stir every 15 minutes.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Put vanilla wafer in bottom of cupcake liner.
Fill 1/2 to 3/4 full with cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes until set. Top with cherry pie filling.

title: party potatoes
directions: Heat the first 4 ingredients to scalding.
Mix the remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Pour the hot liquid over the instant potato mixture; blend well (a mixer works best).
Pour into a lightly greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding just enough mayonnaise to moisten.
Mix well and serve.

title: uncle ned's soft molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add molasses, eggs and spices; mix.
Add flour alternating with the milk.
Add baking soda; mix well.
Roll dough in balls size of walnut.
Flatten on cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen cookies.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Heat cranberry sauce, flavored gelatin of choice and 2 cups water until gelatin dissolves.
Soften unflavored gelatin in 1 cup cold water and stir into hot mixture.
Refrigerate until mixture begins to thicken.
Fold in nuts, apples and celery.
Pour into an 11 x 7 or 8-inch square pan and chill thoroughly.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce.
May be put into individual molds if preferred.
This is easily doubled or tripled and keeps very well for several days.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash; cook in water over medium-high heat until tender; drain and mash.
In large bowl, combine squash, sour cream, carrots, onion, soup, salt and pepper; mix thoroughly. Spray a 3-quart casserole dish with vegetable spray.
Sprinkle 1 cup of crackers on bottom of casserole dish.
Pour squash mixture over crackers; top with remaining cup of crackers.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Combine butter, sugar, egg and flavoring.
Add bananas, cream and nuts.
Add flour.
Beat until well mixed.
Fill bread tin 2/3 full.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Each biscuit makes three dumplings.
Separate biscuit into 3 flakes and wrap a slice of apple in each.
Place in 13 x 9 dish and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Mix remaining ingredients together, bring to a boil.
Pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Cover bottom of pie shell with half of the berries.
Mix sugar and flour.
Pour half of the flour mixture over the berries in the shell.
Add the remaining berries and the rest of the sugar mixture.
Then dot with the margarine.
Add 1/2 cup of water and cover with the other pie shell.
Slit the top crust with a knife before placing in the oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all together and pour in buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spinach dip bread ring
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and water chestnuts together.
Add spinach when you are ready to serve.
Hollow out a round sourdough bread.
Serve with spinach dip in the middle and wedges of bread around.

title: pepper cabbage
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar in small saucepan. Boil 5 minutes. Cool mixture. Grate cabbage. Sprinkle salt over the top of cabbage. Let stand for 1 hour. Squeeze out excess water. Stir in carrots, bell pepper and celery. Gently fold in sugar and vinegar mixture.

title: moist pineapple sheet cake
directions: Cook cake according to directions on box.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Punch holes in cake while cake is still hot and pour Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Let cake cool and then spread drained pineapple over top.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Coconut can be spread over Cool Whip if desired.
Refrigerate.

title: cajun spice mix
directions: Combine ingredients in a small jar.
The mix can be kept in a tightly covered glass jar in a cool, dry place out of direct light for up to 4 months.
Makes 1/4 cup.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix ingredients, except butter, and pour into greased loaf pan.
Do not knead.
Pour melted butter on top, reserving a small amount.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Take out of pan and brush with butter.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix until crumbles the flour, sugar, oats and Crisco. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: fudge pie
directions: Put butter and chocolate chips in saucepan on medium heat until melted. Remove from heat; add flour, sugar, salt and meal. Add milk; stir until well combine, then add eggs. Mix well and pour in pie shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sparkling coolness
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Add ice and serve.

title: black bean salsa
directions: Drain and rinse black beans and Shoepeg corn. Place in large mixing bowl. Add cilantro, pepper, onion, tomatoes and jalapeno pepper. Blend well. Drizzle the canola oil and lime juice over the top of mixture. Add salt and garlic powder and mix well. Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours. Serve with baked tortilla chips.

title: checkerboard cake
directions: Melt chocolate squares in 3/4 cup boiling water.
Add Knox gelatine which was dissolved in 1/4 cup cold water.
Leave this mixture cool.
Beat egg yolks and add sugar.
Beat well, then beat egg whites stiff and fold into chocolate mixture and pour over cubed angel food cake.
Mix well.
Put into torte pan.
Chill and top with Cool Whip.

title: bean dip(yields 4 cups)
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, place the beans, water, onion, garlic, cumin seed, pepper, molasses and tomatoes; simmer for 1 hour.
Add the lemon juice, chili powder and salt.
While the beans are still hot, add the oil and grated cheese.
Mash or blend until smooth. Serve hot or cold with corn munchies or homemade crackers.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips, butter and peanut butter together.
Pour over cereal and coat well.
Pour powdered sugar into bag.
Dump in coated cereal.
Shake until well coated.
Pour into airtight bowl.

title: chocolate - caramel - nut candy
directions: Melt over hot water the chocolate chips and shortening.
Stir until melted and smooth.
Pour half into an 8-inch foil lined square pan.
Refrigerate until firm (15 minutes). Return remaining to low heat.
Combine over hot water the caramels, butter and water. Stir until caramels are melted and mixture is smooth. Stir in nuts.
Pour over cooled chocolate.
Spread and refrigerate 15 minutes. Top with remaining chocolate.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Cut in squares.

title: egg fu yong
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni according to package.
Cool.
Beat eggs with soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Stir in Rice-A-Roni, bean sprouts and onion.
Drop mix by 1/2 cupful onto greased griddle.
Brown on each side.

title: polynesian chicken
directions: Combine first three ingredients in large bowl.
In another bowl, mix dressing of mayonnaise, chutney and curry.
Cover both bowls and chill at least 1 hour.
Just before serving, drain liquid, if any, from chicken mixture.
Add sliced banana, peanuts, coconut and drained oranges.
Mix in dressing until well coated.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Pour sugar over rhubarb; let set overnight.
Cook over low heat until soft.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin and Kool-Aid; mix well until all powder is dissolved.
Pour into pint jars and seal. Makes 2 pints.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar. Add egg; beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in milk and vanilla. Sift together dry ingredients and blend into creamed mixture. Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
To make a design (roll the mixture), add extra 1/2 cup flour.
Chill 1 hour before using. Use 1/2 at a time, keeping 2nd half chilled.

title: hawaiian sausage dipper
directions: On high heat, brown sausage in a very large skillet.
Drain fat.
Reduce heat and add spices, tomato sauce and pineapple. Simmer for 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: instant hot browns
directions: Prepare mashed potatoes according to package directions. Open soup and heat.
Do not add water!
Arrange sliced bread on serving plates.
Spoon potatoes onto bread.
Ladle soup over all. Takes 10 minutes.
You will need 1 can soup, 6 slices bread and 2 cups of potatoes for 3 servings.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding and Cool Whip.
Add fruit, nuts and marshmallows. Stir and chill for 1/2 hour.

title: hello dolly bars
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle remaining ingredients in the order given.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.
Cut immediately.

title: pastor's wild enchiladas
directions: In a frying pan, brown ground beef.
In a separate pan, heat enchilada sauce; then pour in container large enough to dip tortillas in.
Take a tortilla and dip in sauce, then lay in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish/pan.
Spread a large spoonful each of meat and cheese inside tortilla.
Follow with a small spoonful of olives and onions.

title: peppery scallops
directions: Rinse the scallops under cold water.
Pat dry with paper towels.
In a medium size bowl toss the scallops with the melted butter to coat well.
On a paper plate, mix the bread crumbs, basil and pepper.
Dip one flat side of the scallop into the crumb mixture.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet, pepper side up. Broil close to the broiler for about 5 minutes.
Serve with lemon wedges.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine ingredients as listed and bake in a greased 2 to 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, milk, sugar and butter.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, about 30 minutes, stirring often.
Add vanilla. Pour into serving dish.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together as listed.
Beat well.
Bake in a greased loaf pan for 35 minutes in a moderate 375° oven.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beating well after each addition.
Add flour, extract and 7-Up.
Beat well.
Pour in floured greased pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: nut raisin pie
directions: Cream together 3 egg yolks, sugar and butter.
Mix together nuts, raisins, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg, salt and vinegar.
Add to eggs, sugar and butter.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Slowly beat in 1/2 cup sugar.
Fold into mixture.
Bake in uncooked pie shell at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Heat mushroom or celery soup with cream cheese; stir until smooth.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup of water.
Add to soup mixture and stir.
Add crabmeat or shrimp, mayo, scallions and celery.
Put in mold.
Refrigerate overnight.
Garnish with shrimp.

title: makeover peanut butter pie
directions: In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Mix in peanut butter and sugar.
Gradually add milk, mix well.
Gently fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Brown ground meat and drain.
Set aside.
Mix up cornbread mix.
Pour 1/3 of cornbread mix into casserole dish.
Mix meat and other ingredients with 1/3 of remaining mix and add to casserole dish.
Cover with last 1/3 of mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake 1 hour and 25 minutes at 325°.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Steam zucchini, mushrooms, carrots and onion until tender. Add spinach and spices until warm.
Layer noodles, veggies and cheeses with cheese over last layer of noodles.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: quick jam cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Add flour, jam and walnuts.
Mix may be thick, but bake as directed, on mix box.
Top with cream cheese frosting.
Great with holiday meals.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Steam or saute vegetables and set aside while preparing sauce.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Soak Doritos in chicken broth and spread over greased casserole dish.
Put chicken pieces over Doritos and the cans of soup.
Sprinkle onions and peppers over this.
Spoon on Ro-Tel. Cover top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Mix Cheerios, pretzel sticks, cheese crackers and mixed nuts. In a shallow pan, mix butter, garlic salt, Worcestershire sauce and celery salt.
Pour second mixture over first mixture.
Stir. Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Stir after 15 minutes.
Makes 6 cups.

title: chicken and chips casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup potato chips and place in a casserole dish. Top with remaining chips; cover and bake at 450° for 15 minutes. Serves 8.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All.
Grate Cheddar cheese. Mix all ingredients, except crackers and butter.
Pour into greased casserole dish. Mix butter and crackers.
Sprinkle over top. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1 cup cheese and chips.
Turn in 8 x 12-inch buttered casserole.
Combine cheese/chips and spread on top.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: lemon lush
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pat into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: fruit crisp dessert
directions: Combine topping ingredients and set aside.
Combine flour, sugar, sour cream, vanilla and eggs and mix well.
Spray 9 x 9 cake pan with Pam.
Spread fruit cocktail in pan.
Pour batter over fruit.

title: spanish rice
directions: In a 2-quart microwave saucepan, combine uncooked rice, onion, garlic and oil.
Cook uncovered on High 4 to 6 minutes or until onion is tender, stirring once.
Add broth, water, tomato sauce and pepper.
Cook uncovered on High 5 to 7 minutes or until boiling.
Stir cook on Medium 16 to 19 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed, stirring every 5 minutes.

title: pumpkin pound cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with electric mixer about 2 minutes or until soft and creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears.
Combine flour and next 5 ingredients.
Combine pumpkin and rum.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture alternately with pumpkin mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix at lowest speed just until blended after each addition.
Pour batter into grease and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan on a wire rack 10 minutes; remove from pan, and cool completely on wire rack.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients into a jar and shake.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Bake in loaf pans which have been sprayed with Pam.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine peaches, 1 1/2 c. sugar and water. Bring to a boil; simmer to allow fruit to soften. Blend 3 Tbsp. flour, 1/4 c. sugar and spices. Pour into peach mixture. Stir until thickened. Remove from heat. Pour into 12 inch skillet or cobbler pan. Cool slightly.
Combine remaining flour, sugar, baking powder and milk, blend well. Season with salt. Pour in an irregular shape over center of cobbler. Bake 45 minutes until golden brown at 400°.

title: microwave divinity
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water. Put them in microwave for 3 minutes on High. When it stops, stir it and then cook again on High for 6 to 8 minutes or until it forms a hard ball when dropped in cold water.

title: barbecue cocktail sausages
directions: Mix all together and place in crock-pot. Heat thoroughly.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly flour an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar over bottom pan.
Place pecans and pineapple on brown sugar.

title: fool you pie
directions: Place bread in small serving dish.
Add apples, sweetener, spices and water.
Microwave for 3 minutes.

title: fiesta banana cake
directions: Stir shortening just to soften.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Add 1/2 of milk and bananas.
Mix until flour is dampened, then add rest of milk, eggs and nuts.
Bake in 3 greased and floured pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Put together layers with whipped cream and mashed bananas.
Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: 5 + can casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in an 8 x 8-inch pan. Sprinkle reserved noodles on top.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Can be doubled for a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Just double all ingredients.

title: roadside potatoes
directions: Heat cream and butter together and add salt.
Place potato patties in oblong baking dish or pan.
Pour cream mixture over potatoes.
Sprinkle top generously with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: tiny pecan tarts
directions: Combine cream cheese (softened) and margarine; blend in flour. Chill 1 hour.
Shape into balls about 1-inch thick and press into tiny ungreased muffin tins.

title: hamburg barbecue
directions: Brown meat.
Mix together with other ingredients and simmer.

title: creamy celery and garlic soup
directions: Combine oil and green onion in a microwaveproof 2-quart casserole dish.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 2 minutes, or until soft.
Add garlic, celery, potato, 1/2 cup water, bouillon granules and parsley flakes.
Cover and microwave on High for 8 minutes or until vegetables are soft, stirring once.
Place in processor or blender with pepper and salt.
Cover and microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes, until heated through.
Add grated cheese, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: taco bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook hamburger and onion until beef browns. Drain.
Spoon into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Stir in taco seasoning (dry), tomato sauce and corn.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix Bisquick and milk.
Pour over beef mixture. Bake 35 minutes until golden brown.
Serve with sour cream for topping.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Add bread, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Cover with a layer of corn and onions.
Top with tomatoes.
Cook and simmer on range for 20 minutes.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Spread potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan or dish and combine 1/2 cup melted margarine, cheeses, sour cream, soup, pimentos, onion and salt in bowl; mix well.
Spoon over potatoes. Top with corn flakes and drizzle with 1/2 cup butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Wash cranberries.
Put in saucepan.
Add orange juice.
Bring to boil over low heat.
Cook 5 - 10 minutes, until skins break. Add sugar.
Cool.
Store in refrigerator.

title: dried peaches(for fried pies)
directions: Set overnight.
Cook until thick.
Put in jars and seal.

title: bread pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees. Pour pudding, in large bowl, whisk together milk, eggs, sugar and vanilla until well blended. Place bread in 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with 1 small can of drained, sliced peaches. Pour milk mixture over peaches. Cover with foil. Bake 30 to 45 minutes. Remove foil and continue baking 10 minutes.

title: creamy turkey and broccoli
directions: Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions.
Stir in 1/2 can French fried onions.
Spread stuffing over bottom of greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Arrange broccoli spears around outer edge of dish.
Prepare cheese sauce mix according to package directions using 1 1/4 cups milk.
Stir in sour cream.
Combine turkey and cheese sauce.
Mix well.
Pour over broccoli.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining onions over turkey and bake uncovered 5 minutes more.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix together cream cheese, butter, Cool Whip, vanilla pudding, milk and powdered sugar.
Put following in pot: layer with cookies crushed and alternate with creamed mixture and gummy worms.
Top is crushed cookies.
Top with flowers.

title: tutti-frutti ice cream
directions: Pour in freezer; add 1 liter Big Red drink and fill freezer.

title: blitzes
directions: Cut crust off bread.
Roll thin with rolling pin.
Mix cream cheese, yolks and 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat with a spoon.
Spread mixture on bread.
Roll up.
Cut in thirds.
Dip in butter and roll in 3/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.
(Can be frozen; thaw first before baking.)
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: marshmallow fudge
directions: To keep pasta, rice and potatoes from boiling over, add a teaspoon of oil or water.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Broil with water over breasts for about 1 or 1 1/2 hours. Debone the chicken and tear it into small pieces.
Mix the first 5 ingredients over the chicken and put in a greased casserole dish. Crumble up the roll of Ritz crackers over the mixture and add butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: lucy's pie crust
directions: Take 1/3 cup flour and 1/3 cup water, make a paste.
Add to remaining flour, salt, butter and shortening.
Mix well until hands become clean.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain fat.
Add all ingredients and simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour mixture in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Lay cheese on top.
Place biscuits on top of cheese.
Cook until biscuits are brown.

title: peanut butter cornflake cookies
directions: Put sugar and syrup in a saucepan and let it come to a boil, slightly stirring all the time.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add corn flakes and mix.
Pour in a greased pan.
Press down.
Cut in squares while warm.
(Easy to make and very good.)

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Put nuts and coconut on top of Pam.
Mix cake mix and place on top of nut mixture.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar and butter.
Pour this over cake mixture and swirl into batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.
Cool completely before removing from pan.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Add salt. Add flour. Add some raisins,
coconut, nuts, cherries and crushed pineapple (drained well). Bake at 275° to 300° until done.

title: potatoes deluxe
directions: Thaw hash browns; mix with soup, sour cream, onion, margarine and cheese.
Place in baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: wild mushroom cream sauce
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet.
Add onions and saute 3 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add brandy and ignite.
When flames are out, return to heat.
Add beef broth and boil until reduced to 1/2 cup. Add whipping cream and bring to boil.
Stir mushrooms into simmering sauce.
Reduce heat and simmer until tender, about 20 minutes.
Season to taste (salt and pepper).
Wonderful as a steak sauce.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Combine ingredients and roll into balls.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
May freeze and cook later.

title: diabetic candy
directions: Blend together peanut butter, milk, sweetener and vanilla.
Add raisins and crushed graham cracker.
Form into balls or in 1 bar shaped piece.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Mix together Oreo cookies, melted margarine, 1/2 can Hershey's syrup and nuts.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour caramel topping on crust.
Slice ice cream in 1/2-inch thick slices and place on top of caramel.
Pour 1/4 can of Hershey's syrup on ice cream. Cover with plastic wrap and tinfoil and freeze for 2 to 3 hours. Remove from freezer and spread Cool Whip over cake.
Drizzle with remaining 1/4 can Hershey's syrup.
Sprinkle with nuts if desired. You may substitute Rice Krispies for the nuts or use any flavor ice cream in place of vanilla.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Mix 2 tablespoons picante sauce and 1 cup water in shallow pan.
Place tortillas in this and soak for 5 minutes.
Next, place tortillas on paper towel to drain.

title: rice pudding
directions: In a heavy saucepan, scald the milks together.
Combine cornstarch, salt and sugar.
Stir into hot milk mixture, stirring constantly over medium heat until thick and smooth.
Add rice. Reheat to a full boil.
Remove from heat.
Pour a little of the hot mixture into beaten eggs while stirring rapidly.
Return egg mixture to hot milk and rice.
Stir until thickened (only a minute or two).
Remove from heat.
Stir in spices and vanilla.
Chill. Makes 8 (1/2 cup) servings.
Raisins can be added.

title: green bean parmesan(microwave)
directions: In glass container (measuring cup), cook 1 tablespoon margarine on High in microwave for 20 to 30 seconds until melted. Stir in bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Cook 45 seconds to 1 minute until crisp and brown; stir halfway through cooking.
Set aside.

title: lil mednis' pecan rolls
directions: In a 9 x 1 1/2-inch round pan, stir together the caramel and melted oleo.
Arrange nuts on caramel-oleo.
Separate bread sticks, but do not unroll.
Place bread sticks over caramel, oleo and nuts; 8 just fit.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Let stand 3 minutes before inverting on plate.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Thinly slice cabbage, bell pepper and onion.
Bring to a boil the next 6 ingredients.
Pour boiling mixture over cabbage mixture and mix well.
Refrigerate.
Toss several times.
Will keep two weeks.

title: caramel icing
directions: Boil hard for 1 minute, then add 1/3 cup milk and cook 2 minutes.
Cool; add 2 cups powdered sugar.
Cream until smooth and spread on cake after cool.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs; add flour and sugar.
Stir in butter, milk and vanilla.
Pour in pie shell and sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine crumbs and 1/2 cup melted butter. Press into a 9 x 12 pan. Chill. In small mixing bowl, combine eggs, 1/2 cup butter and confectioners sugar. Beat on high speed about 5 minutes until thick and creamy. Spread on chilled crust. Arrange sliced banana, slightly overlapping to cover creamed mixture. Spread well drained pineapple over bananas. Top with whipped cream. Sprinkle with nuts and cherries. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together the sugar, butter, milk and cocoa in a saucepan and boil 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove and add the oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla, then drop by spoonfuls into wax paper.
Yields 20.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook ground beef. Blend together in blender all the remaining ingredients.
(It may take 2 blenders full.)
Mix blended mixture with ground beef and pour into saucepan or slow cooker. For best results, cook 6 or 7 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: peanut butter confection(cookie)
directions: Blend all together except Rice Krispies.
Then gently fold in Rice Krispies.
Press in pan and let stand in refrigerator a few hours.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: do ahead breakfast
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Combine eggs, milk, dry mustard and salt.
Add bread and sausage to egg mixture.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Refrigerate, covered, overnight. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.
(You can double this recipe.)

title: texas panhandle coleslaw
directions: Combine vegetable oil, vinegar, sugar, pepper and salt as a dressing.
Combine vegetables.
Just prior to serving, add sunflower seeds and crushed noodles.
Pour dressing over all.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix water and yeast together and let rise. Mix sugar, salt, shortening, eggs and 1/2 of flour. Then add yeast mixture. Mix and add remaining flour. Add milk and mix. Make sticky dough and knead well. Rise until double
shape. Roll out and shape rolls. Let them rise again. Grease pans and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: mulled cider
directions: Orange Sparkle:
Reconstitute frozen orange juice with sparkling soda instead of water.
Serve with maraschino cherry.

title: italian love cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: old time jam cake(mrs. sam wise, smithfield, kentucky)
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add beaten egg yolks.
Sift flour, cocoa and spices together.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk to mixture and mix well. Add jam, raisins and beaten egg whites.
Bake in a 350° oven.

title: cocoa pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Add cocoa.
Beat 3 egg yolks well, add to milk and other ingredients and cook on top of stove. Beat 3 egg whites stiff and put on top.
Brown at 325°.

title: italian dressing
directions: Beat all ingredients thoroughly.
Add 1 clove garlic.
Store in refrigerator.
Shake well before using.

title: easy fruitcake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Generously grease and flour a 9 or 10-inch tube pan.
Sift together flour and baking soda; set aside. In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 50 minutes to 2 hours or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean. Cool 15 minutes.
Turn out of pan and cool completely.
Glaze and garnish as desired.

title: trail mix supreme
directions: Use several fresh fruits.
For each skewer, choose at least 2 fresh, canned or dried fruits that have a nice contrast in color, flavor and texture.
Avoid soft or messy fruits.
Cut large fruits into bite size pieces.
Drain canned fruits well and blot any extra juice on paper towels.
If you use light-colored, fresh fruits that tend to darken such as apples, apricots, bananas and pears, dip them in lemon juice.

title: cucumber dill canape
directions: Mix Italian dressing mix with mayonnaise and cream cheese. Spread cream cheese mixture on cocktail bread slices.
Top with cucumber slice and sprinkle with dill weed.
Refrigerate.

title: philly fudge
directions: Place cheese in bowl; cream until soft and smooth.
Slowly blend the sugar into cheese.
Add melted chocolate; mix well.
Add vanilla, salt and nuts.
Mix until well blended.
Press into a well-greased, shallow pan.
Place in the fridge until firm and cut into 1-inch squares.
Store covered in fridge.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: In Dutch oven, cook celery and onion in margarine until tender. Add water, chicken, carrots, bouillon and pepper.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add noodles and parsley. Cook until noodles are tender.

title: lighter chocolate torte
directions: In a large bowl, combine gelatin and cool water and allow to stand 5 minutes.
Add boiling water and stir until gelatin has completely dissolved.
Add cocoa powder and margarine and stir until margarine has completely melted.
Set aside to cool.

title: five-minute fudge
directions: Combine evaporated milk, sugar and salt in medium saucepan. Heat over high heat to boiling, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat and continue to boil for five minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Stir in nuts, chocolate chips, marshmallows and vanilla. Mix well. Pour into buttered baking pan. Cool completely. Cut into squares.

title: glazed fruit
directions: Prepare fruit and drain.
Discard syrup.
Chill in a pretty bowl.
Dissolve cornstarch in 2 tablespoons of cool water.
In saucepan combine water, sugar and jello.
Heat to a soft boil. Add cornstarch and stir until it begins to thicken.
(If mixture gets too thick, thin with small amount of cool water.)
Cool in refrigerator.
When cool, pour over fruit and mix.
Keep refrigerated.
Makes approximately 3 quarts.
Acceptable to prepare half of recipe.

title: apple cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix together 2 cups sugar, flour, oil, juice, eggs, vanilla and baking powder.
Combine cinnamon with 3/4 cup sugar.
Mix apples with lemon juice and some of the cinnamon-sugar.
Let stand about 10 minutes.
Pour half of the batter into a well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top the batter with apple mixture and then with remaining batter.
Sprinkle with nuts and the remaining cinnamon-sugar.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Cool in pan and cut in squares.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Bring sugar, oleo, cocoa and milk to a boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Take off stove and add peanut butter, oats and vanilla. Mix quickly and drop by spoonfuls on plastic wrap or waxed paper.

title: angel pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand, Cool Whip and lemonade until well blended. Pour into crust.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: apple and sausage cornbread stuffing
directions: Prepare corn muffin mix according to package directions, cool and crumble.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Place sausage in a large, deep skillet and cook over medium high heat until evenly brown.
Drain and set aside.

In skillet over medium heat, slowly cook and stir the mushrooms, celery, onion and garlic until soft. In a large bowl, mix the crumbled cornbread, sausage, mushroom mixture, apple, bread, salt and pepper.
Transfer the mixture to a medium baking dish and bake for 45 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine and top with sprinkled sugar and small pats of butter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: no bake pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and
2 Tbsp. milk together and put in bottom of graham cracker crust.
Mix vanilla pudding, 1 C. milk, pumpkin, and spices; place on top.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken!
directions: Melt butter in large frying pan.
Dip and cover pieces of chicken with butter.
Remove to baking dish.
In another pan, brown bacon and onion; gradually add flour, stirring until smooth. Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Put half of this sauce on the chicken and allow to bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Add remaining sauce and bake another 20 minutes.

title: crockpot lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Drain fat.
Add spaghetti sauce with meat and onion.
Fill the jar that the sauce was in 3/4 full of water.
Pour 1/4 of the water into the meat mixture and stir.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef and onion together.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer 15 minutes.
Just before serving, add grated cheese.

title: red cake
directions: Mix flour, cocoa and soda.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add the vanilla. Combine buttermilk, food coloring and vinegar.
Add the dry ingredients alternating with buttermilk mixture.
Bake in layer cake pans at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: golden yellow punch
directions: Mix ingredients and chill.
Before serving, add 1 bottle ginger ale.

title: double-good fudge
directions: Combine 1 package powdered sugar, chunky peanut butter and 1/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons milk in a large microwave-safe bowl, stirring well.
Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla. Stir until smooth. Cover with wax paper and microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes. Spread evenly into pan sprayed with vegetable cooking spray.

title: tangy crab dip
directions: In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, prepared mustard, worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, seasoned salt, and liquid hot pepper sauce.
Stir in crab until all is blended.
Serve with crackers.
Serves 16.

title: mexican appetizer
directions: Soften cream cheese; mix green chilies, picante sauce and green onions (minced) together.
Mix with cream cheese.
Spread on flour tortillas and roll.
Wrap in wax paper in plastic bag. Chill at least 2 hours.
Cut in pieces and serve.
Serve with or without picante sauce.

title: crab casserole
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Place in oblong greased casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake covered for 25 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and add onion rings and bake 10 minutes more. Serves 5.

title: tuna mayo casserole
directions: Prepare Kraft dinner as directed.
Add tuna, tomatoes, parsley and salt and bake 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: southern sweet potatoes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Put in dish last 3 ingredients and sprinkle with sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shimmering peach cream
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Measure 1 cup and add cold water; chill until slightly thickened.
Add ice cream to remaining gelatin and stir until melted and smooth.
Pour into serving bowl. Chill until set, but not firm.
Arrange peach slices on gelatin-ice cream mixture.
Top with clear gelatin.
Chill until set.

title: frozen pie crust
directions: In a large bowl or pan, mix flour and salt well with an electric mixer. Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Stir in corn syrup and water. Divide dough into fist-size balls. Place in individual bags, then into a larger resealable bag. Freeze.

title: herb-marinated chicken kabobs(servings:  4)
directions: Lightly flatten chicken breasts; cut each breast lengthwise into 3 one-inch strips.
Place chicken in bowl with zucchini and bell pepper.
For marinade, combine vinegar and remaining ingredients in jar.
Cover; shake vigorously.
Pour marinade over chicken and vegetables.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Drain marinade into small saucepan.
Boil marinade. Alternately thread chicken and vegetables onto skewers; brush with marinade.
Broil 3 to 5 inches from heat source, until chicken is cooked, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Turn and brush occasionally with marinade.
Serve with rice, if desired.
Calories:
Fat:
8 grams.

title: easy cheese rolls
directions: Combine 1 cup flour, sugar, yeast and salt. Set aside. Heat butter, milk and water until warm (120 to 130 degrees). Add milk mixture to the flour mixture and stir well. Add eggs and 1/2 c. flour, stir well. Stir in remaining ingredients. Stir well until stiff dough forms. Shape dough into 12 equal balls, place in greased muffin cups.
