Cover and let rise in a warm place for 45 minutes or until double in size. Bake at 375 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes. Remove from muffin cups and cool on wire rack.

title: potato chip dish
directions: Mix all well, place in a large casserole.
Crush 2 to 4 cups potato chips, sprinkle over the top of chicken.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1/2 hour.
Serves 12 or more.

title: banana yogurt milkshake
directions: Place banana, yogurt and milk into a blender; blend well.
Add ice to make it slushy.

title: caper salad dressing for pasta
directions: Puree the first 8 dressing ingredients.
Slowly pour in the oil, blending continuously until smooth.
Pour the dressing over the pasta.
Serves 4 deliciously.

title: stuffed bell peppers with shrimp
directions: Melt margarine.
Saute seasonings.
Add shrimp; cook until pink and tender.
Add soups; cook 15 minutes.
Add cooked rice until desired consistency.
Stuff in cleaned peppers; top with bread crumbs and bake, uncovered, in a 350 degree oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pot roast and vegetables
directions: Rub roast with garlic.
Heat oil in 4 1/2-quart dutch oven. Sear roast on all sides.
Add bay leaf, soup mix, sherry and onion.
Cover.
Place on medium heat.
When lid is hot to touch, reduce heat to low.
Cook 2 hours.
Add vegetables and cook 1 hour or until tender.
Serves 8.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine corn syrup, sugar, salt, vanilla, butter and lemon juice and stir until well blended.
Stir in eggs well, but do not beat.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° and bake 35 to 40 minutes longer or until crust and filling are golden brown.
Allow to cool and serve plain or with whipped cream.
Extra delicious and rich!

title: lemon squares
directions: Combine 1 cup flour and 1/4 cup powdered sugar; add butter and pecans, mixing well. Spoon into 9-inch square baking pan. Press into pan evenly. Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes until lightly browned.

title: noodles
directions: Mix together the beaten egg, salt and milk.
Then stir that into the flour in a medium bowl.
Roll thin and let dry for 20 minutes.
Then roll again, cut and let dry for 2 hours.
Drop noodles into boiling mixture of chicken broth.

title: crusty cheese tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes in half crosswise.
Place, cut side up, in ungreased, shallow baking pan.
Sprinkle with combined salt and pepper, then with cheese.
Combine Rice Krispies, paprika and butter; sprinkle over cheese.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for about 20 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: five ecstasy
directions: A wok is a must.
Cut steak and chicken into small, bite-sized pieces.
Cut vegetables in same manner.
Get everything and put it close to stove.
Heat wok.
Add 1 spoon oil and put steak and chicken in, moving them around constantly until almost done.
Add vegetables and keep stirring.
Nothing should stop moving.
Cook about 2 minutes.
Take out and put into dish.
Put 1 more teaspoon oil in empty wok.
Stir-fry eggs and noodles 2 minutes.
Dish out and enjoy.
Pleases all five senses.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Put into 2 quart casserole dish.
Add beans and mixture of soup and milk, and cut-up onions. Place tater tots on top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Take from oven and put Cheddar cheese on top, until melted.
Serves 4.
This can easily be doubled for more people.

title: chicken and rice(club member: keisha hudson)
directions: Spread rice in large pan; add 3 cups water. Salt lightly and sprinkle a small amount of soup mix over rice. Place chicken parts on rice and water. Sprinkle with rest of soup mix. Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: jack cheese and green chili quiche squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat eggs and egg whites with electric mixer until fully blended. Combine flour and baking powder and stir to mix well. Add to eggs.
Beat with electric mixer to blend well. Add Monterey Jack and cottage cheeses, green chilies, green onions and cilantro, if desired.
Mix well.

Pour mixture into a 7 x 11-inch nonstick baking pan that has been sprayed with a nonstick vegetable cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until firm and lightly brown on top. Cool in pan for 10 minutes before cutting into 28 squares. Serve warm with salsa or picante sauce for dipping.
Makes 28 squares.

title: deviled crabs
directions: Saute onions and green pepper lightly in melted butter. Combine all remaining ingredients in large bowl, blending well. Stuff crab backs with mixture, filling each generously.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 to 35 minutes or until top of crab meat lightly browns.

title: hawaii style toast
directions: Mix margarine, cinnamon and curry powder.
Spread on one side of each slice of bread.
Broil spread side up until lightly toasted.
Top each slice with one slice of ham and 1/2 slice of pineapple.
Broil until warm.
Top with 1/2 slice of cheese; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Broil until cheese is melted.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and chop into pieces.
Grease a medium sized casserole dish with butter.
Mix together chicken, soup and sour cream.
Pour into dish.
Mix crushed crackers with melted margarine and sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes and mix all other ingredients with potatoes with hand mixer.
Place in greased casserole, baking dish, dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until hot in center.
Broil for 5 minutes.

title: curried peas casserole
directions: Spread the bottom of a long baking dish with melted butter. Spoon rice in dish.
Then spread peas which have been drained. Sprinkle almonds which have been toasted to the top of the mixture.
Spread cooked chicken over the mixture.
Blend and pour cream of chicken soup, milk and grated Cheddar cheese over all. Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: pecan balls
directions: Make 5 or 6 balls of ice cream and roll in chopped pecans to completely cover.
Wrap each ball for freezing.
Freeze and store. Serve with Hot Fudge Sauce or Caramel Sauce.

title: sand cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Roll out thin.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Roll in sugar. Cut out. Place in cookie pan with turner.
Cook at 350°.

title: salmon patties
directions: Take bones out of salmon and mix all ingredients together. Fry in frying pan. Great meal!

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Add dry ingredients, which have been sifted together.
Add vanilla.
Roll out on floured board and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 400° for approximately 10 minutes.
(Do not grease cookie sheet.)

title: strawberry cobbler
directions: Stir a dough of first 3 ingredients.
Put 1/2 in round pan. Bake a few minutes until golden brown.
Let cool.
Mix strawberries with sugar.
Pour over crust.
Put the other 1/2 of dough on top of berries.
Bake until top dough is golden and baked through.

title: freezer cookies
directions: Mix together and form roll.
Place in freezer overnight. Slice in 1/4-inch slices.
Bake at 350° to 375°.

title: verna's pirate's pie
directions: Saute meat, onion and green pepper in 1 tablespoon oil.
Add tomatoes and salt.
Cover and simmer over low heat 15 minutes. Stir in kidney beans and pimento.
Pour mixture into 2-quart baking dish.
Follow directions for dumplings on muffin mix. Spoon dumplings close together around edge of casserole to form a solid border.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: very blueberry muffins(lo-cal)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray 12 muffin cups with cooking spray. Combine dry ingredients with milk, egg and oil.
Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill muffin cups.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: jiffy pineapple upside-down cake *
directions: Mix 1/2 box of your favorite yellow cake mix as directed.
Then melt butter or margarine in an iron skillet frypan; dissolve and pour mixed batter over pineapple and sugar.
Cook in oven at 325° for about 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool a minute, run knife around side and turn onto large plate, so as to catch the juice from the bottom of the skillet.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Pour sugar over apples; let stand 30 minutes.
Add oil and beaten egg.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add apple sugar mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° in greased and floured 8-inch square pan.
Serve with whipping cream or frost with powdered sugar frosting flavored with lemon.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients well and add prunes and buttermilk with soda.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.
May be baked in two loaf pans, if desired.
One for the freezer and one to eat now!
Baking time should be reduced when using the two loaf pans.

title: broccoli cheese dip
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in margarine.
Mix all remaining ingredients in well.
Serve warm with Doritos or tortilla chips.

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: Bring large pot of salted water to a boil.
Cut zucchini lengthwise into 1/8-inch thick slices.
Parboil in 3 batches, 5 to 6 minutes.
Remove from pot and drain well on paper towels.
In large saucepan, saute onion and garlic in oil over medium-high heat until soft, but not brown, 6 to 8 minutes.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; cool.
Pour in cold water in which yeast has been dissolved.
Add beaten eggs.
Add flour slowly.
Knead until dough is ropy.
Make out rolls; let stand 2 hours before baking.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: mexican chip dip
directions: Fry meat (like for Sloppy Joes); drain very well.
Return to frypan.
Cut cheese in chunks to be put on top of meat.
When melted, add both jars of taco sauce.
Stir together.
Serve warm.

title: peanut butter sticks
directions: Cut crust from bread.
Cut each slice into 5 strips.
Dry out in a 250° oven but do not brown.
Heat peanut butter in oil; dip strips of bread in mixture, then roll in cracker crumbs.
These keep well in freezer.

title: carrot, raisin and sour cream salad
directions: Soak carrots in ice water for 1 hour; drain and grate coarsely. Add remaining ingredients except sour cream. Mix lightly. Add sour cream and toss.

title: ray's clam sauce
directions: Cook oil, seasonings, garlic, onion, parsley and pepper until onions are clear.
Add tuna, anchovies, clams and butter.
Cook over low heat for 30 minutes.
Serve over vermicelli or angel hair.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Pour into 2 small or 1 large pie crust.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add flour, salt and baking soda mixture to ingredients.
Then add 1 egg at a time.
Blend in sour cream and then flavors.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: 6 layer dinner
directions: Layer the ingredients in a baking dish as listed.
Bake for approximately 2 hours in a 300° oven.

title: cabbage and beef soup
directions: Brown beef; drain fat.
Add all ingredients.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat; simmer 1 hour.

title: bacon wraps
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cut bacon in half. Using two crackers, spread cream cheese on one cracker and top with the other; wrap 1/2 of bacon piece around sandwiched cracker.
Place on a cookie rack in a shallow pan and put bacon wrap on top.
Cook 15 minutes and turn bacon wraps over and cook an additional 20 minutes or until done.

title: pepperoni salad
directions: In large salad bowl, combine all ingredients, except dressing. Pour salad dressing over.
Toss lettuce mixture lightly with dressing.
Sprinkle with salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste.

title: children's banana boats
directions: Chop peanuts on cutting board.
Leaving bananas in peeling, gently wash and pat dry with paper towel.
Carefully slit top of banana lengthwise, leaving 1 inch uncut at each end.
Cut away 1/2 inch of peel on each with scissors forming a pocket.
Put Cool Whip in a bowl.
Scoop banana out of peelings with teaspoon.
Add mix with Cool Whip.
Mix with rubber scraper.
Fill each peeling with 1/4 mixture.
Sprinkle with 1/4 peanuts and cherry.
Serve right away or refrigerate 1 hour.
Fun to make with your child.

title: day ahead cake
directions: In large bowl, beat together sugar, egg and margarine.
In a separate bowl, mix together Cool Whip, strawberries and pecans. Fold this mixture into sugar mixture.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan make a layer with vanilla wafers.
Pour 1/2 of strawberry mixture over this and make another layer of vanilla wafers.
Pour remainder of strawberry mixture over this layer.
Cover and chill overnight. Makes 15 servings.

title: pineapple meatballs
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and bake at 350° until brown.
Mix pineapple juice, sugar, vinegar, ketchup, ginger and Worcestershire sauce in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add cornstarch to thicken. Pour over meatballs and pineapple and return to oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix all of these together.
Pour into graham cracker crusts and refrigerate.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream margarine with confectioners sugar, then blend in vanilla, sifted flour and chopped pecans.
Chill and then take out pieces of dough and roll into about the size of a walnut or mold into fingers.
Bake on ungreased sheet for about 15 minutes at 350°.

title: buckeyes(candy)
directions: Mix sugar, peanut butter and margarine in a large bowl; chill 30 minutes.
Form into small balls.
Melt wax and chocolate chips together in top of double boiler.
When mixture is very hot, dip bottom half only of candy into chocolate.
Place on waxed paper to cool.

title: graham cracker quickies
directions: Separate graham crackers into fourths, dividing along lines. Place in a single layer on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Combine milk, brown sugar and margarine in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring until smooth.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in wheat germ, coconut and cinnamon.
Spread evenly over graham crackers.
Bake for 7 to 8 minutes or until golden.
Cool completely.

title: lemon bars
directions: Cream ingredients together and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: gone-all day stew
directions: Mix together soup, water and flour until smooth.
Combine with remaining ingredients in covered roaster.
Bake at 275° for 4 to 5 hours.
Add about 1 cup frozen peas during last hour.

title: spanish coffee cake
directions: Mix first six ingredients together and reserve 1/2 cup for top of cake.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan or 2 (9-inch) round pans.
Sprinkle the 1/2 cup reserved crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: squash pickles
directions: Layer squash and sprinkle with salt until all squash are in a large container.
Cover with cold water and soak overnight.
Drain squash.
Combine squash with all other ingredients and boil 3 or 4 minutes.
Seal in hot, clean jars.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: In a heavy Dutch oven, combine flour and oil until smooth. Cook over medium-high heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Reduce heat to medium. Cook and stir about 10 minutes more or until mixture is reddish-brown (the color of a penny). Add onion, celery, green pepper and green onions; cook and stir for 5 minutes. Add chicken broth, water, okra, paprika, salt, oregano and pepper. Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes. Add seafood and parsley. Simmer, uncovered, about 5 minutes more or until seafood is done. Remove from heat; stir in file. Yield: About 6 quarts.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until done.
Put in baking pan with other ingredients.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Cream together the cheese and butter. Stir in vanilla and powdered sugar, a little at a time, beating until smooth.

title: sweetheart salad
directions: Heat pineapple and sugar until warm.
Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Stir into pineapple mixture.
Add lemon and cherry juice.
Set aside to cool.

title: fruit dip
directions: With electric mixer, cream: cream cheese and juices.
When creamy add marshmallow cream and mix.
While mixing add Cool Whip. Serve with fresh fruit like:
grapes, apple slices, strawberries, pineapple chunks, melon cubes, peach slices, banana chunks.
Dip fresh fruit in orange juice to keep from turning brown.

title: microwave fresh mushroom stuffing
directions: Place mushrooms, onion, celery and butter in a 3-quart casserole.
Cook, covered, on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until tender.
Stir in stuffing mix and enough broth to moisten. Stuffing should be very moist.
Spread stuffing evenly in casserole and cook on High for 2 to 4 minutes.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 4.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, crumbs, onion, milk, egg, parsley, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Make into meatballs.
Brown in shortening.
Remove from skillet and pour off fat.
Heat chili sauce and jelly until jelly melts.
Add meatballs.
Simmer uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain well and set aside.
Saute onions in butter until soft.
Add spinach.
Cook and stir over medium heat, about 3 minutes.
Blend in salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Set aside.
Combine eggs, half and half and bacon bits and blend well.
Stir in spinach and cheese.
Spoon into pie crust or tart shells.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes (20 minutes for tarts).

title: icebox cake
directions: Cream butter and
sugar;
add
eggs (well beaten), then add nuts and pineapple.
(At this point, original recipe says: "line a cracker box
with
wax paper").
Then pour 1/2 of this mixture over two
layers
of
vanilla
wafers or sugar cookies which have been placed in bottom of pan.
Add another layer of cookies,
then the
remainder
of
the
mixture.	Cover
with another layer of cookies
and
let
mold
for
48 hours in the refrigerator, then cover
top	with
whipped cream.
Slice and serve.

title: deer steak casserole
directions: Cook deer steak in pressure cooker for about 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Cut up into small pieces.
Spread evenly in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spread on top of deer steak the salt and pepper, chicken soup, broccoli soup and Stove Top dressing.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add water and vanilla.
Mix well. Add flour and pecans.
Shape into small balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for about 20 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: sweet relish
directions: Grind first 4 ingredients.
Put salt on mixture; let stand 2 hours.
Drain 2 hours or overnight.
Add remaining ingredients and cook up all together and can.
Makes about 5 pints.

title: quilting party salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water and let partially jell.
Add the next 4 ingredients and let congeal until firm.

title: ken's sauerkraut sauce(for meat)
directions: Saute apple and onion in a little butter in the bottom of a heavy saucepan.
Then add the other ingredients and simmer until thickened.

title: creamy chicken casserole
directions: Prepare elbow macaroni according to package.
Drain.
Prepare sauce in 2-quart saucepan over medium heat.
In hot butter, cook mushrooms and onion until tender.
Do not brown.
Stir in remaining ingredients except macaroni and bread crumbs.
Heat through.

title: caramel pie
directions: Cook until thick brown sugar, sugar, flour, cornmeal, egg yolks, milk and margarine.
Takes 2 to 30 minutes of stirring for it to thicken.
Pour the filling into baked pie shell.
Spread with meringue or Cool Whip, if desired.

title: pork chop delight
directions: Trim as much of
the
fat
from chops as you can.
Heat oil in a large
skillet and brown chops on both sides.
Spread rice evenly in the bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan that has been well-greased.
Add
hot water, 1 teaspoon of the salt and the red pepper.
Place
the
chops
over
rice;
top
with onion, bell pepper,
remaining
teaspoon
of salt and black pepper.
Spoon soup over
the
top; cover and bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until rice and chops are tender.

title: barbecued chicken(light)
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients in a 2-cup glass measure. Microwave, uncovered, at High for 1 1/2 minutes, or until mixture boils.
Set aside.
Arrange chicken in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish with thickest portions toward outside of dish.
Cover with wax paper; microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Drain drippings. Rearrange chicken.
Brush with sauce.
Cover; microwave on High 9 to 10 minutes, or until done.
Rearrange and brush chicken with sauce after 5 minutes.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Serves 6, 163 calories per serving.

title: crab or shrimp ball
directions: Mix all ingredients very well.
Form into a small round ball, flattened on top.
Cover and chill.
Just before serving, top with chili sauce.
Serve with crackers.
Recipe will feed several.

title: blueberry log roll
directions: Brush jelly pan or cookie sheet with oil.
Line with wax paper; oil paper.
Beat yolks and regular sugar until pale yellow and thick.
Beat in ground walnuts and baking powder.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into egg and sugar.
Spread batter in pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cover with damp cloth and cool.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Spread Cool Whip on cake. Roll up.
Cover cake with Cool Whip and blueberries.

title: chicken with curry dill sauce
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, melt butter. Add the flour, salt and pepper; stir until smooth. Gradually add milk and bring to a boil. Boil and stir for 2 minutes. Remove from the heat. Add the mayonnaise, dill and curry; stir until smooth. Set aside.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream peanut butter and shortening together.
Add sugar. Blend well.
Add well beaten eggs in.
Sift flour and soda together.
Add to creamed mixture and blend.
Roll into small balls.
Dip fork in cold water and crisscross and press down.
Add a slice of walnut to top.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peanut brownies
directions: Place oleo and chocolate in glass mixing bowl.
Microwave on High, uncovered, 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until softened, stirring once.
Stir until melted.
Blend in sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in an 8-inch square glass baking dish, greased on bottom only.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 5 1/2 to 6 1/2 minutes or until no longer doughy, rotating dish 3 or 4 times.
Remove plastic.
Cool and cut into bars.
Makes about 24 bars, 75 calories each.

title: pasta, southern style, with chicken and shrimp(calorie saver)
directions: Bake chicken with skin on at 350° for 45 minutes or until almost tender.
Drain, then remove and discard the skin and bone.

title: ada's most requested chocolate cake
directions: Combine cocoa and hot water, stirring.
Cool.
Cream oleo and sugar; beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Blend in vanilla and cocoa mixture.
Sift flour, salt and soda together; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beating well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites; pour mixture into 2 greased and floured pans. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost.

title: the original granny casserole
directions: Cook noodles per package directions.
Place in large casserole dish or 2 medium casserole dishes.
Mix cream cheese, cottage cheese, sour cream, onion and pepper until well blended.
Spread over the noodles.

title: punch for a bunch
directions: Mix together Kool-Aid, sugar and Tang.
Add water to make 10 gallons.
Just before serving, add the ginger ale and sherbet. Let sherbet float on top.
Makes 12 gallons.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Refrigerate 24 hours or at least overnight before serving.

title: garbage pail candy
directions: In microwave melt butter, peanut butter and chocolate chips. In large bowl, mix the syrup (butter mixture) with Rice Chex, raisins and salted peanuts.
In small plastic trash bag, put powdered sugar and contents of the bowl and shake!

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Put milk on in double boiler.
Mix egg yolks until there are no yellow specks.
In separate bowl, mix flour, sugar and salt, then mix this with egg yolks and small amount of cool water.
Add to milk and cook until thick.
Add coconut, vanilla and small slice of oleo.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with egg whites meringue. Place in oven and brown meringue.
Remove from oven and let cool before cutting.

title: peppernuts
directions: Mix together, adding flour one cup at a time.
It will be very difficult to stir at the end.
Make into balls.
Bake at 350° for 13 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops on both sides in hot frying pan. Grease deep casserole dish and place 3 chops in dish. Combine flour, salt, pepper and parsley. Sprinkle half over chops. Cover with half of potatoes. Repeat layers. Heat milk in skillet in which chops were browned. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Uncover for the last 20 minutes to brown top.

title: cheesy hash brown casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine hash browns, cheese, soup, sour cream, onion and 1/2 cup butter. Spread into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with paprika. Combine crushed corn flakes with remaining butter and sprinkle on top of casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until hot and browned.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish with bread slices.
Put 2 or 3 cups chicken or more on bread.
Cook mushrooms and put over chicken.
Add water chestnuts.
Dot with mayonnaise.
Top with cheese slices.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken.
Mix soups and pimentos.
Pour over all.
Cook, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Sprinkle bread crumbs mixed with oleo on top.
Broil until brown.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add to margarine mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats and raisins; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until brown.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; remove to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Store in airtight container.

title: oklahoma fruit pie
directions: Mix well and pour in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 300°.
Cool, then top with Cool Whip.

title: full meal casserole
directions: Use 1 to 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Brown ground beef and season.
Put meat in bottom of dish.
Mix soup and milk together; pour over beef.
Chop up and add onion.
Cover with Tater Tots. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Combine 2 cups flour and 2 teaspoons sugar. Cut in butter with a pastry blender until it resembles coarse crumbs or meal.
Press crumb
mixture evenly in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown. Set aside.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar; sift into a large mixing bowl.
Heat shortening, cocoa and water to a rapid boil.
Pour over flour-sugar mixture; beat well.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well. Bake in a greased and floured 16 x 11 x 1-inch pan for 20 minutes.
Ice in pan.

title: applesauce cake in a jar
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs, applesauce and water.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to applesauce mixture. Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased pint jars (wide mouth) about 1/2 full.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Remove 1 jar at a time.
Wipe sealing edge clean.
Put the lid and ring on tight.
(Jar will seal as cake cools.)
Store as you would regular canned goods.
Makes 8 pints.

title: grandma's greatest potato pancakes
directions: In a bowl, grate potatoes and onion.
Add flour, salt, pepper and nutmeg; blend.
Fry in hot greased skillet until golden brown. Perfect!

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Tie all spices in cheesecloth or put in tea strainer.
Set on high for 1 hour, then to low.

title: rocky road pizza
directions: Mix powdered sugar, butter, egg, vanilla and almond extract. Stir in flour, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Cover and refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Sift flour.
Mix 3/4 cup sugar, 1 1/2 tablespoons cocoa, salt, baking powder, melted butter, milk and vanilla and pour mixture into a greased 10-inch glass pie dish.

title: chili con carne
directions: Heat non-stick skillet 30 seconds; add oil and heat 30 seconds.
Add onion and beef; cook, stirring until onion is brown, 10 to 12 minutes.
Reduce heat to low; add chili powder and cumin. Cook, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and broth; cook 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Dissolve cocoa in hot water; add cocoa mixture and beans; cook 5 more minutes. Serves 4.

title: dad's marinated salad
directions: Shred cabbage and put into a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Add layer of sliced onion, separated into rings.
Add layer of sliced pepper.
Pour sugar over this.
Do not mix.
Combine vinegar, salt, celery seed, mustard and oil; bring to boil.
Pour over cabbage while hot.
Do not mix.
Put in refrigerator until cool or overnight.
It is best when it has had time to marinate.
Serves 8.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in carrots, raisins, nuts, coconut and apple.
Beat eggs, oil and vanilla. Stir into the flour mixture until batter is just combined.
Spoon into well-greased muffin cups, filling to top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 14 large or 20 small muffins.

title: sugar-free cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until dry.
Mix all ingredients well and bake in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan or Bundt pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix kaukauna spread, dry ranch mix into cream cheese.
Chop the chipped beef into fine pieces.
Add to cream cheese mixture and combine well.
Onto waxed paper, sprinkle shredded cheese.
Place mixture onto cheese and roll into a ball shape, as you incorporate the cheese coating.
Place in the refrigerator.
Makes one large ball, or you can divide mixture before rolling onto cheese and make several small balls.

title: new england vegetables
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain and set aside.
In a 2-quart glass casserole, melt butter in microwave on High for 30 to 60 seconds.
Stir in cornstarch; microwave on High an additional 1 to 2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds until butter slightly thickens.
Add vegetables, including broccoli, garlic salt and Parmesan cheese.
Heat on High in microwave 5 minutes, stirring twice.

title: a taste of hawaii(honey-ginger chicken)
directions: Twist crown of leaves from pineapple.
Using sharp knife, halve pineapple lengthwise (refrigerate unused half).
Cut fruit from shell, then into chunks; set aside.
Place chicken between 2 sheets of waxed paper; using wooden mallet or rolling pin, pound chicken to 1/2-inch thick cutlets.
Rub chicken with garlic; season with salt (if desired) and pepper.

title: nine bean soup
directions: Sort and wash bean mix.
Place in a dutch oven; cover with water, and soak overnight.
Drain beans; add 2 qts water and next 4 ingredients, cover and bring to a boil, reduce heat, and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 30 minutes stirring occasionally.

title: cheese soup
directions: Combine bouillon cubes, 1 quart water, cubed potatoes, celery, onion and diced carrots.
Cook until tender, about 10 minutes. Add Italian vegetables which have been chopped in blender.
Cook 10 minutes longer.
Add cream of chicken soup.
Rinse cans with small amount of water and add to mixture.
Cut up cheese and add. When melted, it is done.
Store leftovers in refrigerator.
When using leftovers, cook slowly, stirring constantly.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Sift together the flour, salt and baking powder.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until onion is tender.
Drain water. Add margarine, salt, pepper, 2 cups stuffing and sour cream.
Stir until mixed.
Line buttered casserole dish with remaining 2 cups stuffing.
Pour squash mixture into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.
Add cheese and bake until melted.

title: date nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir enough just to mix ingredients.
Put in greased loaf pan and bake for 1 hour.

title: picnic basket squares
directions: Cream the sugar and oleo together.
Add eggs, flour and vanilla.
Beat well.
Spread batter evenly into greased jelly roll pan.
Mark into 24 squares. Place 1 tablespoon of filling in center of each square.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
When done, sprinkle over top with powdered sugar.

title: rumaki
directions: Mix together oil, soy sauce, ketchup, vinegar, pepper and garlic. Cut chicken livers in half and marinate in mixture for 4 hours.
Drain. Wrap bacon around chicken liver and water chestnut. Secure with toothpick.
Roll in brown sugar. Broil 10 minutes until crisp.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Place berries in a 9-inch square baking dish.
Combine 3/4 cup of sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Sprinkle over berries.
Dot with butter.
Roll pastry to fit pan and place on top of berries.
Trim and seal edges.
Brush with milk and sprinkle with 1 tablespoon of sugar.
Make slits in top.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Can be frozen before or after baking.

title: elfin dream cookie drops
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well after each addition.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Decorate with frosting of your choice (cream cheese frosting is delicious on these!).

title: kobe's pink sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Keeps indefinitely in refrigerator.
Great with fried rice and stir-fry.

title: seafood dip
directions: Knead softened cream cheese with shrimp or crab and form into a ball.
Top with seafood sauce.
Serve with Ritz or butter crisp crackers.

title: quick and easy salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon, reserving 2 tablespoons liquid. In mixing bowl, mix salmon, egg and onion until sticky. Stir in flour. Add baking powder to salmon liquid; stir into salmon mixture. Form into small patties and fry until golden brown in hot shortening, about 5 minutes per side. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: wild duck with turnips
directions: Chop onion and celery.
Peel and chop turnips.
Cut up duck. Brown flour in oil.
Add onion and celery; cook for 5 minutes. Put duck and turnips in to brown.
Add water to barely cover duck. Cover pot and slow cook for 1 1/2 hours.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Melt oleo; add cocoa and Coke and bring to a boil.
Pour this mixture over flour and sugar.
In a bowl, combine beaten eggs, buttermilk and soda and add to flour mixture. Add marshmallows.
Bake in a single large pan, sheet cake size, greased and floured at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: memphis corn pudding
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix all ingredients in large mixing bowl until blended.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes, or until lightly browned and set.

title: reduced fat new england clam chowder
directions: Drain clams, reserving the juices. If necessary, add enough water to the clam juice to make 1 cup.

title: chocolate oatmeal cake
directions: Combine oatmeal and boiling water; set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar; add oatmeal mixture, eggs, vanilla.
Then add flour mixture.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° until done.
Top with frosting.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Cook broth, milk, lemon juice and flour until thick.
Put chicken into buttered casserole, pour broth over chicken.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
May add vegetables as desired (corn, peas, etc.).

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C). Bake potatoes in preheated oven for 1 hour.

title: cornmeal pudding
directions: Put milk in large saucepan and bring to a boil.
Using low heat, slowly stir in cornmeal and let cook a few minutes, stirring constantly; add salt.
Take off stove and let cool for a few minutes.
Add milk to thin a little; then add one well-beaten egg, sugar and allspice.
Pour into casserole and bake in a moderate oven about 35 minutes.
Stir twice while baking.

title: peanut butter oat bars
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Mix top six ingredients.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 inch pan.
Bake 12 - 14 minute until brown.
Cool before topping.

title: tangy party meat balls
directions: Roll the first 7 ingredients into firm, small balls (1 1/2 inches).
Set aside.
Make sauce from the next 4 ingredients. Place meat balls with sauce in baking dish.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease pan with butter.
Pour in pie filling and pineapple. Sprinkle cake mix (1/2 to 3/4 box).
Cover with pecans.
Take butter and cover over with the pecans.
Cook in 350° oven for an hour.
Get crust light brown.
No cover is necessary.

title: dutch potato salad
directions: For a very different salad, try mixing romaine lettuce, small diced Vidalia onion (or other mild sweet onion), sliced strawberries topped with poppy seed dressing.
It's wonderful!

title: pork chops 'n coke
directions: In a pan or skillet, melt butter and mix with salt and pepper. Lay pork chops in melted butter mixture. Pour ketchup on each chop and pour enough Coke to cover the chops in the pan. Let come to a boil. Simmer for 45 minutes or until tender and sauce begins to thicken.

title: old fashion chocolate creams
directions: Mix butter and milk with electric mixer; add powdered sugar a little at a time, until creamy.
Cool in freezer.
Mix chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler until melted.
Form into balls and put back in freezer for a little while until firm.
Dip balls in chocolate with toothpick and put on wax paper to cool.
Makes a lot of candy.
